{"_id":"06dx5obmoUeXf37E","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","content":"","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d6wak2736pv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/6.1. Enchantments","color":"#000000","name":"6.1. Enchantments","children":["PlI3MhjIncD23HfQ","hMwfLYBr28XXXvaw","pbCQNBzz4ARtuBAk","sG7NzEEiEQKZAHro","jfvLAutQQwzkl4zw","Iw2cbSmJkGTg6Bnc","BsmS4It9vSMq0KRw","EIua6OVfmlKSXvnM","kyZD4VX3J6GxNKzg","pIXs0JkdAj0IYDDL","ccnpocDWh1OSxnxO","Chvdt2b5TVbrkveK","MyF1K4eUC8jq5ZZe","xnM0pGSbPLv4BpAC","ofFuPTnVboV6K9vd","iuFAwlTJRQ2ANEFK","LnvOqhHPsx6eq0vg","gaP0zf6waEQzXWLZ","3pyIPNVJUdcDgShP","kIpE7V9cwUa2USNX","zDplrIRoqRkzZOx1","fvcAtgJJdxub8J5r","PvuH3yi0ex3BiWzF","nBdcRfjZECSXGLg8","PlIcz5SJyqS0CzRb"],"folderPath":["temp_5n9ndtjortv","temp_otr25ys05qi"]}}}
{"_id":"0F1FhrL8lyjaSRiW","name":"Push","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Push</h2>\n  <div>\n\t\t<img src=\"/assets/art/45 Bar Fight.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n\t\n\t<p>Sometimes characters may want to push a foe in hopes of knocking him out of position, prone, or even into a deadly hazard.</p>\n\t<p>Pushing a foe is an action that requires opposed roll of Strength. If the attacker is successful he pushes the foe back 1″ (two yards), or twice that with a raise.</p>\n\t<p>A character who’s successfully Pushed must make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll (at −2 if the attacker got a raise) \n\t\tor be knocked @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n\t<p><strong>Running:</strong> If the attacker runs at least 2″ (four yards) before the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Push]{Push}, he adds +2 to his total.</p>\n\t<p><strong>Size Matters:</strong> Double the distance pushed if the attacker’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size %26 Scale]{Scale} is larger than the foe’s. \n\t\tCreatures may not generally Push a foe more than two Sizes larger then themselves unless they have exceptional Strength for their Size (GM’s call).</p>\n\t<p><strong>Skill:</strong> The attacker or defender may roll Athletics instead of Strength if they choose.</p>\n\t<p><strong>Shields:</strong> Attackers and defenders add their shield’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonus to their Strength \n\t\t(or Athletics) rolls when pushing.</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.p859xBP2z8otE8Ga"}}}
{"_id":"0JGowJy94gy81aSV","name":"High Adventure","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>High Adventure</h2>\n<p>Characters can spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to gain the one-time use of a Combat Gain a new @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge}. They have to meet the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} and any Edge requirements as usual but can ignore Trait requirements. Multiple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} can be spent in one round for multiple Edges, either for different effects or in order to meet a needed requirement to gain another Edge.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rv4q29jrhjs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.CivzuUolPzMkydQ3"}}}
{"_id":"0ZqgoyXmkyJpscoU","name":"1 Using Magic Items","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"chapter-heading\">\n\t\t\t<h1>Magic items</h1>\n\t\t\t<figure class=\"chapter-number\">Savage Pathfinder</figure>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t \n\t\t\t \n\n\t\t\t<p class=\"drop-cap\">This section contains descriptions, prices, and abilities for magic items found on Eberron. Some are rare, possibly one-of-a-kind relics sought after by great heroes and nefarious evils. Others are relatively common items sold in city markets, found in monster lairs, or wielded by enemies. Such magical treasures are a boon to all Pathfinders as they quest across the wild lands of Eberron. </p>\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\">Using magic items</h1>\n\t\t\t<p>Each type of item on the following pages tells you how it’s used, but there are a few common rules between them:</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Active Powers are Actions:</span> An item that requires a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait roll} is an action unless it says otherwise. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} means the user takes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} (and loses a charge if the item has them).</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Edges and Abilities:</span> If an item grants an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Edges]{Edge} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Special Abilities]{Monstrous Ability} and the wielder already has that Edge, it grants the improved version (if there is one).</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Minor &amp; Major Powers:</span> Some items grant minor or major powers using the powers listed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{here}. A minor power automatically activates with the effect of a standard success, and a major power activates with the effect of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} (no Trait roll is made). Unless the item says otherwise, this is an action and the effect lasts for the power’s full Duration and cannot be maintained.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Stacking:</span> If two sources would increase a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Trait}, use only the highest modifier (effects don’t stack). Increases to a Trait from a magic item’s effects don’t count for determining @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Advancement]{Trait Advancements}. They do affect secondary statistics like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} or Toughness, however. </li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Multiple items:</span> a character can only wear one magic item in each location (head, eyes, shoulders, neck, chest, belt, wrists, hands, feet). Putting on a second necklace or a second belt, for example, has no effect. The exception to this rule is rings. A character can wear two rings and benefit from both magical effects.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Enemies with Magic Items</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>Enemy characters and monsters equipped with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchanted} and magical items have the bonuses conferred by those items built into their profiles.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>An evil knight wearing @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Heavy Breastplate]{plate armor} enchanted with the Aegis enchantment, for example, might have a Toughness of 12(5), where the plate armor's bonus of +4 has already been increased by the Aegis enchantment's +1.</p>\n\t\t\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/andoran-cover.webp\" />\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Purchasing Magic Items</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Most towns have an apothecary shop with a few potions for sale, a few local merchants reselling magical items, or even individuals looking to sell off devices they no longer need. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>When the adventurers want to buy magic items, roll on the table below to see what's available that week (or month if it's a particularly isolated or low-magic area).</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The table has three entries:</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Potions &amp; Scrolls:</strong> Half the items are potions and half are scrolls, rounding in favor of potions. Roll randomly from the tables on the following pages.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Healing:</strong> This tells you how many @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Potion of Minor Healing]{potions of minor healing}, ubiquitous across Eberron, are available from various vendors for 150 gp each. This is in addition to any healing offered by local clerics or healers (prices for a cleric's services are equivalent to potions of <em>healing</em>).</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Other Items:</strong> This tells you how many other magical treasures may be found or purchased in the settlement. If the result is positive, roll on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Other Item Categories]{Other Item} table to determine the category, then roll on the appropriate subtable. If the category is a Wondrous Item, the GM chooses which item is available.</p>\n\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t<colgroup>\n\t\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t</colgroup>\n\t\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"4\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tMagic Items availability\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t</th></tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tType\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tPotions &amp;<br />Scrolls*\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tHealing<br />Potions\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tOther<br />Items*\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Village</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6−2</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>1d4</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d4−2</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Town</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6−1</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>1d4+1</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6−2</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>City</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>1d6</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6−1</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Large City</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6+1</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>1d6+1</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>d6</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t\t</table>\n\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t<colgroup>\n\t\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t</colgroup>\n\t\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"dark\" colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tOther Item Categories</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\td20\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tType\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>1–11</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Available Armor &amp; Weapons]{Armor &amp; Weapons}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>12–13</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Available Rings]{Rings}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>14–16</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Available Rods &amp; Staves]{Rods &amp; Staves}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>17–18</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Available Wands]{Wands}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>19–20</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Wondrous Items</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t\t</table>\n\t\t\t<h3>Purchasing Items</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>Exactly where the items are available is up to the Game Master. Common or relatively inexpensive items might be for sale at a shop or merchant's stall. Rare or expensive items might require finding an elusive seller or completing some task in addition to the cost in gold.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Exotic Items</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>A hero might seek out a specific magic item rather than waiting for it to appear at random. In that case, the character can either commission the item with a down payment (usually half its total cost in gold pieces), or perform a task or quest of some sort.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>At the Game Master's discretion, finding someone to make or sell such items might be an adventure on its own, or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} roll with a penalty determined by the item and the size of the settlement.</p>\n\t\t\t\n<h2 class=\"example\">Example: Shopping in Sandpoint</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>The party is about to set off on a quest to defeat an orc warlord. They decide to stock up on potions and other magical items before entering the warlord's domain.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The adventurers are in a town, so the GM rolls on the Potions &amp; Scrolls column and determines there are three potions and two scrolls. She rolls randomly on the potions and scrolls tables to see which specific brews are available.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Next, she rolls for Healing Potions and gets a total of 3. The party scoops up all of them.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Then she rolls on the Other Items column and gets a 2. She rolls a d20 twice and gets a ring and a rod. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Ring table gives her a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Ring of Protection, Minor]{ring of minor protection}. She decides it's for sale at a second-hand merchant shop in town.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Rods table results in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Rod of Negation]{rod of negation}. That's a fairly rare item, so the GM tells the group it's owned by a retired mage who will only sell it for a favor. They travel to the mage, who agrees to sell the rod at half value if the party will chase away a dangerous group of bugbears that have moved into her favorite herb-gathering spot.</p>\n\t\t\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/crafting.webp\" />\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t<colgroup>\n\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t</colgroup>\n\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"dark\" colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAvailable Armor &amp; Weapons\n\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\td12\n\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\" style=\"text-align:left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\tItem\n\t\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>1</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Weapon with a (1) @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchantment}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>2</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Armor with a (1) @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchantment}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>3</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Shield with a (1) @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchantment}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>4</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Weapon with a (2) @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchantment}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>5</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Armor with a (2) @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchantment}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>6</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Shield with a (2) @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Enchantments]{enchantment}</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t