ls of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Conjures an ally of various sorts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Conjures mundane animals under characters control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Moves items with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} of d10 (d12 with a raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Character teleports up to Smarts x5 miles distant.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{Time Stop}</td>\n<td>H</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Caster takes an additional turn (of 4 actions with a raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Character can walk on walls at half @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} (full Pace with raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Grant target a Combat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edge}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{Wish}</td>\n<td>L</td>\n<td>20</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Uni}</td>\n<td>Choose one of several reality-altering events.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zombie]{Zombie}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1h</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Nec}</td>\n<td>Raises and controls the undead.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3> </h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsjso9rnq9","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/4.1. Using Magic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"5xI9POfTYFCDhZH0","name":"Encumbrance","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Encumbrance</h2>\n<p>Most of the time you don’t need to worry about how much weight a character is carrying. If it becomes important to track, use the <strong>Encumbrance Levels</strong> table. If a character carries more than the listed weight, he’s Encumbered.</p>\n<p>Encumbered characters subtract 2 from Pace (minimum 1), running rolls, Agility and all linked skills, and Vigor rolls made to resist <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}</strong>.</p>\n<p>At three times the lifted weight or more, he can move at a Pace of 1 for a number of rounds equal to his Vigor. Every round thereafter he must succeed at a Vigor roll or take a level of Fatigue.</p>\n<p>The maximum weight a character can lift or carry is four times the listed weight.</p>\n<p><strong>Bulky Items:</strong> Carrying a bulky, awkward, or unbalanced item, such as a large box, treasure chest, a person, and so on, may make a character Encumbered despite its actual weight (GM’s call).</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"2\">Encumbrance</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Strength</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Can Freely Carry Up To...</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">d4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">d6</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">40 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">d8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">60 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">d10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">80 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">d12</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">100 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Each +1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">+20 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.yZutkhibo6To97ET"}}}
