{"_id":"9DrxYWOt9RhHpgCL","name":"Defend","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Defend</h2>\n<p>A character can choose to focus all her energy and skill into defense against melee attacks with the \n  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Defend]{Defend} maneuver. \n  This increases her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} by +4 and takes her entire turn— \n  she cannot perform @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions}. \n  She may move normally but may not run. The bonus lasts until the beginning of her next turn.</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.zW0vCtrPnvUbt0ns"}}}
{"_id":"9IkIEjNwnbMYYipu","name":"Raises","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Raises</h2>\n  <p>Sometimes it’s important to know just how successful a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait roll} was. \n    Every 4 points over the Target Number is called a “raise.” If your hero needs a 4 to shoot an opponent and rolls an 11, he hits with a raise. \n    Figure raises after adjusting for any modifiers.\n</p>\n<p>A raise always provides an additional effect of some sort, such as bonus damage when attacking or a benefit determined by the GM for other rolls.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.wHFIvFOAbqPZIdOV"}}}
{"_id":"9K5QUOefLRTr7Bsl","name":"Distracted and Vulnerable","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Distracted and Vulnerable</h2>\n  <p>Characters may be Distracted or made Vulnerable by special abilities, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{1 Powers}. \n\t\tThese states last until the end of the character’s next turn unless otherwise noted. \n\t\tIf a hero becomes Distracted or Vulnerable during her current turn, \n\t\tit lasts until the end of her <em>next</em> turn. \n\t\tLike effects don't stack.</p>\n\t\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>Distracted:</strong>  The hero subtracts 2 from all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait rolls} until the end of his next turn.</li>\n\t\t<li><strong>Vulnerable:</strong>  Actions and attacks against the target are made at +2 until the end of his next turn. \n\t\t\tThis doesn’t stack with <strong>The Drop</strong> (see below).</li>\t\n\t</ul>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.DlAApOqk5Qygv0gU"}}}
{"_id":"9NYfv5zozqLArWgu","name":"Withdrawing From Melee","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Withdrawing from Melee</h2>\n  <p>Whenever a character retreats from melee, all adjacent non-@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shaken]{Shaken} \n\t\tand non-@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} opponents get an immediate Free Attack \n\t\t(see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attacks}</strong>).</p>\n\n\t<blockquote>\n\t\t<em><strong>Example:</strong></em> \n\t\tOur druid is surrounded by three bandits. She must get to a wounded sorcerer. She takes the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Defend]{Defend} option \n\t\t(increasing her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} by +4) and backs away from the bandits. \n\t\tAll three of her opponents get a Free Attack, at +2 for Ganging Up. Fortunately, the druid’s Parry bonus fends them off and she makes her way to her injured friend.\n\t</blockquote>\n\t\t\t\n\t<br />\n\t\n\t<div>\n\t\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/gazetteer-cover.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.9o9GaenKCs6W0G6K"}}}
{"_id":"9d8gyBz9ozc3qQ9O","name":"Two Hands","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Two Hands</h2>\n  <p>A two-handed weapon can be used with one hand at a −4 penalty. The hero counts full Strength for damage but loses all other advantages such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonuses.</p>\n\t<p>Two-handed weapons are normally required to make use of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Sweep} Edge.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.9jzEdURG28k9jprF"}}}
{"_id":"9pAAJ5A3Id1qF07Z","name":"Noble","content":"<p>The highest levels of nobility are shared among the nations of Khorvaire, but other nobles exist among families of great import or strong political ties.</p>\n<p>When Galifar was founded, the Five Nations all employed forms of medieval feudalism. Nobles governed lands tended by tenant farmers in exchange for providing taxes and military service to the leader of the nation. In many nations, the nobility was also responsible for the administration of justice. Galifar was built on this framework. It was acknowledged that all power and authority flowed from the sovereign, through the princes and princesses that governed the land, and then down through local nobles and administrators. Throughout Galifar, the nobility remained the foundation of the united kingdom. Nobles were responsible for maintaining their territory, including collecting taxes and raising levies for military and national service. Under the Galifar Code of Justice, the nobles didn’t administer justice, but it was their duty to maintain the system, appointing justices and maintaining the local courts. As the kingdom expanded and as life became increasingly more complicated, this produced a class of dedicated civil servants and landowners—initially ennobled viscounts and crown reeves, but ultimately expanding into gentry and merchant classes. But at the start of the Last War, it remained the case that the majority of property was associated with a noble’s domain, and that it was the local lord who appointed justices, mayors, and other officials. A crown reeve was responsible to the count, the count to their duke, the duke to the prince, the prince to the king.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Common Knowledge, Intimidation, Persuasion, Traditions</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Aristocract, Charismatic, House Scion, Rich, Filthy Rich</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.zds95QdTAYavucmH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ADkqUlindL5Tm2wJ","name":"Limitations","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n    <h2>Limitations</h2>\n    <div>\n        <img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/storm-woman.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/storm-woman.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"424\" />\n      </div>\n      <p>\n        Sometimes a power’s  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping} imposes a limitation on the power. \n        This gives the power focus at the expense of versatility. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation} is permanent and always in effect unless \n        changed with an Advance as noted below.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n        Each limitation placed upon the power reduces its total @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points} cost by\n        one (to a minimum of 1). If this would normally reduce the cost to 0, you\n        gain a +1 bonus (+2 maximum) to the arcane skill total instead.\n      </p>\n      <ul>\n        <li>\n          <strong>Trappings Range:</strong>The power’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} is reduced to Touch\n          (if its usual Range is greater).\n        </li>\n        <li>\n          <strong>Personal:</strong> The power’s Range becomes Self (if its usual\n          Range is Touch or it has the range Limitation, above). This includes an\n          item if the power is normally cast on an object (such as <em>smite</em>).\n        </li>\n        <li>\n          <strong>Aspect:</strong> The character can only access one aspect of a\n          power (that has more than one choice), such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{sloth/speed}</em> or\n          <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower}</em> Trait.\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{See full Powers rules here}</p>\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Powers]{See full Powers list here}</p>\n&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; Updated upstream\n    <p>@Compendium[@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{See full Power Modifiers list here}</p>\n=======\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{See full Power Modifiers list here}</p>\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Stashed changes\n    \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{See full rules here}\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_inkjjer1fuj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/Powers keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.DZoO2axjZPEM04Bq"}}}
{"_id":"AJxOVRr5wa2SWp9o","name":"Ship Repairs","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Ship Repairs</h1>\n<p>Damage suffered in combat may only be repaired at a dry-dock (unless a character on board has the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em> Power).</p>\n<p>There are dry-docks in all of the Great Ports. Repairs there typically take 1d4 days per @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} (and critical hit) to be fixed. The cost is 10 times the ship’s base @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} per wound or critical hit to be repaired.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Boarding]{Boarding}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranks of Archers]{Ranks of Archers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Sinking]{Sinking}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6g48t5q06rw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"AN1DxzZwzW6Os1CY","name":"Parry","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Parry</h2>\n  <p>The weapon adds the bonus to the character’s Parry score. If a character wields a weapon in each hand, penalties to Parry stack but bonuses do not (unless she has the Ambidextrous Edge). This also applies to carrying two shields at once (use the best Parry bonus).</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.H531wJIhziVVScZT"}}}
{"_id":"ASXIR6dwndy2V5TG","name":"7 Trait Summaries","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h1 class=\"wide\">Trait summaries</h1>\n  <table>\n    <colgroup>\n      <col></col>\n    </colgroup>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <th class=\"left sub-heading\">Attributes</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>Agility:</strong> Nimbleness, dexterity, and overall physical\n          coordination of muscles and reflexes.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>Smarts:</strong> Raw intellect, perception, and ability to\n          sort and make use of complex information.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><strong>Spirit:</strong> Inner strength and willpower.</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><strong>Strength:</strong> Raw muscle power.</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><strong>Vigor:</strong> Endurance, health, and constitution.</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <th class=\"left sub-heading\">Skills</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Academics]{Academics} (Smarts):</strong> Knowledge or ability to research\n          written or recorded information.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <span class=\"star-icon red\"><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Agility):</strong></span>\n          Overall athletic coordination and ability. Climbing, jumping,\n          balancing, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} (Smarts):</strong> Strategy, tactics, and understanding\n          military operations. A key skill in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} (Agility):</strong> Ability to sail or pilot a boat,\n          ship, or other watercraft.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n            <span class=\"star-icon red\"><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} (Smarts):</strong></span> General knowledge of a character’s world.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Driving]{Driving} (Agility):</strong> The ability to control, steer, and\n          operate ground vehicles.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n            <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Faith]{Faith} (Spirit):</strong> The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{Arcane Background (Miracles)}.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} (Agility):</strong> Skill and utter ferocity in armed\n          and unarmed combat.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling} (Smarts):</strong> Skill and familiarity with games\n          of chance.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} (Smarts):</strong> The ability to treat and heal\n          Wounds and diseases, and decipher forensic evidence.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (Spirit):</strong> A character’s ability to\n          threaten others into doing what she wants.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <span class=\"star-icon red\"><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (Smarts):</strong></span> General awareness and perception.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} (Smarts):</strong> Knowledge of supernatural events,\n          creatures, history, items, and ways.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} (Spirit):</strong> Singing, dancing, acting, or\n          other forms of public expression.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <span class=\"star-icon red\"><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} (Spirit):</strong></span> The ability to convince others to do what you want.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} (Agility):</strong> Skill with maneuvering vehicles\n          that operate in three dimensions, such as airships.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} (Smarts):</strong> The ability to fix mechanical and\n          electrical gadgets.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} (Agility):</strong> A character’s skill in mounting,\n          controlling, and riding a tamed beast.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science} (Smarts):</strong> Knowledge of scientific fields such\n          as biology, chemistry, geology, engineering, etc.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} (Agility):</strong> Precision with any type of ranged\n          weapon.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} (Smarts):</strong> \n          The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)}.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <span class=\"star-icon red\"><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} (Agility):</strong></span> The ability to sneak and hide.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} (Smarts):</strong> How to find food, water, or\n          shelter, and tracking.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} (Smarts):</strong> Insulting or belittling another.\n          Almost always done as a <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}</strong>.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} (Agility):</strong> Sleight of hand, pickpocketing,\n          lockpicking, and other typically shady feats.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.MSp9w8wqDXKj0mTc"}}}
{"_id":"AWkCLhQQu3yfAeqx","name":"Changeling","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Changeling</h1>\n<p>Changelings can shift their forms with a thought. Many changelings use this gift as a form of artistic and emotional expression. It's also an invaluable tool for grifters, spies, and others who wish to deceive. This leads many people to treat changelings with suspicion.</p>\n<h3>A Hidden People</h3>\n<p>Wherever humans live, changelings reside also; the question is whether their presence is known.</p>\n<p>Changelings are born to one of three paths. A few are raised in stable communities where changelings are true to their nature and deal openly with the people around them. Some are orphans, raised by other races, who find their way in the world without ever knowing another like themselves. Others are part of nomadic changeling clans spread across the Five Nations, families who keep their true nature hidden from the single-skins. Some clans maintain safe havens in major cities and communities, but most prefer to wander the unpredictable path of the god known as the Traveler.</p>\n<p>In creating a changeling adventurer, consider the character's relationships with people around them. Does the character conceal their true changeling nature? Do they embrace it? Do they have connections to other changelings or are they alone and in search of companions?</p>\n<h3>Masks and Personas</h3>\n<p>In their true form, changelings are pale, with colorless eyes and silver-white hair. It is rare to see a changeling in that form, for a typical changeling changes their shape the way others might change clothes. A casual shapeone created on the spur of the moment, with no depth or history-is called a mask. A mask can be used to express a mood or to serve a specific purpose and then might never be used again. However, many changelings develop identities that have more depth. They build an identity over time, crafting a persona with a history and beliefs. This focused identity helps a changeling pinpoint a particular skill or emotion. A changeling adventurer might have personas for many situations, including negotiation, investigation, and combat.</p>\n<p>Personas can be shared by multiple changelings; there might be three healers in a community, but whoever is on dutywill adopt the persona of Tek, the kindly old medic. Personas can even be passed down through a family, allowing a younger changeling to take advantage of contacts established by the persona's previous users.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Change Appearance]{Change Appearance}:</strong> Changelings can alter physical appearance at will as per the <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em> power except it cannot affect clothing or gear. The power has no limit on duration. When they die they return to their natural form.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Changeling Instinct]{Changeling Instinct}:</strong> Changelings are socially and psychologically intuitive due to their adoption and understanding of different personas. They add 1 to rolls made with two of the following skills: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, </em><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}<em>, </em><span style=\"font-style:normal\">or</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}</em><em>.</em></li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Outsider (Changeling)]{Outsider (Minor)}:</strong> If identified as a changeling, they have −2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} as other races tend to distrust them.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/changeling.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/changeling.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L4NqGfd9AVja33DY"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"AgFq2DOZhgC7MV9Y","name":"Heat","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Underlined Header</h2>\n  <p>Heat over 90° Fahrenheit can cause heat exhaustion and heatstroke.</p>\n  <p>\n    A character must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Trait Summaries]{Vigor} roll every four hours spent in weather above\n    90° F; at −2 if the temperature is above 110° F. Failure means the hero\n    incurs a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} level.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Roll only once per day if a character has plenty of water, or once every\n    five days if well-provisioned with shelter, food, and other resources.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Heatstroke:</strong> A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} when resisting heat\n    indicates heatstroke! The hero must make a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Trait Summaries]{Vigor} roll or perish.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Recovery:</strong> A victim must cool down somehow to recover\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}. This usually means water, shade, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rest]{rest}.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4txb7iklyvb","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.QPzMmopakLUDPFjK"}}}
{"_id":"Au6zFp6gJuzvxRUD","name":"Hard Choices","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Hard Choices</h2>\n<p>Use this rule for more dramatic and gritty games. The GM and her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} characters don’t start with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies}, but every time the players spend one it goes into her pool where it can be used for any of her characters. If this rule is in play, Jokers no longer grant Bennies to either side.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rv4q29jrhjs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.nF3w2ly84awwGf3z"}}}
