{"_id":"BTYbwZzSBg6HIcpQ","name":"Shaken","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Shaken</h2>\n  <p>Shaken characters are nicked, bruised, or otherwise rattled. They may only take @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Actions]{free actions}, such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{moving} (including running). At the start of their turn, Shaken characters must attempt to recover from being Shaken by making a Spirit roll. This is a free action.</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><span class=\"list-heading\">Failure:</span> The character remains Shaken. She can only perform free actions.</li>\n    <li><span class=\"list-heading\">Success:</span> The character is no longer Shaken and may act normally.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies}:</strong> A player may spend a Benny at any time to remove her Shaken status (even when it’s not her turn).</p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Combat]{See full rules here.}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aeejh0xnzv6","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Combat keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.zzh3mj1QDalp0RYf"}}}
{"_id":"BX6BfcMRdtSojlai","name":"Wounds","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Wounds</h2>\n  <p>\n    Every raise on the damage roll inflicts a Wound. Extras are @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} if\n    they take a single Wound (and aren’t <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Special Abilities]{Resilient}</strong>). They’re\n    dead, injured, or otherwise out of the fight.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} can take three Wounds and still function \n    (more with certain @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Edges]{Edges} or abilities). Further damage doesn’t cause additional Wounds but Incapacitates them instead.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Wound Penalties:</strong> Each Wound a character suffers causes a −1\n    cumulative penalty to his Pace (minimum of 1″) and all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait rolls}--up to a\n    maximum penalty of −3.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Timing:</strong> Characters sometimes take multi­ple hits on the same @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card}. \n    Resolve each damage roll separately before moving on to the next (including any Soak rolls).\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Combat]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aeejh0xnzv6","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Combat keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.cLOTyCTOQsITJx9X"}}}
{"_id":"Bh5CpFZQUCJFbTUy","name":"Life Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Life Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Healing, life, love, mercy, peace</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> The Sovereign Host, Arawai, Boldrei, Olladra, The Silver Flame, The Blood of Vol, The Undying Court</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Champion of Faith]{Champion of Faith}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Consecrate/Desecrate Ground]{Consecrate Ground}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-