{"_id":"EfICZmrNYqv8zhkI","name":"Called Shots","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Called Shots</h2>\n\n\t<p>Targeting a particular part of the body is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shot}. \n\t\tThe modifier to the attack roll depends on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size %26 Scale]{Scale} of the target itself \n\t\t(not the creature it’s part of). Use the <strong>Scale Modifiers</strong> table in the Size and Scale section further down to determine any bonus or penalty \n\t\tfor the target’s Scale. These modifiers are already listed in parentheses for Normal scale creatures, along with any specific game effects:</p>\n\t\t\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>Hand (-4)</strong>: Target may be <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disarm]{Disarmed}</strong>.</li>\n\t\t<li> <strong>Head or Vitals (-4)</strong>: Hitting the head or vital organs of living creatures adds +4 damage to the attacker’s total. \n\t\t\tThe penalty is −5 if attempting to target the face of someone wearing an open-faced helmet (thus bypassing the helmet’s Armor).</li>\n\t\t<li><strong>Item</strong>(?) : Use the dimensions on the Scale table for items. Targeting something the size of a dagger, for example, is −4.</li>\n\t\t<li><strong>Limbs</strong>(-2) Unless attempting to Disarm (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disarm]{here}), \n\t\t\thitting a limb has no additional special effect since it’s already accounted for by Wound and Pace penalties \n\t\t\t(see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wounds]{here}</strong>).</li>\n\t\t<li><strong>Unarmored Area</strong> (?) : The attack targets the unprotected area of a target otherwise covered in Armor. \n\t\t\tThe penalty depends on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size %26 Scale]{Scale} of the area. \n\t\t\tThe eye slit of a helmet is Tiny (−6), for example, while the flesh beneath the missing scale of a Huge dragon might be Very Small (−4).</li>\n\t</ul>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.wRiMH2UnqU3C3w9i"}}}
{"_id":"F8WWzQRhZzNlNBjM","name":"Center","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Center</h1>\n<p>The hero focuses on whatever brings her happiness. That might include quality time with friends, a solitary hunt through a secluded forest, riding a favorite horse, painting, reading, writing, performing, dancing, or courting a romantic interest.</p>\n<p>Whatever the activity, the goal is inner peace and happiness. Taking a week to enjoy the fruits of one’s labors grants the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Conviction]{Conviction}.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Downtime Activities</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Carouse]{Carouse}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Center]{Center}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Earn]{Earn}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Enchant]{Enchant}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Train]{Train}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Research]{Research}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rest]{Rest}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_lrlfbg8dda","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Downtime keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
