\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSarenrae\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tGood\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tHealing, honesty, redemption, sun\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tFire, Glory, Good, Healing, Sun\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tShelyn\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tGood\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tArt, beauty, love, music\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAir, Good, Luck, Protection\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tTorag\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tGood\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tThe forge, protection, strategy\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tEarth, Good, Protection\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tUrgathoa\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tEvil\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDisease, gluttony, undeath\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDeath, Evil, Magic, Strength, War\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tZon-Kuthon\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tEvil\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDarkness, envy, loss, pain\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDeath, Destruction, Evil\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t</table>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\">Druid</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Druid</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>In the purity and beauty of nature lingers a power beyond the marvels of civilization. These primal magics are guarded by servants of balance known as druids. Allies to beasts and manipulators of nature, these protectors shield their lands from all who threaten them. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Rewarded for their devotion with incredible powers, druids gain unparalleled shape-shifting abilities, the companionship of mighty beasts, and the power to call upon nature’s wrath. The mightiest temper powers akin to storms, earthquakes, and volcanoes with wisdom long forgotten by civilization.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Arcane Background</span> <strong>(Druid):</strong> Druids use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Faith]{Faith} as their arcane skill. On taking this Edge, the hero gains 3 starting powers and 10 Power Points.<br /><strong>Available Powers:</strong> Druids choose spells from the cleric's available powers and under the Nature Domain. </li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armor Interference</span> <strong>(Light):</strong> Bulky armor interferes with a druid’s ability to sense and commune with nature. They subtract 4 from their Faith rolls and from their Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using medium or heavy armor or shields. Druids cannot use metal armor at all.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Nature Bond:</span> A druid may attune herself to nature or a special animal companion. See <strong>Nature Bond,</strong> below.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Nature Sense:</span> Druids commune with nature and its spirits. Survival is linked to Spirit rather than Smarts. </li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Secret Language:</span> All druids know the secret language known as druidic.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Vow</span> <strong>(Major):</strong> Druids have a major vow to protect nature. Those drawing energy from divine sources must uphold the principles of the Nature Domain. <br />If the druid violates her deity's trust  (GM's call) the druid subtracts 2 from Faith rolls for a week. Truly sacrilegious acts might rob her of her powers entirely until she atones in some way.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Wilderness Stride:</span> Druids pass through terrain such as dense forest, rocky hills, or desert sands with ease. They ignore penalties for Difficult Ground (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Movement}).</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Nature Bond</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>The bonds druids form with nature are deep and powerful. Choose one of these abilities:</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Attuned:</strong> The druid gets one free reroll anytime she fails a Faith roll to activate a spell.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Beast Master:</strong>  The druid gains the Beast Master Edge, gaining an animal companion. This companion is a Wild Card.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Wild Shape</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wild Shape]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Druid</p>\n<p>The druid gains the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</em> spell, if she doesn’t already have it. The Duration is one hour for her, and she casts as if she were one Rank higher than her actual Rank on the <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</strong> table.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Favored powers (druid)</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Druid)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Druid</p>\n<p>The druid has great familiarity with some of her core powers and can cast them quickly and easily.  As a limited free action, she may ignore up to two points of <em>any</em> penalties (Multi-Action, Wounds, Fatigue, etc.) when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}.</em></p>\n<p>This Edge doesn’t give her those powers— they must be taken separately.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Divine Mastery</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Divine Mastery]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Druid</p>\n<p>Nature rewards its defenders with additional power and energy. A druid who takes this Edge gains access to all her powers’ @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Epic Power Modifiers}.</p>\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Lini <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Druid)</span></h2>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Lini]{Lini} has a way with wild creatures, especially big cats. The gnome prefers the company of her snow leopard, Droogami, to other humanoids, although she gets along well enough with people she trusts. Curious and quirky, she collects sticks from every forest she visits.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Gnome]{Gnome} (Gnome Magic, Keen Senses, Low Light Vision, Obsessive, Reduced Pace, Tough, Size −1)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d6</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 5</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 6 (2)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 5 (d4)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 3</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> All Thumbs, Curious, Quirk (Collects sticks), Vow (Major—protect nature)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Druid, Beast Master (Droogami the Snow Leopard, see @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Cat, Large]{Cat, Large}), New Powers</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Common, Druidic, Elven, Gnome, Sylvan</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Faith]{Faith} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d8</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Powers:</span> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{environmental protection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}.</em></p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Sickle (Str+d4), sling (Range 4/8/16, Damage Str+d4, uses Athletics), soft leather tunic and pants (+2), traveler’s outfit, 20 stones, adventurer’s kit, spell component pouch, thunderstone, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Potion of Minor Healing]{potion of minor healing}, 5x smoke sticks, 39 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n\t<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> Woodsman\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> Smarts d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Wild Shape (Grants <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</em> power)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 </strong><strong>–</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower trait}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Power Points (15 Total)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Favored Powers (Druid)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> Spirit d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Faith]{Faith} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d6\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Beast Master (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting})\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Divine Mastery\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> Beast Master (Strength)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> Power Points (20 total)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Faith d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{resurrection}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Beast Master (Vigor)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Giant Killer\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Professional (Faith d12 + 1)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t\t\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/p53_Pathfinder_Druid.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Fighter</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Fighter</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fighter]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Strength d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Some take up arms for glory, wealth, or revenge. Others do battle to prove themselves, to protect others, or because they know nothing else. Still others learn the ways of weaponcraft to hone their bodies in battle and prove their mettle in the forge of war. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Lords of the battlefield, fighters are a disparate lot. Some train with many weapons; some prefer just one. Whatever their tactics, fighters excel at combat. They protect their own and defeat their enemies, rarely shying away from battle. They often lead the charge, a role they relish even if they don’t insist on it.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>These skilled warriors turn hunks of metal into arms capable of taming kingdoms, slaughtering monsters, and rousing the hearts of armies. Woe to those who dare stand against them.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Martial Flexibility:</span> Once per encounter, as a limited free action, a fighter can choose to gain the benefits of a single Combat Edge. He must meet all of the Edge’s Requirements, and the benefits of the chosen Edge end after five rounds.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Deadly Blow</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Deadly Blow]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Fighter</p>\n<p>The fighter adds +1 to the damage of all successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Martial Flexibility (Improved)</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility (Improved)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Fighter</p>\n<p>The fighter gains the benefits of two Combat Edges (subject to the usual restrictions of Martial Flexibility). He may choose both Combat Edges at the same time, or choose the second Edge as a separate limited free action in a subsequent turn.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Martial Prowess</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Prowess]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Fighter</p>\n<p>The fighter gets a free reroll on any failed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll.</p>\n    <img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/6-opener.webp\" />\n\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Valeros <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Fighter)</span></h2>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Valeros]{Valeros} takes an easy-come, easy-go approach to life, wealth, and relationships. Nevertheless, he remains fiercely loyal to his adventuring companions, even if he acts on impulse in battle. The burly warrior prefers to fight with a sword in each hand, although his proficiency with a bow proves a boon when hunting and engaging in ranged combat.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Human]{Human} (Adaptable)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d6</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 9 (3)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 3</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Impulsive, Loyal, Vengeful (Minor)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Ambidextrous, Brawny, Fighter</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Common, Dwarven, Elven, Sylvan</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d4</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Longsword (Str+d8), short sword (Str+d6), long bow (Range 15/30/60, Damage 2d6), 20 arrows, scale mail shirt (+3), leather leggings (+2), adventurer’s kit, 29 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> Vigor d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> Nerves of Steel\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> Two-Weapon @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Deadly Blow\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> Agility d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d6\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Fighting d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Martial Flexibility (Imp)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> Strength d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> Combat Reflexes\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Block\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Martial Prowess\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> Fighting d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> Vigor d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d8, Riding d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Vigor d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> Tough as Nails\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Weapon Master\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Master of Arms\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Tougher than Nails\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/fighter.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Monk</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Monk</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monk]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d6+, Spirit d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>For the truly exemplary, martial prowess transcends the battlefield— it is a lifestyle, a doctrine, a state of mind. Such warrior-artists search out methods of battle beyond swords and shields, finding weapons within themselves as lethal as any blade. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>These monks adhere to ancient philosophies and strict martial disciplines. They elevate their bodies to become weapons of war. Monks tread a path of discipline and balance— in mind, breath, and body. </p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armor Restriction</span> <strong>(Any):</strong> Monks must be completely unhindered to perform their complex maneuvers. They subtract 4 from Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using  light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Martial Discipline:</span> Monks hone their bodies to perfection, gaining an additional +1 Toughness if wearing no armor.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mobility:</span> Quick and nimble, monks increase their running die by one die type.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">STUNNING FIST:</span> When a monk hits a target with an Unarmed Strike and scores a raise, he may make the foe Distracted or  Vulnerable. This occurs even if the victim takes no damage or Soaks it (the states are applied after the victim attempts to Soak). </li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Unarmed Strike:</span> Monks gain +1 to Fighting attacks when attacking unarmed and AP +2. They cause Str+d4 damage with their hands, feet, or other <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</strong> (if they have such appendages). <br />If the monk already has a Strength damage die from Claws (available to some ancestries), or the Brawler Edge, increase the damage a die type for each.<br />Monks can apply the Trademark Weapon Edge to their unarmed attacks. <br />Monks always count as armed. Some use regular weapons in their off-hand, but abilities that refer to their Unarmed Strike apply only to unarmed attacks as defined above.<br />On a raise the monk rolls a d10 for his bonus damage.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Mystic Powers (monk)</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Monk)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Monk</p>\n<p>As a limited free action, the monk can invoke one of the following \"ki\" powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait} </em>(Agility, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, Fighting, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite},</em> and <em>speed.</em> All are self only, but the monk gains no benefit from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The monk has 10 dedicated Power Points that @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Recharging]{recharge} normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} for more information on specific spells.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn’t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background. If the monk also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Great Ki</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Ki]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Monk, Mystic Powers (Monk)</p>\n<p>The monk further nurtures and refines his ki. He adds the following spells to his Mystic Powers Edge: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait} (Strength), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{wall walker}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Wholeness of Body</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wholeness of Body]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Monk, Mystic Powers (Monk)</p>\n<p>The monk may spend 2 Power Points to make a Soak roll. This does not count as spending a Benny.</p>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Sajan <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Monk)</span></h2>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Sajan]{Sajan}’s vow to find his twin sister, Sajini, drives his will to survive. He remains patient and loyal in his quest, searching for clues to her whereabouts with each passing day. Sajan exhibits discipline and perseverance in all things, but especially in the rigors of his martial training. The monk always helps those in need, even if it puts him in harm’s way.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Human]{Human} (Adaptable)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d8</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 7</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 7</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 8 (d10)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 3</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Heroic, Loyal, Vow (Minor)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Fleet-Footed, Monk, Trademark Weapon (unarmed strike)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Common, Elven, Giant, Goblin</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d8</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Temple sword (treat as short sword, Str+d6), 6x shurikens (Range 3/6/12, Damage Str+d4), caltrops, adventurer’s kit, 3x @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Alchemists Fire]{alchemist's fire}, sunrod, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Potion of Minor Healing]{potion of minor healing}, 21 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\t\t\n\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n\t<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> Strength d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> Brawler\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> First Strike\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong>  Mystic Powers (Monk)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> Agility d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> Frenzy\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Block\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Great Ki\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> Trademark Weapon (Imp)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> Spirit d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Wholeness of Body\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> Nerves of Steel\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> Common Bond\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> Combat Reflexes\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Fighting d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> Counterattack\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Improved Block\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Vigor d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Tough as Nails\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t\t\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/monk.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Paladin</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Paladin</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Paladin]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Strength d6+, Spirit d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Vow]{Vow} (Minor or Major—serve their deity or order)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Through a worthy few shines the power of the divine. Called paladins, these noble souls dedicate their swords and lives to the battle against evil. Knights, crusaders, and lawbringers, paladins seek not just to spread righteous justice but to embody the teachings of the virtuous deities they serve. In pursuit of their lofty goals, they adhere to ironclad laws of morality and discipline. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>As a reward for their service, these holy champions are blessed with boons to aid them in their quests. They gain abilities to battle evil opponents, heal allies, and inspire the faithful. Their conviction leads them into conflict with the very souls they would save. Paladins weather endless challenges of faith and temptation. They risk their lives to do right and ensure justice.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Aura of Courage:</span> As long as the paladin is conscious, all allies within 10” (20 yards) add +1 to their Fear checks.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Code of Honor:</span> All good paladins have the Code of Honor Hindrance. They strive to keep their word, won’t kill or abuse prisoners, and generally uphold the highest standards of etiquette and manners. This is in addition to their other Hindrances.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Detect Evil:</span> As an action, the Paladin can concentrate on any one object or individual within Smarts range to determine whether it’s Evil in nature. See the Cleric section for deities and their alignments.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Smite Evil:</span> As a free action, a paladin can choose an enemy. If that enemy is evil, she gets a free reroll on any failed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls against that target for the remainder of the encounter. She may use this ability once per Rank per encounter.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Mystic Powers (Paladin)</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Paladin)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Paladin</p>\n<p>As a limited free action the paladin can invoke one of the following miracles: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em>(@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, Strength, and Vigor only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}, </em>and<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}.</em> <em>Boost trait </em>and <em>smite}</em> are self only, but the paladin gains no benefit from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}).</p>\n<p>The paladin has 10 dedicated Power Points that @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Recharging]{recharge} normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} for more information on specific spells.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn’t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background. If the paladin also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Mercy</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mercy]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Paladin</p>\n<p>As an action, a paladin can grant “Mercy” to any character within a Range equal to her Spirit. Mercy removes one of the following: Distracted, Vulnerable, or Shaken.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Mount</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mount]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Paladin</p>\n<p>The paladin forms a divine bond with a mount she currently owns. This is usually a horse or pony, but may be any mount approved by the GM of Size 3 or less. On forming the bond, the mount gains two advances (Traits or appropriate Edges, GM's call), and is Resilient. It may be summoned as a limited action, arriving at the start of the next round and acting on the paladin's Action Card if in combat.</p>\n<p>If the mount perishes, the paladin may acquire and bond with another, but may only ever have one bonded mount at a time.</p>\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Seelah <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Paladin)</span></h2>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>A faithful follower of Iomedae the Inheritor, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Seelah]{Seelah} honors her goddess every day. Sworn to a strict code, she strives to act with honor and ensure justice at all times. Seelah practices personal cleanliness and dedicates herself to rooting out evil on Eberron. Her vow to bring evildoers and scofflaws to justice guides her decision-making. </p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Human]{Human} (Adaptable)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d8</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 8 (2)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 9 (3)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 3</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Code of Honor, Loyal, Thin Skinned (Minor), Vow (Major—Serve Iomedae)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Paladin, Champion</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Celestial, Common, Dwarven, Elven</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d4</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Longsword (Str+d8), long bow (Range 15/30/60, Damage 2d6), 20 arrows, explorer’s outfit, chain mail shirt (+3), leather leggings (+2), medium shield (+2 Parry, −2 Cover), adventurer’s kit, holy symbol, holy water, 15 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d4\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} d4, Occult d6\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> Command\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Mystic Powers (Paladin)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> Vigor d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> Natural Leader\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Common Bond\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Mercy\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> Fervor\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> Counterattack\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Strength d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Mount\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> Vigor d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> Beast Bond\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Fighting d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> Tough as Nails\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Tougher Than Nails\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Weapon Master\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Followers\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/paladin.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Ranger</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Ranger</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ranger]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>For those who relish the thrill of the hunt, there are only predators and prey. From scouts, to trackers, or bounty hunters, all rangers share the predator’s perspective. They value skill with weapons. They excel at stalking even the most elusive game. They train relentlessly to defeat a wide range of quarries. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Knowledgeable, patient, and skilled hunters, rangers pursue man, beast, and monster alike. While some track dangerous creatures to protect the frontier, others pursue more cunning game— even fugitives— into and through the dangerous wilds. </p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armor Restriction</span> <strong>(Medium):</strong> Rangers are agile and mobile fighters and scouts. They subtract 4 from Agility and Agility-based skill rolls when wearing heavy armor or using a heavy shield.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Favored Enemy:</span> Rangers study their foes, learning their ways, how to find them, and how to defeat them. Choose a type of enemy from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Bestiary]{Bestiary}. The ranger gets one free reroll when failing to track (Survival) or attack (Athletics (throwing), Fighting, Shooting) that type of being.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Favored terrain:</span> Choose a terrain type (Arctic, Desert, Forest, Jungle, Plains, Hills/Mountains, Rivers/Seas, Swamp, Urban, or Underground). The ranger draws an additional Action Card for initiative when in his Favored Terrain. (This has no effect on the number of cards a Ranger can use, so a Level Headed character can still choose which card to use, while a Hesitant character must still take the worst card.)  </li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Wilderness Stride:</span> Rangers pass through rough terrain such as dense forest, rocky hills, or desert sands with ease. They ignore movement penalties for <strong>Difficult Ground</strong> (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Movement}).</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Quarry</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Quarry]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Ranger</p>\n<p>The ranger's expertise expands to include additional enemies and terrain. Choose an additional enemy and terrain type for your Favored Enemy and Favored Terrain abilities.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken once per Rank.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Mystic Powers (Ranger)</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Ranger)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Ranger</p>\n<p>As a limited free action the ranger can cast one of the following spells: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend},</em> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait} </em>(@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle},</em> and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}.</em> <em>Boost Trait </em>and <em>warrior’s gift</em> are self only, but the ranger gains no benefit from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The woodsman has 10 dedicated Power Points that @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Recharging]{recharge} normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} for more information on specific spells.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn’t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the ranger also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges and abilities can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Master Hunter</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Hunter]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Ranger</p>\n<p>Rangers have now become deadly enemies of their chosen prey. They add an additional d6 damage when making a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack against their Favored Enemy.</p>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Harsk <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Ranger)</span></h2>\n\t\t\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>An uncommon dwarf, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Harsk]{Harsk} enjoys the open plains and verdant forests more than claustrophobic tunnels. He prefers the taste of tea to ale. Few things make him happier than crouching in a tree stand with his crossbow. Harsk carries his brother’s axe, a reminder of his vow to protect the wilds from the likes of the giants who killed Sigur 20 years ago.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Dwarf]{Dwarf} (Darkvision, Iron Constitution, Reduced Pace, Stonecunning, Tough)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d8</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 5</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 8 (2)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 5 (d4)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 3</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Habit (Minor—Tea), Suspicious (Minor), Thin Skinned (Minor), Vow (Minor)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Ranger (Favored Enemy—Humanoid, Favored Terrain—Forests), Woodsman</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Common, Dwarven, Goblin, Sylvan</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d8</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Sigur’s battleaxe (Str+d6), heavy crossbow (Range 15/30/60, Damage 2d8, AP 2, Reload 2), 20 bolts, handaxe (Str+d6), studded leather tunic and leggings (+2), adventurer’s kit, climbers kit, tanglefoot bag, 34gp.</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> Strength d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> Rapid Reload\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> Trademark Weapon (Heavy Crossbow)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Quarry (Animals, Mountains)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> Marksman\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Agility d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Mystic Powers (Ranger)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> Giant Killer\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Extraction\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Master Hunter\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> Dodge\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> Trademark Weapon (Imp)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> Nerves of Steel\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Agility d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> Shooting d12, Intimidation d6\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Professional (Shooting d12+1)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Expert (Shooting d12+2)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Master (Shooting)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/p61_Pathfinder_Ranger.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Rogue</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Rogue</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armor Restriction</span> <strong>(Light):</strong> Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from Agility and Agility-based skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Sneak Attack:</span> Rogues add an additional d6 to their damage when they have the Drop on their victim, or the victim is Vulnerable. This applies to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\" style=\"clear:both\">Trap Sense</h3>\n\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-left\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/thieves-tools.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/thieves-tools.webp\" />\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Rogue</p>\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5” (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can’t be Shaken or Stunned. This works generally like Danger Sense but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>Traps are fully described @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{here}.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be Evaded, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of Evasion penalties to do so. If the trap can’t normally be Evaded, anyone warned may Evade at the usual −2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps: </strong>Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Uncanny Reflexes</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Uncanny Reflexes]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Rogue</p>\n<p>The rogue has an uncanny ability to avoid area attacks and effects. She ignores the usual −2 Agility penalty when making <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion}</strong> attempts. She also gets a regular Evasion attempt against area effect attacks or effects that don’t usually allow it (at the usual −2 penalty) such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst} </em>or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}, </em>or even<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion} </em>or similar spells cast with the Area Effect modifier. </p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Opportunist</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Opportunist]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Rogue</p>\n<p>When a target <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdraws From Melee}</strong> with the rogue, she gets a free attack even if the foe has Extraction or Improved Extraction. If the foe doesn’t have either of those Edges, he counts as Vulnerable to her for the free attack.</p>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Merisiel <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Rogue)</span></h2>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>The elves have a name for orphans raised by humans— the Forlorn. Although @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Merisiel]{Merisiel} never learned the entire truth about her parents, she knows enough to bear the shame of her circumstances. Life lessons learned, including prison time in more than one city, Merisiel now lives every moment to the fullest.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Elf]{Elf} (Agile, Elven Magic, Intelligence, Keen Senses, Low Light Vision, Slender)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d6 (-1)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 6 (7 Rapier)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 6 (2)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 2</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Bad Luck, Enemy (Minor), Shamed (Minor)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Acrobat, Rogue, Thief</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Common, Elven, Giant, Goblin, Sylvan</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} d6</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Rapier (Str+d4, Parry +1), 6× throwing knives (Range 3/6/12, Damage Str+d4), 2× daggers (Str+d4), soft leather jacket and leggings (+2), thieves’ tools, tanglefoot bag, adventurer's kit, climbers kit, 35 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> Quick\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> Agility d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Trap Sense\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> Extraction\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d6\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Feint\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Uncanny Reflexes\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d10, Thievery d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> Combat Acrobat\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Counterattack\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Opportunist\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> Agility d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> Humiliate\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> Athletics d12, Fighting d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Weapon Master\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> Master of Arms\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Professional (Athletics d12+1)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Expert (Athletics d12+2)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Master (Athletics)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/p63_Pathfinder_Rogue.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Sorcerer</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Sorcerer</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Scions of magical bloodlines, pawns of fate and destiny, or simply flukes of fickle magic, sorcerers look within themselves for arcane prowess. As they tap into powers few mortals can imagine, these magic-touched souls must learn to harness the power of their birthright.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>While some seek to control their abilities, others give in to their magic, letting it rule their lives. Sorcerers live and breathe that which other spellcasters devote their lives to mastering. For them magic is more than a useful tool or a field of study; it is life itself.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Arcane Background</span> <strong>(Sorcerer):</strong> Sorcerers use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} as their arcane skill, but it is linked to Spirit instead of Smarts (if multiclassing as a Smarts-based spellcaster, use the better of the two Attributes). On taking this Edge, the hero gains 15 Power Points and two starting powers from the list below. <br /><strong>Available Powers:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Baleful Polymorph]{baleful polymorph}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{banish}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{blind}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower trait}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]{burrow}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]{curse}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{damage field}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{darksight}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispel}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{divination}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{drain power points}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{environmental protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{fear}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{growth/shrink}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light / Darkness]{light/darkness}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{mind link}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{mind reading}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Wipe]{Mind Wipe}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{object reading}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Binding]{planar binding}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{plane shift}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{puppet}</em>,<em>  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{sloth/speed}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{slumber}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{sound/silence}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{stun}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{summon ally}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{time stop}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{wall walker}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{wish}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zombie]{zombie}</em>.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armor Interference</span> <strong>(Any):</strong> Sorcery requires rapid, intricate, and unhindered somatic movements. Sorcerers subtract 4 from their Spellcasting rolls and from their Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Bloodline:</span> The sorcerer must choose a bloodline. Beneath each Bloodline description is also the additional special ability one gains when taking the Advanced Bloodline Edge.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\" style=\"clear:both\">Favored powers (Sorcerer)</h3>\n<img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/whatsinthebox.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/whatsinthebox.webp\" />\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Sorcerer)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Sorcerer</p>\n<p>The sorcerer has great familiarity with certain powers and can cast them quickly and easily.  As a limited free action she may ignore up to two points of <em>any</em> penalties (Multi-Action, Wounds, Fatigue, etc.) when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em>, or<em> p</em><em>rotection</em>.</p>\n<p>This Edge doesn’t give her those powers— they must be taken separately.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Arcane Mastery</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Mastery]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Sorcerer</p>\n<p>True understanding of magical energy comes with practice and experience. Those who take this Edge gain access to all their powers’ Epic Power Modifiers (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers}).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Advanced Bloodline</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Advanced Bloodline]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Sorcerer</p>\n<p>You gain the additional ability listed for your Bloodline.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    \n\t\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Seoni <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Sorcerer)</span></h2>\t\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>Born into a nomadic tribe known as the Varisians, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Seoni]{Seoni} manifests the natural magic of her bloodline. Driven by dreams to learn more about her magical heritage, she travels Eberron seeking arcane knowledge and power. Seoni has an Arcane Bloodline, and chose a familiar for her Arcane Bond ability. Her pet is a small, blue-tailed skink called Dragon.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Human]{Human} (Adaptable)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d4</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d6</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 4 (5 Staff)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 5</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 6</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 4</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Curious, Hesitant, Loyal</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Calculating, Luck, New Powers, Sorcerer (Arcane Bloodline, Familiar—lizard)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Common, Draconic, Elven, Goblin, Sylvan</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} d6</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">POWERS:</span> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispel}</em></p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Staff (Str+d4, Parry +1, Reach 1, two hands), dagger (Str+d4), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Alchemists Fire]{alchemist's fire}, antitoxin, adventurer's kit, scroll of <em>bolt</em>, scroll of <em>lower trait</em> (Vigor), 28 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> Power Points (20 total)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Favored Powers (Sorcerer)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> Spirit d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} d10\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{sloth/speed}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Arcane Mastery\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> Great Luck\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</em><em>, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Agility d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Advanced Bloodline\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> Spellcasting d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{mind reading}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> Dodge\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Professional (Spellcasting d12 + 1)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> Expert (Spellcasting d12 + 2)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{time stop}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{wish}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Power Surge\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Master (Spellcasting)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t\t\t\t<img style=\"-webkit-transform:scaleX(-1);transform:scaleX(-1)\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/sorceress.webp\" />\n\t</div>\n</article>\n\n<div>\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Bloodlines</h1>\n\t\t\t<p>Below are the bloodlines available to sorcerers. Many grant various forms of environmental resistance— you'll find those rules @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Elemental Resistance]{here}.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Aberrant</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Aberrant (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A bizarre and alien legacy taints the sorcerer’s blood. Her strange form increases her Toughness by +1. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}, </em>and<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> spells must be cast with the Lingering Damage @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifier}, but cost the sorcerer only 1 additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Point} instead of 2.</p>\n<p>Finally, her long limbs give her Reach +1. In addition to allowing the sorcerer to attack at a distance, this can be used for determining a spell’s Range or origin.</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The character is never @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Surprise]{Surprised} and is immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} unless @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound}. Her alien form grants her another point of Toughness.</li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Abyssal</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Abyssal (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Generations ago, a demon corrupted the hero’s heritage. She has environmental resistance to electricity, +1 Toughness, and sharp claws that cause Str+d4 damage.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The abyssal can conjure demons to aid her. The cost for <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{summon ally}</em> is reduced by 2 (to a minimum of 1), and the entities summoned cause Fear. She also gains environmental resistance to cold and fire.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Arcane (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>The sorcerer forms a magical bond with a creature or an object. Use the rules for the wizard’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard]{Arcane Bond}.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The sorcerer’s connection to magic is incredibly strong. She gets a free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reroll]{reroll} on any failed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} roll.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\n    <img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/avernus.webp\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<h3>Celestial</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Celestial (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>A celestial ancestor or divine intervention of some sort blessed this hero’s bloodline. Her <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}, </em>and<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> spells cause +2 damage to evil creatures (this stacks with Champion, see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.9 Edge Summaries]{Weird Edges}). She also gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Environmental Resistance]{environmental resistance} to cold and acid.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The celestial can extend or hide angel-like wings as a free action. While extended, she gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight} at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Destined</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Destined (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>The character is destined for great things. She gains one additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} per session.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The hero starts with two extra Bennies per session.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Draconic</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Draconic (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>There’s a dragon lurking somewhere in the family tree. Its scion gains claws (Str+d4), scaly skin (Armor +2), and +1 damage to powers with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{trappings} suitable to her draconic bloodline.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The sorcerer’s claws now add @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} +2 and she gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Environmental Resistance]{environmental resistance} common to her bloodline (acid for black, fire for red, etc.).</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Elemental</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Elemental]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>The mage’s family was touched by a powerful elemental force. Choose one of the elements listed below. Your hero gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Environmental Resistance]{environmental resistance} to that element and one of the following abilities:</p>\n\t\t\t<ul class=\"bullet\">\n\t\t\t<li><strong>Air:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} 6.</li>\n\t\t\t<li><strong>Earth: </strong>Burrowing Pace 6 (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]{Burrow}).</li>\n\t\t\t<li><strong>Fire:</strong> +2 damage to damaging Powers with a fire @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping}.</li>\n\t\t\t<li><strong>Water:</strong> Enemies are automatically @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hinder or Hurry]{Hindered} when affected by your powers.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> Once per encounter, you can unleash an elemental blast as an action. This causes 3d6 damage, uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template}, and may be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t <img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/woman-cultist.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/woman-cultist.webp\" />\n\t\t\t<h3>Fey</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Fey (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>The capricious nature of the fey runs in this sorcerer’s family. She ignores Difficult Terrain in the wilderness and has the “laughing touch.” If she successfully touches a target with her hands (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Touch Attack]{Touch Attack}), the target is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> Victims of a fey’s spell with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Lingering Damage]{lingering} effect, such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{blind}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{lower trait}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{stun},</em> and the like, subtract 2 from any roll made to recover.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<h3>Infernal</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infernal (Bloodline)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>A relative made a deal with dark forces in the distant past. The character gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Environmental Resistance]{environmental resistance} to fire, immunity to poison, and adds +1 to the damage of any attack powers with a fire @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping}.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The infernal grows or hides giant bat wings as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Actions]{free action}. Her wings grant her @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight} at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Undead</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Undead]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>The taint of the grave runs through the character’s bloodline. She gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Environmental Resistance]{environmental resistance} to cold and a +1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Advanced Form:</span> The sorcerer is truly undead. She gains the full @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Undead]{Undead} ability and the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Outsider]{Outsider} (Major) and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Ugly]{Ugly} (Major) Hindrance. The heroine might actually be attractive but she’s still disturbing to the living!</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n</div>\n\n<article class=\"class-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"wide\" style=\"clear:both\">Wizard</h1>\n\t\t\t<h3>Wizard</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Beyond the veil of the mundane hide the secrets of absolute power. Mysteries, and wonders of arcane realms call to those with the ambition— and the intellect— to grasp true power. Such is the path of the wizard. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>These magic-users research, collect, and covet esoteric knowledge. Some choose to become a master of a particular field of magic. Others embrace versatility, reveling in the unbounded wonders of all magic. In either case, wizards prove a cunning lot, capable of smiting their foes, empowering their allies, and shaping the world to their every desire.</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Arcane Background</span> <strong>(Wizard):</strong> Wizards use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} as their arcane skill. A hero who takes this Edge gains 10 Power Points and three powers from the list below.<br /><strong>Available Powers:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Baleful Polymorph]{baleful polymorph}</em>,<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{banish}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{blind}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower trait}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]{burrow}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]{curse}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{damage field}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{darksight}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispel}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{divination}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{drain power points}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{environmental protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{fear}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{growth/shrink}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light / Darkness]{light/darkness}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{mind link}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{mind reading}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Wipe]{Mind Wipe}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{object reading}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Binding]{planar binding}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{plane shift}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{puppet}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{sloth/speed}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{slumber}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{sound/silence}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{stun}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{summon ally}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{time stop}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{wall walker}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{wish}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zombie]{zombie}</em>.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Arcane Bond:</span> Wizards form an intense magical bond with an object or creature. See <strong>Arcane Bond,</strong> below.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armor Interference</span> <strong>(Any):</strong> Like sorcerers, wizards must gesticulate in precise patterns. They subtract 4 from their Spellcasting rolls and from their Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">School:</span> A wizard’s studies lead him down one of two paths— the “universalist” who dabbles in all the various “schools” of magic, or a “specialist” who focuses on one school at the expense of some others.<br />Specialists must choose one favored school and two opposition schools from the list @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Schools of Magic]{here}}. They gain a free reroll on arcane skill rolls to cast spells (not activating an item) from their favored school, but spells cast from their opposition school cost one additional Power Point and suffer a −2 penalty to the wizard's arcane skill roll.<br />Wizards mark opposition spells in their power lists with an asterisk, like this: <em>banish*</em>.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Spellbooks:</span> Wizards must keep and maintain spellbooks.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane Bond</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>Wizards immerse themselves in the study of eldritch lore and arcane theories. During these long hours they form a bond with a dependable item or friendly creature (a “familiar”). Choose one of the following options for your wizard:</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Bonded Object:</span> The spellcaster possesses an amulet, ring, staff, wand, or weapon that adds +1 to all his Spellcasting totals when worn or in hand. If the object is lost or destroyed, the mage can replace it with a new object worth at least 500 gp.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Familiar:</span> The mage has a magical pet. See the sidebar below.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Favored powers (Wizard)</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Wizard)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Wizard</p>\n<p>The wizard has great familiarity with certain powers and can cast them quickly and easily. As a limited free action, he may ignore up to two points of <em>any</em> penalties (Multi-Action, Wounds, Fatigue, etc.) when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispel}</em>.</p>\n<p>This Edge doesn’t give him those powers — they must be taken separately.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"iconic-path\">Ezren <span class=\"reduced\">(Novice, Iconic Path Wizard)</span></h2>\n\t\t\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Ezren]{Ezren} finds solace in his arcane studies, which he pursues in the field rather than dusty libraries. The elderly wizard travels far and wide to research and discover new magics, partly as a way to put the shame of his father’s heresy behind him.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Ancestry:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Human]{Human} (Adaptable)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"statblock\">\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Attributes</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Agility d6 (-1)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Smarts d10</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Spirit d8</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Strength d4 (-1)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vigor d6 (-1)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"red-label\">Derived</span>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Parry: 4 (5 Staff)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Toughness: 5</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pace: 5 (d6-1)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bennies: 3</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Hindrances:</span> Elderly, Shamed (Major—Father’s Heresy)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Edges:</span> Wizard (Bonded Object—Cane, School—Universalist), Jack of All Trades</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><span class=\"red-label\">Languages:</span> Abyssal, Common, Dwarven, Elven, Giant, Thassilonian</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Skills:</span> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Academics]{Academics} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">POWERS:</span> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</em>,<em> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em></p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Gear:</span> Cane (Str+d4, Parry +1, Reach 1, two hands), dagger (Str+d4), hand crossbow (Range 5/10/20, Damage 2d4), 20 bolts, spell component pouch, spellbook, adventurer's kit,  ink pen, ink, parchment, scroll of <em>slumber</em>, 24 gp.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n<div style=\"width:50%;float:left\">\n<h2>Advancement</h2>\n\t<table>\n\t<tbody><tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>1 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower trait}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>2 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light / Darkness]{light/darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{summon ally}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>3 –</strong> Power Points (15 total)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>S –</strong> Favored Powers (Wizard)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>5 –</strong> Channeling\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>6 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{sloth/speed}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>7 –</strong> Agility d8\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>V –</strong> Arcane Mastery\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>9 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{puppet}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>10 –</strong> Concentration\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>11 –</strong> Power Points (20 total)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>H –</strong> Eldritch Inspiration\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>13 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{growth/shrink}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>14 –</strong> Extraction\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>15 –</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} d12\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>L –</strong> Professional (Spellcasting d12 + 1)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>17 –</strong> New Powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{Plane shift}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{time stop}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{wish}</em>\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>18 –</strong> Expert (Spellcasting d12 + 2)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>19 –</strong> Power Points (22 total)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t<tr>\n\t<td class=\"left\">\n\t\t\t<strong>20 –</strong> Master (Spellcasting)\n\t</td>\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody></table>\n\t<p> </p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"float:right;width:50%\">\n\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/wizard.webp\" /></div>\n</article>\n\t<div>\t<aside class=\"sidebar\" style=\"clear:both\">\n\t\t\t\t<h1 class=\"red\">Familiars</h1>\n\t\t\t\t<p>“Familiars” are small Animals (Size −2 or −3) that serve as loyal pets and magical companions to certain kinds of spellcasters.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Familiars are loyal to their masters but aren’t slaves. They are typical but very smart versions of their species and can occasionally be distracted by their own inherent instincts. For example, a cat might interrupt its task to chase a mouse or take a brief nap, and a hawk will almost certainly be distracted by sudden movements.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>A familiar is a Wild Card with respect to Wounds and rolling a Wild Die with its Trait rolls. It doesn’t get Bennies, but the mage can spend his own on its behalf.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>The familiar can understand its master’s speech and vice-versa (others hear only the creature’s natural sounds), though concepts are limited to what a member of its species might understand. </p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>The familiar has 5 Power Points of its own. It cannot cast spells, but the mage can draw on them as if they were his own. They recharge separately and at the same rate as the mage’s. </p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>The bond between the familiar and the mage makes it immune to the <em>beast fri</em><em>end</em> power.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>If a familiar dies, the hero is automatically Stunned (no matter how far away he is). He can summon another after 10 days and can change the type if she chooses.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Familiars don’t advance, but instead gain one of the advantages below for each of its master’s Ranks (including Novice) and for every fourth advance the hero gains past Legendary.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t<li>The owner may use the familiar’s senses as if they were her own, with a maximum range of 10 miles. She is Distracted and Vulnerable while doing so.</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t<li>The mage can increase one of the familiar’s Traits one die type (no more than once per Trait).</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t<li>The familiar gains an Edge. It must make sense for the familiar’s species (GM’s call) and meet the Requirements as usual.</li>\n\t\t\t\t</ul></aside></div>\n\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Arcane Mastery</h3>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Wizard</p>\n<p>True understanding of magical energy comes with practice and experience. Wizards who take this Edge gain access to all their powers’ Epic Power Modifiers (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers}).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Eldritch Inspiration</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Inspiration]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, Wizard</p>\n<p>Great wizards gather esoteric information in their spellbooks, allowing them to harness magical powers at a whim. Assuming he has his spellbook on his person, the wizard can spend a Benny to cast any power of his Rank or lower. The power may be maintained normally but afterwards is forgotten (the wizard doesn’t add it to his list of powers).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Spellbooks</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Spellbook, Wizard (blank)]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>Wizard spells are strange, complex things that fade quickly from the minds of even the most accomplished casters. For this reason, each wizard maintains a spellbook with the spells he’s translated and acquired. He studies them daily, transcribing their mystical patterns onto his mind.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The link to the book is far more than rote memorization— it is an arcane bond with the power and patterns within. If a wizard doesn’t have access to his spellbook, he may continue to cast normally until the next sunset or sunrise (whichever comes first). After that, the magical imprint on his mind fades and he can no longer cast them.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Wizards may only carry one active spellbook at a time. The mountains of scrolls, magical notations, and research needed to prepare another cannot be carried with the wizard and must be stored safely somewhere. It takes a week of work and 500 gp to create a replacement spellbook once the wizard has access to his magical notes.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>When a wizard takes the New Powers Edge, he chooses any two powers as usual. If he has found any spells (including scrolls) through exploration or purchase, and it is of his Rank or less, he may take one of those as a bonus third power at that time as well</p>\n\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Combat Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>These Edges are designed to help your hero dish out terrible damage— or survive it— in the bloody battles of <cite>Savage Worlds</cite>.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Block</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Block]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Through hard-fought experience your hero has learned to defend himself in vicious hand-to-hand combat. His Parry increases by +1 and any Gang Up bonus against him is reduced by one.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Block</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Block]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Block</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero’s Parry bonus is now +2 and the Gang Up bonus against him is reduced by 2.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Brawler</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawler]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it’s made of stone. Brawlers increase their Toughness by 1 and roll Strength +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Claws]{Claws}</strong>, the monk’s Unarmed Strike ability, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Brawler Edge doesn’t make the character’s fists <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</strong>.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Bruiser</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bruiser]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Brawler</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The fighter increases his Toughness an additional +1, and the damage caused with his fists or claws another die type.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Calculating</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Calculating]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A few seconds to study a foe’s actions gives your hero a major advantage. When his Action Card is a Five or less, he ignores up to 2 points of penalties on one action that turn, which can include Multi-Action, cover, Range, and even Wound penalties.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Combat Reflexes</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Reflexes]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your warrior recovers quickly from shock and trauma. He adds +2 when rolling to recover from being Shaken or Stunned.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Counterattack</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Counterattack]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Fighters with this Edge deal instant punishment for an enemy’s mistakes. Once per round (if not Shaken or Stunned), the character receives a <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attack}</strong> against one failed Fighting attack against him. The counterattack takes place immediately (before other hits against the hero on the same Action Card, if any).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Counterattack</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Counterattack]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Counterattack</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As above but the hero gets a Free Attack against up to three failed attacks each round.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Dead Shot</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dead Shot]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>When your Action Card is a Joker, double the total damage of your first successful Athletics (throwing) or Shooting roll this round.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Dodge</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dodge]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Agility d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero can anticipate attacks or move erratically under fire. Unless the victim of a surprise attack is taken completely unaware, Dodge subtracts 2 from all ranged attacks made against him. Dodge does <em>not</em> stack with actual cover.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Dodge</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Dodge]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Dodge</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero adds +2 when evading area effect attacks. See <strong>\"@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion}</strong>.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Extraction</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extraction]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>When a character withdraws from melee, adjacent attackers get a free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against him (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdrawing From Melee}</strong>). This is a very dangerous proposition for most, but not your wily champion. When moving away from adjacent foes, one of them (player’s choice), doesn’t get his free Fighting attack.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Extraction</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Extraction]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Extraction</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Up to three foes’ (player’s choice) don’t get attacks when your warrior moves out of melee with them.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Feint</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Feint]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>When performing a <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}</strong> with the Fighting skill, you can choose to make the foe resist with Smarts instead of Agility.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>First Strike</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.First Strike]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Once per round, as long as he’s not Shaken or Stunned, the hero gets a free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against a foe immediately after he moves into Reach. (See <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attack}</strong>).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved First Strike</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved First Strike]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Heroic, First Strike</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As above but the hero may attack up to three foes each round.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Formation fighter</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Formation Fighter]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character has trained to fight alongside others, overwhelming their common foe with synchronized strikes and blows. She increases the Gang Up bonus by an additional +1 for herself and her allies. The maximum Gang Up bonus is still +4 no matter how many Formation Fighters stand together.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Free Runner</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Free Runner]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character is skilled and fearless when it comes to running, jumping, swinging, or scampering up walls and obstacles, through crowded city streets, or even swinging through the rigging of a ship.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>While on foot, she moves at her full Pace in such circumstances and adds +2 to Athletics rolls made to climb or negotiate obstacles as long as there are hand- or footholds she can bound on, bounce off, or swing from.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Frenzy</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A character with Frenzy rolls a second Fighting die with any one of his standard Fighting attacks for the turn (extra dice from Frenzy cannot be added to limited actions). The extra die may be allocated to the same or different targets as he sees fit. Resolve each separately.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Frenzy</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Frenzy</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The fighter rolls an extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with up to two Fighting attacks in the same turn.</p>\n\t\t\t<blockquote><em><strong>Example:</strong></em> A fighter attacks a giant scorpion. He has Improved Frenzy and decides to attack three times (a Multi-Action at the usual penalty). He rolls the Fighting skill with an extra die for his first and second attack. The fighter doesn’t get the extra die on the third Fighting roll.</blockquote>\n\t\t\t<h3>Giant Killer</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Giant Killer]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The bigger they are, the harder they are to kill. At least for most. Your hero knows how to find the weak points in the most massive of foes.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>He adds +1d6 damage when attacking creatures who are three or more Sizes larger than himself (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size &amp; Scale}</strong>). A human (Size 0) gets the bonus against a creature of Size 3 or greater.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Hard To Kill</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hard To Kill]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his Wound penalties when making Vigor rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bleeding Out]{Bleeding Out}</strong>.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Harder to Kill</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Harder To Kill]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Hard to Kill</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If your Pathfinder is ever “killed,” roll a die. On an odd result, he’s dead as usual. On an even roll, he’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} but somehow escapes death. He may be captured, stripped of all his belongings, or mistakenly left for dead, but he somehow survives.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improvisational Fighter</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improvisational Fighter]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Smarts d6+ </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Heroes often find themselves @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} with pieces of equipment or furnishings not designed for combat. A brawler with this Edge has a knack for using such improvised weapons. He ignores the usual −2 penalty when wielding them. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Improvised Weapons]{here} for details on <strong>Improvised Weapons</strong>.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Iron Jaw</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Jaw]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Vigor d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero can shrug off even extreme blows. He adds +2 to Soak rolls and Vigor rolls to avoid <strong>Knockout Blows</strong> (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Killer Instinct</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Killer Instinct]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This hero hates losing. He gets a free reroll in any opposed Test he initiates.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Level Headed</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Smarts d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Fighters who can keep their cool when everyone else is running for cover make deadly combatants. A hero with this Edge draws an additional Action Card in combat and chooses which to use.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Level Headed</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Level Headed]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Level Headed</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As above but the hero draws two additional cards and chooses which to keep.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Marksman</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Marksman]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d8+ or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero is a natural with ranged weapons. If she doesn’t move in a turn and fires no more than a Rate of Fire of 1 as her first action, she may add +1 to an Athletics (throwing) or Shooting roll, or ignore up to 2 points of penalties from Called Shots, Cover, Range, Scale, or Speed. This is a lesser version of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Aim]{Aim} maneuver and does not stack with it. Marksman doesn’t apply to additional attacks after the first in a turn, including those fired with the Rapid Shot Edge or similar abilities.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Mighty Blow</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mighty Blow]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If your Action Card is a Joker, double the damage of your first successful Fighting attack this round.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Nerves of Steel</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nerves of Steel]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Vigor d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your hero has learned to fight on through the most intense pain. He may ignore 1 point of Wound penalties.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Nerves of Steel</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Nerves of Steel]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Nerves of Steel</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero ignores two points of Wound penalties.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>No Mercy</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.No Mercy]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned</p>\n\t\t\t<p>When this killer spends a Benny to reroll damage, he adds +2 to his final total. </p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Rapid Reload</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Reload]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The warrior reduces the Reload value of a ranged weapon by 1. See <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload}</strong>. This is most often taken for archers using crossbows with a Reload of 1 or 2. Weapons with Reload 1 may be reloaded as a free action with this Edge.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A character with this Edge may use Rapid Shot with a weapon if its Reload value has been reduced to a free action.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Rapid Shot</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Shot]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The shooter is practiced at taking quick and accurate shots. When she’s armed with a weapon that can be Reloaded as a free action, and has enough arrows to do so, she may increase her weapon’s Rate of Fire by 1 for any one of her Shooting attacks that turn.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Rapid Shot may be used with Rapid Reload.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Rapid shot</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Rapid Shot]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Rapid Shot</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The shooter may now increase her weapon’s Rate of Fire by 1 twice in the same turn (via a Multi-Action). </p>\n<p>Improved Rapid Shot can be used with Rapid Reload.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Steady Hands</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steady Hands]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Firing from the back of a horse or moving platform is tricky business, but your adventurer has figured it out. She ignores the <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unstable Platform]{Unstable Platform}</strong> penalty. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>This also helps when running, reducing the usual penalty from −2 to −1 (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Movement}</strong>).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Sweep</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Strength d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Some heroes are able to face down multiple enemies at once. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>As a limited action, Sweep allows a character to make a single Fighting attack with a two-handed weapon and apply it against all targets in his Reach at a −2 penalty (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that’s hit.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Note:</strong> Some creatures have the Sweep Edge even though they don't have two-handed weapons. In their case their size, lanky limbs, or other advantages allow them to make Sweep attacks.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Sweep</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sweep]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Sweep</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As above but the whirlwind of death may ignore the −2 penalty.</p>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/cutpurse.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/cutpurse.webp\" />\n\t\t\t<h3>Trademark Weapon</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, skill with chosen weapon of d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds +1 to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls, and +1 to Parry when readied (even if it’s a ranged weapon).</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don’t kick in for a few days (however long the GM feels is dramatically appropriate).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Improved Trademark Weapon</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Trademark Weapon]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Trademark Weapon</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As above but the bonuses when using the weapon increase to +2.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Two-weapon fighting</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Two-Weapon Fighting]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If a character makes an attack with one action and another from a different hand in a later action, the second attack doesn’t inflict a Multi-Action penalty. The <strong>Off-Hand</strong> penalty still applies unless he’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}, however.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character can choose to make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack with each hand, an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) attack with each hand, or a combination of these, depending on the readied weapons.</p>\n\t\t\t<blockquote><em><strong>Example:</strong></em> A fighter wields a longsword in one hand and a dagger in the other. He has Two-Weapon Fighting so he rolls Fighting on one action with the sword, and then makes a second Fighting roll—or an Athletics (throwing) roll—with the dagger, with no Multi-Action penalty to either.</blockquote>\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Leadership Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Leadership Edges grant bonuses to allies, making them more effective, reliable, or durable.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Unless an Edge says otherwise, it only affects allied Extras. Wild Cards only benefit if the leader has the Natural Leader Edge. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Leadership Edges aren’t cumulative with the same Edge from other leaders. Characters may benefit from different Leadership Edges by the same or different leaders, however.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Command Range:</strong> Allies must be within 5″ (10 yards) and be able to see and hear their leader to benefit from her abilities. This is called her “Command Range.”</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Command</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Command is the basic ability to give clear instructions and support to allies in the thick of battle. Extras in Command Range add +1 to their Spirit or Vigor rolls when attempting to recover from being Shaken or Stunned, respectively.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Command Presence</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command Presence]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Command</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A booming voice, effective commands, natural charisma, or simple training results in a much more effective combat element. A hero with this Edge has a Command Range of 10″ (20 yards).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Fervor</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fervor]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Spirit d8+, Command</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A simple phrase uttered by a great leader can sometimes have momentous results. A commander with this ability can inspire his troops to bloody fervor.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Extras in range add +1 to their Fighting damage rolls.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Hold the Line!</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hold the Line!]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Hold the Line strengthens the will of any Extras under the hero’s command, adding +1 to their Toughness.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3>Inspire</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inspire]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Command</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Exceptional leaders inspire those around them to great feats of valor and determination. As a limited action, the hero may roll his Battle skill to Support one type of Trait roll, and apply it to <em>all</em> allied Extras in Command Range. A leader could Support all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks in range, for example. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>Bonuses from this Edge can't stack with others.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Natural Leader</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Natural Leader]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Spirit d8+, Command</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This leader has proven herself time and time again, gaining the respect of all those who fight by her side.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Any Leadership Edge that says it applies only to Extras now applies to Wild Cards (including the player characters) as well.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Tactician</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tactician]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command, Battle d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The commander has a natural grasp of small unit tactics and can take advantage of rapidly changing situations.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A Tactician is dealt an extra Action Card each round of combat— kept separate from his own cards. At the start of the round, he may discard it or give it to any one allied Extra in Command Range. The player or GM controlling the receiving character can decide whether to accept and replace her current Action Card, or discard it.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Surprise:</strong> Tacticians don’t get their extra card if Surprised, but they can give it to an ally who’s Surprised if they like!</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Master Tactician</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Tactician]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Veteran, Tactician</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Tactician now gets a total of two extra Action Cards to distribute each round.</p>\n\t\n\t<img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/lady-liberty.webp\" />\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Power Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Power Edges are the key to unlocking the true potential of those with Arcane Backgrounds. They can mean the difference between an apprentice with a few abilities and a master of magic or divine energies!</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane Armor</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Armor]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Armor Interference</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your Armor Interference counts as one level higher (so a character increasing their Armor Interference (Any) to (Light) could wear Light armor with no penalty).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Artificer</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Those who tangle with supernatural forces sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a magic sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even bless holy relics with divine grace.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Artificers can create <strong>Arcane Devices</strong> and give them to their allies. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}. Where possible, the device reflects the forger’s background. A bard’s Arcane Devices are works of art, such as a singing sword, a magical instrument, an epic poem, etc.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Channeling</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channeling]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>When the character gets a raise on her arcane skill roll (or roll to activate or use an arcane device), she reduces its Power Point cost by 1. This <em>can</em> take it to 0.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Concentration</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Concentration]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Through training and focus, the caster is extremely efficient in channeling arcane forces. The base Duration of any non-Instant power is doubled. This includes maintaining powers as well.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Holy/Unholy Warrior</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Vow (to your Deity)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Believers face grave dangers in service to their divine patrons. To survive such hardships, the forces of good (or evil) grant miracles and the ability to turn their favor into supernatural protection.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>After making a Soak roll, the chosen may add +1 to the total for each Power Point spent, to a maximum of +4.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>New Powers</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.New Powers]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Arcane Background (Any)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>An arcane character may learn two new powers by choosing this Edge (which may be taken multiple times). He may choose from any powers of his Rank or lower normally available to his particular Arcane Background. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>A character can add a new Trapping on a power she already has instead of gaining a new one. She might add an ice Trapping to her existing fire <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>, for example, so she could switch between ice and fire Trappings freely.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If a wizard takes this Edge, he may choose to learn two powers, as usual, plus a bonus  third power, if he has discovered one contained in spellbooks or scrolls he has acquired. The wizard transcribes all three new powers into his spellbook and the original scrolls or spellbooks from which he gleaned his knowledge are added to his repository of notes and research in case he has to make a replacement spellbook in the future.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Power Points</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Wizards, sorcerers, and other arcane types always want more power. This Edge grants them an additional 5 Power Points.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Power Points may be selected more than once, but only once per Rank. It may be taken as often as desired at Legendary Rank, but each grants only 2 additional points.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Power Surge</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Surge]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Novice, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character recovers 10 Power Points when his Action Card is a Joker. This may not exceed his usual limit.</p>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/spellbook.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/spellbook.webp\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<h3>Soul Drain</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soul Drain]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Once per day, Soul Drain allows a character to take a level of Fatigue to recover up to five Power Points as a limited free action. Or she can take two levels of Fatigue (Exhaustion) to recover up to 10 Power Points. She cannot render herself @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} in this way.</p>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Prestige Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Prestige Edges build on other Edges, classes, and skills to provide unique talents possessed by a rare few.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A character may only choose a new core Prestige Edge once per Rank (instead of a core Class Edge), and once every four Advances at Legendary Rank. Advanced Edges (the level II and III Edges listed below) are not subject to this restriction.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Arcane Archer</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>An arcane archer uses magical energies to amplify his arrows or bolts. He may automatically grant one \"quality\" into any arrow he fires (designated per shot).</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The first two qualities an archer learns are:</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Enhance:</strong> The archer's arrow adds +1 to Shooting and damage.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Trapping:</strong> The arrow has an environmental Trapping such as fire, cold, darkness, etc.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane Archer II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Arcane Archer</span></p>\n<p>The archer gains two new qualities:</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Phase Arrow:</strong> Once per encounter, the archer may fire an arrow directly through any non-magical barriers, ignoring penalties for Cover or Concealment.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Hail of Arrows:</strong> Once per encounter, the archer may enchant an arrow so it splits into many when fired, raining down in a Large Blast Template. Everyone inside the template is subject to the attack roll— roll damage separately.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane Archer III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\n\t\t\t<p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Heroic, Arcane Archer II</span></p>\n<p>The archer gains two new qualities:</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Imbue:</strong> Once per turn, the archer can imbue any area effect power into an arrow, \"casting\" the spell with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} and using his bow's Range in place of the power's Range. The spell's area of effect is centered where the arrow lands, even if it must normally be centered on the caster. If the arrow misses, the spell fails. Imbued spells can't be Shorted or use the Range modifier.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Death Arrow:</strong> Once per day, the archer can fire a fearsome arrow thrumming with deadly energy. A target Shaken or Wounded by the arrow must make a Vigor roll or die! Death arrows have no effect on constructs or undead.</p>\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/arcane-trickster.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/arcane-trickster.webp\" />\n\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Arcane Trickster</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Sneak Attack ability, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>These prodigious thieves blend subtle aspects of the arcane with the cunning of sleight of hand and misdirection.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Ranged Legerdemain:</strong> The trickster can use his Thievery at a Range of 5” (10 yards) or less at a −2 penalty. Any object manipulated at range must weigh less than 5 pounds.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Impromptu Attack:</strong> Once per encounter, the trickster may use her Sneak Attack ability even if a foe isn’t Vulnerable or subject to the Drop.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane Trickster II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Seasoned, Arcane Trickster</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Invisible Thief:</strong> Once per day, as a free action, the character may cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}</em> for a base cost of 1 Power Point. No arcane skill roll is required, and it's cast as if with a raise. The trickster may use other Power Modifiers or maintain the spell with her own Power Points as usual.</p>\n<p>This Edge doesn't grant the trickster the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}</em> spell; she must have it on her own.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Arcane Trickster III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Arcane Trickster II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Surprise Spells:</strong> The trickster’s attack spells benefit from her Sneak Attack ability.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Assassin</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Sneak Attack ability</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Those with this Edge are adept at infiltration and cold, efficient murder. They consider themselves artisans, and their medium is death.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Death Attack:</strong> If the assassin strikes a living victim with the Drop and causes at least one Wound (after any Soaking), the foe must make a Vigor roll or die.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If the assassin Incapacitates or slays a victim he had the Drop on, the victim drops quietly and without a sound. It may even be a few moments before those nearby @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} the situation, depending on the circumstances.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Assassin II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Assassin</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Hide in Plain Sight:</strong> The assassin may magically hide in plain sight. Treat this as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}</em> (−4), as long as the assassin doesn’t move or make noise.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Resistance to Poison:</strong> The assassin adds +4 to rolls made to resist poison.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Assassin III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin III]{Link to Journal Entry}<span class=\"western\">Requirements: Heroic, Assassin II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Angel of Death:</strong> The slayer gains the mystical ability to charge her attack with lethal death energy. If she chooses to do so, a victim slain by her hand crumbles to dust and cannot be resurrected. She may do this no more than once per day.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Swift Death:</strong> Once per day, as a free action, an assassin gains the Drop over a foe of her choice, even if the target is completely aware of her presence.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Dragon Disciple</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (any) or Mystic Powers (Any), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Spellcasters who embrace their draconic heritage and learn to channel their abilities become fearsome warriors. They possess not only the repertoire of an accomplished sorcerer, but also the ability to unleash the furious power of dragons upon their foes.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Breath Attack:</strong> Once per encounter, as a limited action the dragon disciple may make a breath attack in a Cone Template. The attack causes 3d6 damage and may be Evaded. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>The attack has one of the following effects, based on the type of dragon the character descends from: fire (victims may catch fire, see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}), acid (lingering damage, see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}), electricity (+2 damage to those in metal armor), or cold (victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hinder or Hurry]{Hindered} until the end of  his next turn, see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Dragon Disciple II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Dragon Disciple</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Wings:</strong> The dragon disciple’s body becomes more scaly, his eyes more feral, and he may even grow small horns. Eventually, scaly wings sprout from his back, granting him @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight} (Pace 8).</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/blue-dragon.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/blue-dragon.webp\" />\n\n\n\n\t\t\t<h3>Dragon Disciple III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Heroic, Dragon Disciple II</span></p>\n<p>The disciple’s transformation is now complete— this permanently changes her Type to Dragon.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Dragon Form:</strong> Twice per day as a limited action, the dragon disciple may take the form of a dragon of her bloodline. This makes her Size 3, Strength d12, and Vigor d10. She has Armor 4, and her Bite/Claw attack is Str+d8, AP 2. Her wings grow to accommodate her form.</p>\n<p>If she doesn't already have it, her dragon form also grants her environmental resistance common to her draconic heritage (electricity for blue, fire for red, etc.)</p>\n<p>Her clothing, gear, and magic items meld into her form and provide no benefits. She can remain in this form for up to five minutes, and extend the Duration another five minutes by taking a level of Fatigue.</p>\n<p>She may still speak and cast spells in dragon form.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Duelist</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Agility d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Duelists represent the pinnacle of elegant swordplay, parrying blows and countering their opponent’s actions with expert ripostes. </p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Surgical Strike:</strong> A duelist makes surgical strikes with one-handed piercing weapons with a Min Str of d6 or less, adding +2 to her damage total.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Parry:</strong> If the duelist hasn’t acted this turn, she may declare the Defend maneuver after an opponent declares a Fighting attack against her but before he rolls. She discards her current Action Card and her Parry bonus is +6 instead of +4 that turn.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Duelist II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Seasoned, Duelist</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Crippling Strike:</strong> A foe Shaken or Wounded by the duelist reduces his Pace by 2 until healed. No foe can be subject to more than one crippling strike, and can’t be reduced below a Pace of 1.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Duelist III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Duelist II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Deflect Arrows:</strong> The duelist can now deflect arrows, bolts, and thrown weapons. Enemies subtract 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls to hit him. This stacks with Dodge and similar abilities, and is ignored if the duelist is surprised, Bound, unaware of the attack, or can’t generally parry the projectiles.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Eldritch Knight</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Arcane Background (any) or Mystic Powers (Any), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Elite warriors who train in both the martial and arcane arts learn how to take extra advantage of their prowess in both. These versatile heroes, the Eldritch Knights, are usually characters who studied both the martial and arcane arts.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Eldritch Recharge:</strong> Anytime the knight gets a raise on a damaging attack roll (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), Fighting, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, or arcane skill), he regains a Power Point.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Eldritch Knight II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Eldritch Knight</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Eldritch Strike:</strong> The knight can spend two Power Points after making an attack roll to increase its total by +2.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Eldritch Knight III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight III]{Eldritch Knight III}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Heroic, Eldritch Knight II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Eldritch Strike (Imp):</strong> The knight can spend two Power Points after making a successful attack roll to increase that attack's damage by +2.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Loremaster</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Smarts d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Academics]{Academics} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A gatherer of secrets and arcane lore, this character values the acquisition of intellectual insights above all else. Often obsessed by the written word, the loremaster knows better than any that knowledge is power.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Lore:</strong> She gets a free reroll when making Academics, Common Knowledge, Occult, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science} rolls.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Loremaster II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Loremaster</span></p>\n<p>The loremaster gains special insight into those she’s traveled and adventured with. </p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Secret:</strong> With the Game Master’s consent, she may take one ability from any core Class Edge she doesn’t already have. She might take the druid’s Wilderness Stride ability, for example, the rogue’s Sneak Attack, or a cleric’s ability to Channel Energy.</p>\n<p>This doesn’t confer any other Traits, Edges, or rules required to use the ability.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Loremaster III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Heroic,<br />Loremaster II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Greater Lore:</strong> The loremaster learns two new powers from any of those available in the campaign. This may not be useful if a power depends on mechanics the loremaster can’t make use of, but she can still learn the spell if she likes.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Mystic Theurge</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, two Arcane Backgrounds with two different arcane skills</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Mystic theurges place no boundaries on their magical abilities, whether they stem from the arcane or divine.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Combined Spells:</strong> A theurge can cast two spells as a limited action. The theurge must use two different arcane skills, declare her spells and all Power Modifiers as usual, then roll a die for each (the Wild Die can replace either). If the arcane skills have the same die type use different colored dice so you know which is which.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The cost of both spells must be paid separately, and effects from Critical Failure apply normally but don’t stack.</p>\n\t\t\t<blockquote><em><strong>Example:</strong></em> A theurge casts bolt with Spellcasting (d8) and healing with Faith (d10). She rolls a d8, a d10, and her Wild die, which may take the place of either skill die. She casts both spells, spends the usual number of Power Points, and may use any Power Modifiers she wishes for each.</blockquote>\n\t\t\t<h3>Mystic Theurge II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Mystic Theurge</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Spell Synergy:</strong> When the theurge uses her Combined Spells ability she reduces the cost of each spell by one Power Point (to a minimum of 1).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Mystic Theurge III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Heroic, Mystic Theurge II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Spell Synthesis:</strong> The character's Class Edge abilities can now be applied to all spells provided by any of her classes.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-left\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/guildmaster.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/guildmaster.webp\" />\n\n\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Pathfinder Chronicler</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Pathfinder Chronicler]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Brave explorers and seekers of lost or forgotten knowledge, these heroes are quintessential adventurers. They travel the world searching for esoteric truths, magical and mundane relics, and unexplored vistas. </p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Pathfinding:</strong> The pathfinder increases the party’s speed by 10% when navigating to known or mapped locations. See <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Travel]{Travel}</strong>.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>She also knows which paths are safest and where to exercise additional caution. If the Game Master is drawing for encounters and gets the <span>Enemies</span> result (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Travel]{Travel}), the chronicler may make a Smarts roll at −2 to discard that card and replace it with the next card in the deck.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Pathfinder Chronicler II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Pathfinder Chronicler II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Seasoned, Pathfinder Chronicler</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Epic Tales:</strong> The chronicler recites a moving and evocative tale. Once per session, while the party is resting, every Wild Card ally who hears the tale gains a Benny.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Pathfinder Chronicler III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Pathfinder Chronicler III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Pathfinder Chronicler II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Call Down the Legends:</strong> Once per game week, the chronicler can magically summon five “shades” of great Eberron heroes who have gone before. The shades assume mortal form, have the profiles in the sidebar at right, and last for one hour.</p>\n\n\n\t\t\t<aside class=\"sidebar\">\n\t\t\t\t<h1 class=\"red\">Shades</h1>\n\t\t\t\t<p>The shades appear as silent, somewhat formless heroes of Eberron— elves, dwarves, humans, and others. They cannot be mistaken for living beings except in the most obscured conditions. They appear from darkness and vanish into it when their time on the mortal realm expires. They are physical while here, and have only a fraction of their true self’s abilities. </p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Attributes:</strong> Agility d6, Smarts d4, Spirit d6, Strength d8, Vigor d8</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Skills:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d8, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Pace:</strong> 6; <strong>Parry:</strong> 5; <strong>Toughness:</strong> 8 (2)</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Hindrances:</strong> —</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Edges:</strong> —</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Gear:</strong> Leather armor (+2), long sword (Str+d8).</p>\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n\t\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<li><strong>Construct:</strong> +2 to recover from being Shaken; don’t breathe; immune to poison and disease.</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t<li><strong>Fearless:</strong> Shades are immune to Fear and Intimidation.</li>\n\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</aside>\n\n\n\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"item\">Shadowdancer</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shadowdancer]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} d6+ @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Some characters prefer the shadows, embracing the advantages of darkness to become artists of deception and surprise. </p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Greater Darkvision:</strong> Strong connection to the plane of shadows allows the hero to see perfectly in any illumination up to 10\" (20 yards), including magical darkness and ignoring all penalties resulting from it.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Shadowdancer II</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shadowdancer II]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Seasoned, Shadowdancer</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Shadow Cloak:</strong> Darkness envelops and protects its champion. She gets one free Soak attempt at −2 whenever she's Wounded in Dim or Dark Illumination. This does not count as spending a Benny.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Shadowdancer III</h3>\n\t\t\t<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shadowdancer III]{Link to Journal Entry}</p><p><span class=\"western\">Requirements: Veteran, Shadowdancer II</span></p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Mystic Powers (Shadow Force):</strong> As a limited free action the shadowdancer can cast one of the following spells: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{summon ally}</em>,<em> </em>or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em> (self only). All of these have a Shadow Trapping.</p>\n<p>The shadowdancer has 10 dedicated Power Points that @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Recharging]{recharge} normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} for more information on specific spells. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</em> still requires line of sight, but otherwise automatically hits as long as any part of the target is visible and in Range. </p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn’t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the shadowdancer also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges and abilities can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n\n<h2>Professional Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Professional Edges reflect years of practice or experience in a particular trade, activity, or craft. In some cases they may also represent special blessings from higher powers as well.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Players may purchase Professional Edges after character creation, perhaps roleplaying the achievement by practicing the affected trade during downtime or in between adventures.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Stacking:</strong> Bonuses to the same Trait from different Professional Edges do not stack— apply only the highest.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Ace</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ace]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Aces are pilots and drivers who have a special affinity with their vehicle. They ignore two points of penalties to any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Driving]{Driving}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} roll, and may spend Bennies to Soak damage for any vehicle they control or command, using the appropriate Boating, Driving, or Piloting skill instead of Vigor. Each success and raise negates a Wound.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Acrobat</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Acrobat]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Acrobat gets one free reroll on Athletics totals that involve balance, tumbling, or grappling. It doesn’t affect rolls to interrupt actions, climb, swim, or throw.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Combat Acrobat</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Acrobat]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Acrobat</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The tumbler leaps quickly about so that attacks against her are made at −1 as long as she’s aware of the attack, can reasonably move about, and isn’t suffering any Encumbrance or Minimum Strength penalties.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Born in the Saddle</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in the Saddle]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Whether it’s on the back of fast horse or other more exotic mount, this hero feels more at home in the saddle than on her own two feet.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Edge grants the hero one free reroll on all Riding rolls and increases her mount’s Pace by 2 and its running die one step.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Fix It</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fix It]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero is a natural with mechanical contraptions. She adds +2 to Repair rolls, and with a raise, halves the time normally required to fix something. This means if a particular Repair job says a raise repairs it in half the time, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fix It]{Fix It} can finish the job in one-quarter the time with a raise.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Investigator</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Investigator]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Academics]{Academics} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Investigators spend a great deal of time in vast libraries researching ancient legends, working the streets, or deducing Eberron’s greatest mysteries. They add +2 to Academics or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made to sift through information, sift through stacks of papers, look through shelves of books for something of note, or spy obscured items from piles of junk or debris.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Jack-Of-All-Trades</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Jack-Of-All-Trades]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d10+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Through advanced schooling, book-learning, or just amazing intuitive perception, your hero has a talent for picking up skills on the fly. There’s little she can’t figure out given a little time and a dash of luck.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character makes a Smarts roll as an action after observing or studying some subject. She gains a d4 in the relevant skill with success, or d6 with a raise. She may try again after an hour of study, trial and effort, or immersion if she fails or wants to try for a raise. This lasts until the character attempts to learn a different subject, whether she’s successful or not.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Scholar</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scholar]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Learned professors, devoted students, and amateur enthusiasts spend great amounts of time and energy studying particular subjects. They become experts in these fields, and rarely fail to answer questions in their particular area of expertise.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Academics]{Academics}, Battle, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Occult]{Occult}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}, or a Smarts-based “knowledge”-type skill allowed in your game, and add +2 to the total whenever they’re used.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Soldier</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soldier]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Professional soldiers get used to carrying heavy loads and enduring harsh conditions. After a few days getting used to their gear (GM’s call), they treat their Strength as one die type higher when determining <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Encumbrance]{Encumbrance}</strong>  and <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength}</strong> to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty. (This stacks with the Brawny Edge.)</p>\n\t\t\t<p>They also get a free reroll on Vigor rolls made to survive environmental hazards (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</strong>).</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This Edge has no effect on Armor Interference or Armor Restriction.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-left\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/guild-initiate.webp');-webkit-transform:scaleX(-1);transform:scaleX(-1)\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/guild-initiate.webp\" />\n\n\n\t\t\t<h3>Thief</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Thief]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Agility d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Thieves specialize in deceit, treachery, and acrobatics. They can be invaluable where traps must be detected, walls must be climbed, and locks must be picked.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Thieves know how to use the slimmest protrusions on walls and window ledges to climb the tallest of buildings, scampering through streets and back alleys like cats. They add +1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb in urban areas.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Thieves also know how to use the dark areas between the streetlights of cities to conceal their movements, and add +1 to Stealth rolls when in an urban environment.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Finally, these rogues are— not surprisingly— <br />adept at Thievery itself, adding +1 to those rolls in all circumstances.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Troubadour</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Troubadour]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Troubadours travel the world, learning culture, etiquette, history, and above all, legends. They add +2 to Common Knowledge rolls and may use Performance in place of Battle for Leadership Edges or Edges that require Battle.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Woodsman</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Woodsman]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d6+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Woodsmen are rangers, scouts, and hunters who are more at home in the wilderness than urban areas. They are skilled trackers and scouts, and know how to live off the land for months at a time.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Woodsmen add +2 to Survival and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} rolls made in the wild (not towns, ruins, or underground).</p>\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Social Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Getting people to do what you want is a critical skill, whether by coercion or charm.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Bolster</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bolster]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Belittling or humiliating an enemy can boost your ally’s spirits. When this character successfully Tests a foe, he may also remove the <strong>Distracted </strong>or<strong> Vulnerable</strong> state (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{here}) from one of his allies.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Common Bond</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Common Bond]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Selfless heroes and determined leaders know their greatest strength often comes from their companions, and are willing to give some of their own fortune, fate, or luck to support them.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A character with this Edge may freely give her Bennies to any other character she can communicate with. The player should explain what form this takes, from a quick shout of encouragement to a welcome pat on the back.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Connections</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Connections]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your heroine is connected to people or organizations who can help her when the chips are down. It might be the city guard, a guild, a wealthy noblewoman, or even other adventurers.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Connections may be taken more than once, selecting a new faction or contact each time. Once per session, and assuming she can get in touch with them, the heroine can call on her friends for a favor.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The favor depends on the nature of the contact (GM’s call), but might include a loan, gear, a few allied fighters, transportation, information, or even a professional with critical skills the party doesn’t have, like a tracker or scholar.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Humiliate</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Humiliate]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Those with a cruel wit can destroy a rival’s ego in a single remark or well-timed gesture. Your hero gets a free reroll on Taunt Tests.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Menacing</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Menacing]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, any one of Bloodthirsty, Mean, Ruthless, or Ugly</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Being a brutish lout isn’t always a drawback if you know how to use it. Menacing allows a character to put her bad looks or worse attitude to good use. The goon adds +2 to her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Provoke</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Provoke]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Clever characters can manipulate their foes, drawing enemy focus on themselves to protect their allies. Once per turn, when your hero uses Taunt for a Test and gets a raise (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}</strong>), she may Provoke the foe.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>In addition to all the usual effects of the success and raise, the enemy suffers a −2 penalty to affect any other target besides the one who provoked her. This stacks with Distracted but not further instances of Provoke.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Provoke lasts until a Joker is drawn, someone else Provokes the target, or the encounter ends. Provoke may be combined with <strong>Rabble Rouser</strong> (see below).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Rabble-Rouser</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This instigator knows how to rile up several enemies at once. As a limited action, a character with this Edge can make a social Test with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} against all enemies in a Medium Blast Template. The targets must be able to see and hear the hero clearly. Each defender resists and is affected by the Test separately.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Reliable</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reliable]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>People know they can depend on your hero when they need assistance. He gets a free reroll on any Support roll.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Retort</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Retort]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>This verbal duelist can turn the slings and arrows of social combat right back at the unwitting fools who hurled them.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If a character with Retort gets a raise when resisting an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or Taunt Test, the <em>foe</em> is Distracted.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Streetwise</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Streetwise]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Smarts d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Streetwise characters know how to find the local black market, fence stolen goods, avoid the local law (or criminal element!), lay low when the heat’s on, obtain illegal weapons, find out which “boss” is hiring muscle, or similar shady activities.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Streetwise characters add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls made to <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Network}</strong> with shady or criminal elements. They also add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls pertaining to the types of disreputable activities listed above.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-left\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/lem.webp');-webkit-transform:scaleX(-1);transform:scaleX(-1)\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/lem.webp\" />\n\n\t\t\t<h3>Strong Willed</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strong Willed]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Self-confidence is powerful armor against those who attempt to attack this individual’s will. He adds +2 to his total when resisting Tests with Smarts or Spirit.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Iron Will</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Will]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Brave, Strong Willed</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero now adds his Strong Willed bonus to resist powers and negate their effects. Iron Will doesn’t stack with Brave, nor does it apply to subsequent rolls resulting from powers such as being Shaken by a damaging power, fear, or the like.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Work the Room</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work the Room]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your hero’s words don’t just inspire those they’re directed at— they often inspire others as well. Once per turn, you can use Work the Room to roll an additional skill die when Supporting with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}. The additional die Supports any other ally who can see or hear your hero, and applies to their next action, whatever it may be.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Work the Crowd</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work the Crowd]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Seasoned, Work the Room</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As Work the Room but the hero now can Support another on up to two of her Support actions.</p>\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Weird Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Weird Edges are slightly supernatural in origin. These are usually appropriate in a <cite>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</cite> game, but check with your GM before taking them.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Beast Bond</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Bond]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Some individuals have an extraordinary bond with their animal companions. These characters may spend their own Bennies for any animals under their control, including mounts, pets, familiars, and so on.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Beast Master</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Master]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Animals take to your hero quickly and easily. They won’t attack him unless he attacks them first or they’re enraged for some reason.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Beast Master’s “animal magnetism” is so great he’s attracted a loyal animal of some sort as well. This is typically an animal of Size 0 or smaller, subject to the GM’s approval. </p>\n\t\t\t<p>The beast is an Extra and doesn’t Advance in Rank or abilities. If a pet is dismissed or killed, the hero gains a replacement in 1d4 days.</p>\n\t\t\t<p><strong>More Powerful Companions:</strong> Beast Master may be taken more than once. Choose one of the effects below each time it’s chosen:</p>\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\n\t\t\t\t<li>Gain an additional pet.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Increase one of the pet’s Traits one die type (only one Trait per pet).</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Increase the maximum Size pet you may have by +1, to a maximum of 3.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Make one pet a Wild Card. (The hero must be of Heroic Rank).</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<h3>Champion</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Champion]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Champions are holy (or unholy) men and women chosen to fight for a particular deity or religion. Most are pious souls ready and willing to lay down their lives for a greater cause, but some may have been born into the role and follow their path with some reluctance.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Champions fight the forces of darkness (or good), adding +2 damage when attacking supernaturally evil (or good if they’re evil) creatures. The bonus applies to area effect damage, ranged attacks, powers, etc.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The GM must decide which foes this bonus applies to, but generally it’s any evil (or good!) creature born of magic or with any supernatural abilities.</p>\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img class=\"float-right\" style=\"shape-outside:url('modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/tracker.webp')\" src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/tracker.webp\" />\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3>Danger Sense</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your hero can sense when something bad is about to happen. When rolling for <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Surprise]{Surprise}</strong>, he adds +2 to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll to act in the first round. With a raise, he starts the encounter on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hold]{Hold}.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>In other situations not covered by the Surprise rules (a sniper shot, pit trap, poisoned drink, etc.), Danger Sense gives him a Notice roll at −2 (or +2 if a Notice roll is usually allowed) to detect the hazard and take appropriate action. If this was an attack and the hero makes his Notice roll, the foe doesn’t get @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} against him.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Healer</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healer]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Spirit d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A hero with this Edge gets a free reroll on all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} rolls, whether natural or magical in nature.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Scavenger</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scavenger]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Novice, Luck</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Once per encounter the hero may find, “suddenly remember,” or dig up some much-needed piece of equipment, a quiver half-full of arrows, or some other useful device.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The Game Master decides what constitutes an encounter, and has the final word on what can and can’t be found.</p>\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t    <img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/cave.webp\" />\n\n\t\t\t\n<h2>Legendary Edges</h2>\n\n\t\t\t<h3>Followers</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Followers]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Legendary</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Each time this Edge is chosen, five followers come to fight by the hero’s side. If any are lost, others eventually take their place (how long is up to the GM and the circumstances).</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Followers must be cared for and generally want a share of whatever loot, treasure, or other rewards the hero acquires. Otherwise, they are completely dedicated to their task. They won’t throw their lives away but are willing to risk them repeatedly in his service.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Use the <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soldier]{Soldier}</strong> profile for the followers. A hero may outfit her allies as she sees fit. Use the <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Allies]{Allies}</strong> rules to give them distinctive personalities if desired.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Professional</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Professional]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Legendary, maximum die type possible in affected Trait</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character is an expert at a particular skill or attribute (his choice). This increases the Trait and its limit one step (a d12+1 becomes a d12+2, for example). This Edge may be selected once per Trait.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Expert</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Expert]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Legendary, Professional in affected Trait</p>\n\t\t\t<p>As the Professional Edge, increasing the Trait and its limit one additional step.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Master</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Legendary, Expert in affected Trait</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The character’s Wild Die increases to a d10 when rolling the selected Expert Trait.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Sidekick</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sidekick]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Wild Card, Legendary</p>\n\t\t\t<p>A character who triumphs over evil time and time again becomes an inspiration to others. Eventually, one of these young crusaders may attempt to join the hero’s epic quests.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero gains a Novice Rank sidekick. The sidekick is a Wild Card, starts each session with two Bennies, may Advance, and has abilities that complement his mentor. The player character controls his sidekick just like any other ally, though he may occasionally cause trouble by getting captured, running into danger when he’s not supposed to, and so on. The player should be prepared for this Edge to occasionally become a Hindrance!</p>\n\t\t\t<p>If the sidekick dies, he isn’t replaced unless the hero chooses this Edge again. Fortunately, heroes may always spend Bennies for their sidekicks as if they had the Common Bond Edge. Sidekicks must actually take that Edge to do the same for their mentors.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Tough As Nails</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tough As Nails]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Legendary, Vigor d8+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Your character keeps going when others fall. She can take four Wounds before she’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} (her maximum Wound penalty is still −3).</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Tougher Than Nails</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tougher Than Nails]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Legendary, Tough as Nails, Vigor d12+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The hero can take up to five Wounds before she’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated}! Her maximum Wound penalty is still −3.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Weapon Master</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Weapon Master]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Legendary, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d12+</p>\n\t\t\t<p>The warrior increases his Parry by +1 and the bonus damage die for Fighting rolls is a d8 instead of a d6 (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bonus Damage]{Bonus Damage}</strong>). He must be armed to gain these benefits, but this includes claws or other abilities that count as weapons.</p>\n\t\t\t<h3>Master of Arms</h3>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Arms]{Link to Journal Entry}</p>\t\t\t\n<p><span class=\"red-label\">Requirements:</span> Legendary, Weapon Master</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Increase the hero’s Parry an additional +1 and his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} bonus damage die is now a d10.</p>\n\t\t</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7fFMCfp7M7Bcrqlc"}}}
{"_id":"HfMiuVlyqzj6lJjZ","name":"Ranged Weapons in Melee","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Ranged Weapons in Melee</h2>\n  <p>Heroes may fire ranged weapons when engaged in melee with a few caveats:</p>\n\t\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>The attacker may only use a power or a one-handed ranged weapon (such as a thrown dagger) when in melee. \n\t\t\tHe may not fire two-handed weapons such as a bow. The TN is the defender’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} instead of \n\t\t\tShort Range as he struggles back and forth, etc.</li>\n\t\t<li>If attacking a non-adjacent target with a ranged attack <em>while</em> in melee, the attacker instantly becomes\n\t\t\t@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted %26 Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.HVSO8fN5eyLwm9JF"}}}
{"_id":"Hn8AGLkO540uPf49","name":"Shadowing","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Shadowing</h1>\n<p>On occasion, a hero may wish to follow another character—a \"mark\"—without being noticed, such as following a cultist back to a hidden temple or trailing a wealthy noble. This is not the same as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chase}—though it might lead to one if the person being followed discovers he has unwanted attention.</p>\n<p>Shadowing is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} between the Shadower's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth] skill @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by his opponent's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice] roll. If the character is shadowing by other means of conveyance than walking, he uses the lower of his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth] or the appropriate \"maneuvering\" skill (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding], @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting], etc.).</p>\n<p>Should the shadower roll at least a 4 and win the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} he manages to follow unnoticed. If his roll wins the contest but is less than a 4, the character loses his mark but isn't seen. If the hero loses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} with a 4 or better, his target is followed but detects him. If he loses both the contest and fails to score at least a 4 on his roll, then not only does he fail to keep shadowing, but his target gets a good look at him. If the shadower is discovered, he can continue to follow his mark, but it becomes an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice] versus his opponent's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth] (or maneuvering Trait if lower) to not lose the target.</p>\n<p>While in an urban enviroment, each roll covers roughly fifteen minutes of time, so it's possible several rolls may be required.</p>\n<p>Finally, it's very hard to shadow a target who moves faster than the follower. If the opponent has a higher base @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace}, the shadower suffers −2 to his Trait roll. If the mark's normal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} is more than 50% higher than the follower (round up), the penalty is −4.</p>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":4},"cf":{"id":"temp_coxsqc2solv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit","color":"#000000"}}}
