{"_id":"P9ZZ4DJIgvdXeTcM","name":"Blank","content":"<p>Something</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Something</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dlIGMPxUchlpQ3fD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"PBZ85dMt9evrqoQI","name":"Wild Attack","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Wild Attack</h2>\n  <p>Sometimes a desperate character may want to throw caution to the wind and attack with everything he’s got.</p>\n\t<p>A Wild Attack adds +2 to the character’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or \n\t\t@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) attacks and resulting damage rolls for the turn, \n\t\tbut he is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted %26 Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} until the end of his <em>next</em> turn (not this one).</p>\n\t<p>Wild Attacks can be used with multiple attacks, such as from \"@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions} or \n\t\tthe @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Sweep} Edges. \n\t\tIt can't be combined with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Desperate Attack]{Desperate Attack}.</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.CqpXp3F1m3nDMc4O"}}}
{"_id":"PIYNCn5VVskHKhzA","name":"Druid","content":"<p>Druids draw primal magic from the world itself. Druidic magic is the blood and breath of Eberron herself, granting power to those who seek to defend her and the natural order from the threats beyond. Most druids are swathed in tradition, usually initiated by a sect that teaches the secrets of this primal magic while also charging the aspirant with specific duties.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Animal Handling, Cosmology, Druidism, Healing, Notice, Religion, Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Arcane Background (Druidism)</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Command Presence, Inspire, Tactician, Master Tactician</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Explorer, Woodsman</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Beast Bond, Beast Master</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.lTQ9YEb77jPEGEvj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"POgpvAZRzTFOCnQL","name":"Fire","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Fire and Smoke Inhalation</h2>\n  <p>\n    If a flammable target is hit by fire (GM’s call), roll 1d6. On a 6, the\n    target catches fire and immediately takes the damage listed below. Very\n    flammable targets catch fire on a 4–6. Volatile targets, such as a person\n    dowsed in pitch, catch fire on a 2–6.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Fire continues to cause damage at the beginning of the victim’s turns. Roll\n    a d6 immediately after it does so. On a 6, it grows in intensity to whatever\n    maximum the GM feels is appropriate (usually 3d6 for organic beings). On a\n    1, the fire drops a level, or burns out if reduced below 1d6 damage.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    A character may also make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to put out a fire on himself,\n    others, or a flame the size of a Medium @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast} Template. This is an action,\n    plus any modifiers for intensity, tools, the flammability of the target,\n    etc.\n  </p>\n  <table>\n    <colgroup>\n      <col></col>\n      <col></col>\n    </colgroup>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <th class=\"dark\" colspan=\"2\">Fire Damage</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <th class=\"left\">Damage</th>\n        <th class=\"left\">Description</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>1d6</td>\n        <td>Spot contact, steam</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>2d6</td>\n        <td>Bonfire, burning room</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>3d6</td>\n        <td>Fireball</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>5d6</td>\n        <td>Lava</td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Armor:</strong> Armor protects normally unless the attack or\n    hazard’s description says otherwise. A hero hit with a fireball is still\n    better off if he has a breastplate than not, for example.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Flaming Weapons:</strong> Flame doesn’t cause extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} but may\n    set the target on fire if the target is flammable or volatile (as above).\n  </p>\n  <h3>Smoke Inhalation</h3>\n  <p>\n    Fires in confined areas produce deadly smoke. Each person within must make a\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Trait Summaries]{Vigor} roll every round. If the roll is failed, the character gains a level\n    of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}. A wet cloth or similar precaution adds +2 to the roll.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Death:</strong> A person @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} from smoke inhalation @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Death]{dies} in\n    a number of minutes equal to his Vigor. If someone can get to the victim\n    before then, he can be resuscitated by removing him from the hazard and\n    succeeding on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} roll at −2.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4txb7iklyvb","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.gUtNJpX9g7XrB35y"}}}
