{"_id":"ScMio1MZQo3za7EK","name":"Rest","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Rest</h1>\n<p>Those who have suffered grievous @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} might need to do so during Downtime to recover their health.</p>\n<p>Use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Healing]{natural healing} rules during the week. Any healers in the group can provide @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support}, as can other allies or hired professionals such as priests at a temple, or physicians in a nobleman’s employ.</p>\n<p>Characters may choose to rest even if they have no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}. The provides the same benefits as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Center]{Centering}, with the hero doing nothing but resting mind and body to recover from the stress of adventuring.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Downtime Activities</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Carouse]{Carouse}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Center]{Center}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Earn]{Earn}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Enchant]{Enchant}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Train]{Train}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Research]{Research}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rest]{Rest}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_lrlfbg8dda","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Downtime keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.QGoVXYrMh0YGXTUO"}}}
{"_id":"SirHRg1xoNQRipvG","name":"Priest/Acolyte","content":"<p>It’s important to understand that in Eberron, not all priests can wield divine energies. A priest provides spiritual guidance to a community and congregation and they don’t need magic to do this. An acolyte is a servant in training to a particular faith.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Common Knowledge, Cosmology, Healing, Persuasion, Religion</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Vow</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Miracles), Charismatic</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Command Presence, Fervor, Fanaticism, Inspire, Natural Leader</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Holy/Unholy Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Monster Hunter, Scholar</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Bolster, Rabble-Rouser, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Champion, Healer</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.87vhPveKV00IKJfp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"SoUOAH8w0V8jCaV4","name":"Explorer","content":"<p>Many parts of the world of Eberron either still lie unseen by humanoid eyes or have fallen into forgotten ruin, and there are those who crave wandering the breadth of the land to discover—or rediscover—them. Whether motivated by a thirst for knowledge about Eberron’s most ancient civilizations, a hunger for the long-lost secrets of tremendous arcane power, or simply a lust for gold, explorers subject themselves to tremendous danger to achieve their goals.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Arcana, Athletics, Common Knowledge, Language, Lore, Notice, Persuasion, Riding, Survival, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Fleet-Footed, Linguist, Luck, Great Luck</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Artifact Huner, Explorer, Investigator, Jack-of-all-Trades</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Danger Sense, Scavenger</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.hNHuff7kzRANSTQg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
