{"_id":"SssNtMD9HrTSaNQo","name":"Arcane Devices Creation","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n    <h3>Creation</h3>\n  <p>\n   Creating a device takes one hour per power that can be activated through it. The player must list which powers are \n    in the device and then allocate @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points} to it. \n    The device can only use the powers and Power Points allocated to it.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Power Points invested in an arcane device are lost to the inventor until\n    they’re used or recovered with <strong>Tinkering</strong>. \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Power Modifiers:</strong> A user may spend a device’s Power Points\n    as desired, including enabling any applicable\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}.\n  </p>\n  <p>Arcane devices may not be <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shorting]{Shorted}</strong>.</p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Limitations:</strong> Arcane devices may benefit from\n    <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitations}</strong>.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Activation:</strong> The creator uses his arcane skill as usual.\n    Others use whatever skill is associated with the device’s form— bows use\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, \n    knives use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), \n    and so on. If there is no other obvious skill, such as for a potion or worn item, the character rolls the\n    inventor’s arcane skill as if it were his own (he does <em>not</em> benefit\n    from any of the creator’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Edges]{Edges} or other abilities, however).\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Failure to activate the device costs one of the device's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Point},\n    and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} \n    causes the user @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Tinkering:</strong> A creator can reassign up to five \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points}\n    per action between an arcane device and her own pool. She must be in\n    physical contact with the item to do so. Characters should lend out their\n    devices very carefully!\n  </p>\n\n  <h2 class=\"example\">Arcane Device Examples</h2>\n\n  <p>\n    A powerful vizier makes an <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}</em> cloak and gives it to one\n    of his spies. He has 20 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points} and puts 5 of them into the cloak,\n    reducing his remaining pool to 15.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    When the spy wants to turn <em>invisible</em>, she rolls the vizier’s \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} skill. \n    This costs 1 less Power Point than usual because of the cloak’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}— \n    it must be worn to activate so it has a Range of Touch.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    The vizier also gives the spy the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em> power in the form of a wand\n    and invests it with 10 Power Points. The spy rolls @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} to activate the\n    wand.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    The spy suffers  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} if she rolls \n    a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} activating either\n    device.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Once the cloak or wand is out of energy, the vizier can recover the Power\n    Points he invested in it normally.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Meanwhile, Ezren the wizard makes an “oil of sharpness” for Valeros the\n    fighter. When rubbed on a sword it activates the \n    <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em> power. Ezren\n    invests four Power Points into it. The pair soon find themselves in battle\n    with the undead. Valeros rubs the oil on the blade and rolls Ezren's\n    Spellcasting. The roll fails, which drains the oil of one Power Point. Next\n    turn, Valeros tries again, getting a raise and granting the sword +4 damage.\n    <em>Smite</em> normally costs 2 Power Points but Ezren's Trapping has\n    the Range Limitation so it only costs 1 point for each application. See\n    <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trappings}</strong>.\n  </p>\n    <p>@Compendium[@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Arcane Devices]{See full Arcane Devices Section here}</p>\n    \n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_inkjjer1fuj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/Powers keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.bjkJpuTPogJaOlyU"}}}
{"_id":"SwH2t1Ljg0gDfBEi","name":"Boarding","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Boarding</h1>\n<p>If one ship wants to board another, it must maneuver itself to be on the same initiative card as its foe and perform a successful Force maneuver.</p>\n<p>If successful, the boarders make an immediate group Throwing roll for the crew. Success means the target is grappled and drawn close enough to board. An opponent’s crew can attempt to sever the grapples with an opposed Fighting roll with at least an equal amount of crew. The roll should be modified as follows:</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\" style=\"width:50%\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Boarding Modifiers</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Mod</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Circumstance</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>Enemy is stationary</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–1</td>\n<td>If the enemy ship is faster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>If the enemy ship is twice as fast</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>If the boarders ship is faster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>If the boarders ship is twice as fast</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Boarders have a larger crew</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>Boarders have a smaller crew</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>Rough weather</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–4</td>\n<td>Full-blown storm</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Boarding]{Boarding}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranks of Archers]{Ranks of Archers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Sinking]{Sinking}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_6g48t5q06rw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"T68p9AsAmAUcmoyV","name":"Research","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Research</h1>\n<p>A character can spend her Downtime developing or learning new powers. This doesn’t permanently give her a power, but allows her to use any spell or miracle from her Available Powers list and of her Rank or lower for one entire encounter.</p>\n<p>The character may also temporarily change the Trapping of a power she already has for one encounter—turning a fireball into an ice blast, for example.</p>\n<p>The spell is cast at a −2 penalty, but is otherwise treated just like one of the caster’s regular powers. This can be particularly useful if the mage or priest must prepare to face a threat with a particular weakness.</p>\n<p>Finally, Research can also be used to reveal deep information about a particular subject. No Trait roll is required. The GM decides just how much the investigator can learn in a week given the topic, the location, and resources at hand.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Downtime Activities</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Carouse]{Carouse}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Center]{Center}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Earn]{Earn}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Enchant]{Enchant}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Train]{Train}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Research]{Research}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rest]{Rest}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_lrlfbg8dda","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Downtime keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"TNABCrLFIrh8HKbQ","name":"Poison","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Poison</h2>\n  <p>\n    The bane of adventurers across all of Eberron can be delivered by the smallest of foes — poison!\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    When an adventurer is poisoned, he must make an immediate @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Trait Summaries]{Vigor} roll minus\n    the Strength of the poison (if listed). Failure causes the effects listed\n    below:\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      <strong>Knockout:</strong> The victim is knocked out (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} and\n      unconscious) for 2d6 hours (twice that with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure}).\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <strong>Lethal:</strong> The victim is Stunned, takes a Wound (two with a  Critical Failure), and perishes in 2d6 rounds.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <strong>Mild:</strong> The victim suffers Fatigue, or Exhaustion with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure}. This cannot cause Incapacitation.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <strong>Paralyzing:</strong> The victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}Stunned} and cannot attempt to recover for d4+1 rounds (double that with a Critical Failure).\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>\n    These are basic and simplified poison effects that can be altered as needed\n    to suit specific creatures or hazards. A particularly deadly venomous snake,\n    for example, might still cause Exhaustion to those who resist its effects,\n    or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.\n  </p>\n  <div>\n    <img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/oasis.webp\" />\n  </div>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Treatment:</strong> A character may make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} roll minus the\n    strength of the poison (if any modifier is listed) to stop its effects. If\n    successful, the victim’s life is saved and the poison no longer has any ill\n    effects — paralyzed victims can move and those rendered unconscious wake.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Each character may only attempt one Healing roll per incident to cure the\n    poison, but another character with Healing may try as well.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4txb7iklyvb","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.szDZYOgjOJaEBMX9"}}}
{"_id":"TVSJYegGSdnAeW2w","name":"Destined Bloodline","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Destined</h1>\n<p>The character is destined for great things. She gains one additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} per session.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>★ Advanced Form: </strong>The hero starts with two extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} per session.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w2j6cd7pbcs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.4. Bloodlines","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"Th4Rj2Aw90AHlewl","name":"3 New Size Table","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n\t<table>\n\t\t<colgroup>\n\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t</colgroup>\n\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t\tSize Table\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Use the examples below to estimate the Size of creatures and vehicles not included in the Bestiary.  Mass is usually enough to determine its Size and Toughness bonus, but account for overall dimensions as makes sense.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Tiny creatures have a Strength score of 1. They can’t make a Strength roll (and therefore can’t Ace or get bonus damage). They can damage creatures with a Toughness of 1, but can only harm Small or larger beings if they swarm together (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms}</strong>).</p>\n\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\tSize /<br />Toughness<br />Bonus\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\tTypical<br />Strength<br />Range\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\tScale<br />Modifier\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\tTypical<br />Height /<br />Length<br />Up to…\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\tMass<br />Up to…\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"sub-heading\">\n\t\t\t\t\tExample<br />Creatures\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr></tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<th class=\"bar-heading\" style=\"background-color:var(--color-size-tiny)\" colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t\t <span>Tiny</span>\n\t\t\t\t</th>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td class=\"centered\">\n\t\t\t\t\t−4\n\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td class=\"centered\">\n\t\t\t\t\t1\n\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td class=\"centered\">\n\t\t\t\t\t−6\n\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td class