{"_id":"b2H7h9tS03be2HxU","name":"Cover and Obstacles","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Cover and Obstacles</h2>\n  <p>Melee and ranged attacks suffer a penalty when attempting to hit a target behind @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover %26 Obstacles]{Cover}. \n\t\tPenalties only apply to the targeted area— a skeleton standing behind a knee-high wall doesn't get Light Cover, \n\t\tbut he does if a quarter of his body is protected by a door frame.\n\t</p>\n\t\n\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t<colgroup>\n\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t\t<col></col>\n\t\t\t</colgroup>\n\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\tCover Penalties\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tPenalty\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tCover\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t−2\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<strong>Light Cover:</strong> A quarter of the target is obscured.\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t−4\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<strong>Medium Cover:</strong> Half the target is obscured, or target is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}.\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t−6\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<strong>Heavy Cover:</strong> Three-quarters of the target is obscured.\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t−8\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<strong>Near Total Cover:</strong> The target is hidden or barely visible.\n\t\t\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t</table>\n\n  <h3>Obstacles</h3>\n\t<p>Sometimes characters have sufficient power to attack their foes <em>through</em> obstacles. \n\t\t(See <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Breaking Things}</strong> to actually destroy intervening obstacles.)</p>\n\t<p>When this happens, add an Armor bonus equal to half the obstacle's Hardness to the target beyond (round up if necessary).</p>\n\t<p>If the obstacle is a person or creature, subtract its Toughness from the attack instead.</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.t7bveP3o2a3qz6sB"}}}
{"_id":"bCBranKvgOoaQUSN","name":"Ship Fire","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Ship Fire</h1>\n<p>Fires are very dangerous on ships and kill far more men than cannon shots usually account for. When a ship suffers a Chassis hit, it’s actually been hit in the hull somewhere. The shot itself can start a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fire]{fire}, or it might knock over necessary lanterns and candles.</p>\n<p>Roll 1d6 at the beginning of each round for each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fire]{fire} to see what effect it has on the ship.</p>\n<table class=\"table value=table\" style=\"width:70%\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Fire Table</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">[[/r 1d6]]</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Result</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fire]{Fire} burns out.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2-4</td>\n<td>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fire]{fire} continues to burn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fire]{fire} causes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fire]{fire} spreads, making two fires.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Fighting Fires:</strong> Crews can put out fires, but this takes away from their other duties to do so.</p>\n<p>A team equal to half the ship’s base @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} (ignore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{Armor} and magical bonuses) is required. The team must assemble one round, and the next may make a group @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} roll at –2 for one fire. With a success, the team extinguishes the fire.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Boarding]{Boarding}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranks of Archers]{Ranks of Archers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Sinking]{Sinking}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6g48t5q06rw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"bI5nadXmo74Ob9TB","name":"No Power Points","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>No Power Points</h2>\n<p>Instead of using @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, characters with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Backgrounds} simply choose the power they want to activate and make an arcane skill roll. The penalty to the roll is the power’s total cost in Power Points (base cost plus all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}), divided by 2. Round up.</p>\n<p>Casting <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Protection]{protection}</em> (1 point) with More Armor (+1) and the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hinder or Hurry (+1)]{Hurry} modifier (+1), for example, has a cost of 3 Power Points. Half rounded up is 2.</p>\n<p>Success means the power activates as usual. A raise grants any additional bonuses stated in its description.</p>\n<p>Failure means all current powers are canceled and the caster is Shaken. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} results in <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Activation]{Backlash}</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Maintaining Powers:</strong> Characters can main­tain those powers that allow it as long as desired, but each one maintained inflicts a −1 to all further arcane skill rolls.</p>\n<p><strong>Power Preparation: </strong>A caster may prepare powers by concentrating for an entire round (no move­ment or other actions and must not be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken or Stunned}). If successful, he ignores 2 points of penalties on all powers cast on his next turn. If he does not enact any powers on his next turn, the preparation is lost.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rv4q29jrhjs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.JNvoMEDDC0pVFhlT"}}}
{"_id":"bULwbj6QAP1JwYVy","name":"Races","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"header\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p>Races</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p><cite>Savage Eberron</cite> has the following races that are available for play as player characters. All races are balanced out to +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Making Races]{racial abilities} instead of the usual +2.</p>\n<h2>Races</h2>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bugbear]{Bugbear}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Changeling]{Changeling}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarf}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elf}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gnome]{Gnome}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Goblin]{Goblin}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-elf]{Half-elf}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-orc]{Half-orc}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Halfling]{Halfling}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hobgoblin]{Hobgoblin}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orc}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{Shifter}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Warforged]{Warforged}</h3>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Exotic Races</h2>\n<p>The following races are far more exotic and rare in Eberron. These require DM approval for particular campaigns.</p>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf, Drow]{Elf, Drow}: Xen'drik</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Eneko]{Eneko}: Sarlona</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-giant]{Half-giant}: Sarlona and Xen'drik</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar}: Sarlona, Sharn and small other pockets</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Tiefling]{Tiefling}: Generally rare</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"c182hF1t3jnY2wMK","name":"Reload","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Reload</h2>\n  <p>A character can ready and fire a bow every action— see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reloading]{Reloading}. Heavy crossbows and black powder muskets are slower to reload. The number after the Reload keyword is how many actions of reloading it takes before a weapon can be fired again.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reloading]{See Reloading here}</p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.yh56XqmBUZvNhGWX"}}}
{"_id":"cEvKv6WkzEJTSQm6","name":"Readying Weapons","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Readying Weapons</h2>\n  <p>Characters may “ready” up to two items per turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Actions]{free action}. Readying means drawing, holstering, or \n\t\totherwise moving an item into or out of an easy-to-reach location.</p>\n\t<p>Each additional item readied is an action, as is recovering an item from a difficult location like an ankle sheath, off the floor after being disarmed, \n\t\tor other exten­uating circumstances.</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.IEzBFdW4EluU0BkS"}}}
{"_id":"cFaxcMKsRDvXe9s7","name":"Arcane Bloodline","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Arcane</h1>\n<p>The sorcerer forms a magical bond with a creature or an object. Use the rules for the wizard’s Arcane Bond.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>★ Advanced Form: </strong>The sorcerer’s connection to magic is incredibly strong. She gets a free reroll on any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w2j6cd7pbcs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.4. Bloodlines","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"cFuqh0bBmjHQlwYq","name":"The Countdown","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Underlined Header</h2>\n  <p>\n    Once the cards are dealt, the Game Master starts the round by counting down\n    from Ace down to Two, with each group resolving its actions when its card\n    comes up.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Ties:</strong> Ties are resolved by suit order: Spades ♠ are first,\n    then Hearts <span class=\"red\">♥</span>, Diamonds <span class=\"red\">♦</span>,\n    and Clubs ♣. That’s reverse alphabetical order as used in many common card\n    games.\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><span class=\"list-heading\">Jokers:</span> Characters (or groups) with a Joker act whenever they\n      want in the round, even interrupting another’s action. They also add +2 to\n      all Trait and damage rolls this round!\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Combat]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aeejh0xnzv6","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Combat keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.FGOaSBSLNm4iPuo4"}}}
{"_id":"cbvyMUcqPSNAE5Hf","name":"Knowledge Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Knowledge Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Knowledge, literacy, history, revealing secrets, wisdom</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> Aureon, Onatar, The Traveler, The Udying Court</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{Locate}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{Magic Mark}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{Mind Link}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{Mind Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Wipe]{Mind Wipe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Travel]{Planar Travel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bt6afhtf6wi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Domains","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"ccnpocDWh1OSxnxO","name":"Elemental","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>The weapon causes damage with an energy Trapping—acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic (chosen by creator).</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 2,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> Damaging power with the appropiate energy trapping.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"crcf6QNug2jaymbT","name":"Hunger","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Hunger</h2>\n  <p>\n    Average-size humans need about 1,500 calories of reasonably nutritious food\n    per day to avoid the effects of hunger. If sufficient sustenance isn’t\n    available, a character begins to suffer and die.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    After 24 hours without enough food, the victim must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Trait Summaries]{Vigor} roll.\n    Failure means he gains a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} level.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    See the <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}</strong> skill when a character wants to\n    hunt or scrounge for food from the local environment.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Death:</strong> An @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitated} character @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Death]{dies} from hunger 3d6 hours later.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Recovery:</strong> The victim must have at least a half day’s food to recover.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4txb7iklyvb","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RD78IoXFwMACv93d"}}}
{"_id":"cuk99xgVS3uKgIyX","name":"Adamantine","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2 class=\"wide\">Adamantine</h2>\n<p>Mined from rocks that fell from the heavens, adamantine adds +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} to any melee weapon or ranged weapon ammunition made of its metal. This stacks with the bonus from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Masterwork]{masterwork} items. Adamantine weapons cost an additional 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p>Adamantine armor is harder to pierce than that made from other materials. It ignores up to 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP}. Armor made from this material costs an extra 3,000 gp per point of armor bonus.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Materials]{See Special Materials here}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"dBwZH7VbkIFEFQvK","name":"Heavy Weapon (HW)","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Heavy Weapon</h2>\n  <p>The weapon can affect vehicles or other devices with <strong>Heavy Armor</strong> (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Vehicles]{Vehicles}). This is not to be confused with categories of personal armor— such as heavy armor or shields.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.lZYWrTGhcgUPvLHN"}}}
{"_id":"dKBN19tgHdX933C7","name":"Rate of Fire","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Rate of Fire</h2>\n  <p> Rate of Fire is how many shots (Shooting\n    dice) a ranged weapon can fire in one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{action}. A longbow with a RoF of 1, for\n    example, can fire one shot per action. For weapons with a Rate of Fire 2 or\n    more, declare how many shots you are firing. Then roll that number of\n    Shooting dice and assign them in whatever order you like to the chosen\n    targets.\n  </p>\n   <p>\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll their Shooting dice plus a single Wild Die, which can\n    <em>replace</em> any one Shooting die if desired.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.cRqaxVmaAI6dIqhj"}}}
{"_id":"dWSXyaErNCh2P8Km","name":"Setting Edges","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Setting Edges</h1>\n<p>Below is a list of Edges common to most settings. You’ll find new Edges designed for your game world in official <em>Savage Worlds</em> books as well.</p>\n<p>The Edges are grouped by type to help during character creation. You’ll find a summary below.</p>\n<p>Unless an Edge specifically says otherwise, it may only be selected once.</p>\n<p>The core base Edges are those presented in <em>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</em> rather than the <em>Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</em>.</p>\n<h3>Altered Edges in Savage Eberron from Savage Pathfinder</h3>\n<p>The following <em>Savage Worlds</em> Edges have been altered for <em>Savage Eberron</em>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"red-text\">Arcane Background (Magic), Bard Fighter, Wizard, Pathfinder Chronicler, Pathfinder Chronicler II, Pathfinder Chronicler III</span></p>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<p>Below each Edge is the minimum Rank (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}) required to take it along with any other prerequisites such as attributes, skills, or other Edges.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Class Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]{Artificer}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6, Arcana d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Armor Restriction (Medium)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant Magic Item]{Enchant Magic Item}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Homunculus]{Homunculus}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Infuse Item]{Infuse Item}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Artificer)]{Favored Powers (Artificer)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Artificer</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the artificer may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Artifice]{Master of Artifice}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Artificer</td>\n<td>Spend up to 3 Power Points and@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} to create a device that replicates another power.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artifice Mastery]{Artifice Mastery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Artificer</td>\n<td>The artificer may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Barbarian]{Barbarian}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d6, Vi d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast]{Fast}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rage]{Rage}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Powerful Blow]{Powerful Blow}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Barbarian</td>\n<td>Wild Attacks cause +4 damage instead of +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Intimidating Glare]{Intimidating Glare}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Barbarian</td>\n<td>The barbarian may make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll as a free action when dealt a Jack or better in combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strength Surge]{Strength Surge}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Barbarian</td>\n<td>The hero’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} increases two die types when raging.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard]{Bard}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, Performance d4</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard Armor Interference (Light)]{Armor Interference (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lore Keeper]{Lore Keeper}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sharp Tongued]{Sharp Tongued}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inspire Heroics]{Inspire Heroics}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Bard</td>\n<td>Once per encounter, as a limited free action, the bard gets five Inspiration tokens he can give to his allies for rerolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Countersong]{Countersong}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Bard</td>\n<td>Allies within 5” get a free reroll when resisting or recovering from enemy spell effects.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dirge of Doom]{Dirge of Doom}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Bard</td>\n<td>Enemy Wild Cards within 10” subtract 2 from their totals when spending a Benny.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Cleric]{Cleric}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, Religion d4</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Destroy Undead]{Destroy Undead}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Cleric</td>\n<td>Spend 2 Power Points to create a wave of energy in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. All undead within must make a Spirit roll or take a Wound.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Cleric)]{Favored Powers (Cleric)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Cleric</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the cleric may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>healing</em>, <em>sanctuary</em>, or <em>smite</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Divine Mastery]{Divine Mastery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Cleric</td>\n<td>The cleric may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid]{Druid}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, Animal Handling d4, Survival d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid Armor Interference (Light)]{Armor Interference (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Bond]{Nature Bond}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Sense]{Nature Sense}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wild Shape]{Wild Shape}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Druid</td>\n<td>The druid gains shape change. Duration is one hour and she casts as if one Rank higher than usual.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Druid)]{Favored Powers (Druid)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Druid</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the druid may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>entangle</em>, <em>smite</em>, or <em>protection</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Mastery]{Nature Mastery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Druid</td>\n<td>The druid may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fighter]{Fighter}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Training]{Combat Training}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Deadly Blow]{Deadly Blow}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fighter</td>\n<td>The fighter adds +1 to all his damaging attacks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Martial Flexibility]{Improved Martial Flexibility}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Fighter</td>\n<td>The fighter may now choose two Combat Edges per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Prowess]{Martial Prowess}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Fighter</td>\n<td>The fighter gets a free reroll on any failed Fighting roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monk]{Monk}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Ag d6, Sp d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monk Armor Restriction (Light)]{Armor Restriction (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Discipline]{Martial Discipline}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mobility]{Mobility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Stunning Fist]{Stunning Fist}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Unarmed Strike]{Unarmed Strike}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Monk)]{Mystic Powers (Monk)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Monk</td>\n<td>The monk has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>boost Trait</em> (Agility, Athletics, Fighting, or Stealth), <em>deflection</em>, <em>smite</em>, and <em>speed</em>. All are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Ki]{Great Ki}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Monk</td>\n<td>The monk's Mystic Powers now includes <em>boost Trait</em> (<em>Strength</em>), <em>protection</em>, <em>speed</em>, <em>wall walker</em>, <em>warrior's gift</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wholeness of Body]{Wholeness of Body}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Monk</td>\n<td>The monk may spend 2 Power Points to make a Soak roll. This does not count as spending a Benny.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Paladin]{Paladin}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, St d6, Vow</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aura of Courage]{Aura of Courage}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Code of Honor]{Code of Honor}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Detect Evil (or Good)]{Detect Evil (or Good)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Smite Evil (or Good)]{Smite Evil (or Good)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Paladin)]{Mystic Powers (Paladin)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Paladin</td>\n<td>The paladin has 10 dedicated Power Points she can use to cast <em>boost Trait </em>(Fighting, Strength, Vigor), <em>healing</em>, <em>relief</em>, <em>smite</em>. All but healing and relief are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mercy]{Mercy}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Paladin</td>\n<td>The paladin can remove Distracted, Vulnerable, or Shaken statuses to an ally within Range of Spirit.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mount]{Mount}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Paladin</td>\n<td>The hero gains a loyal WC light or heavy horse.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ranger]{Ranger}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shooting d6, Survival d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ranger Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Armor Restriction (Medium)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Enemy]{Favored Enemy}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Terrain]{Favored Terrain}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wilderness Stride (Ranger)]{Wilderness Stride (Ranger)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Quarry]{Quarry}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Ranger</td>\n<td>The ranger chooses an additional enemy and terrain type for his Favored Enemy and Favored Terrain abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Ranger)]{Mystic Powers (Ranger)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Ranger</td>\n<td>The ranger has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>beast friend</em>, <em>boost Trait</em> (Athletics, Fighting, Shooting), <em>entangle</em>, <em>warrior's gift</em>. All but entangle are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Hunter]{Master Hunter}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Ranger</td>\n<td>The hunter adds an additional d6 damage when making a successful Athletics (throwing), Fighting, or Shooting attack against their Favored Enemy.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue]{Rogue}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Ag d6, Notice d6, Stealth d6, Thievery d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Armor Restriction (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skill Monkey]{Skill Monkey}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Rogue</td>\n<td>The rogue gets a chance to detect traps before springing them. She also ignores up to two points of penalties when disarming them with Thievery.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Uncanny Reflexes]{Uncanny Reflexes}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Rogue</td>\n<td>The rogue ignores the usual –2 Agility penalty to Evasion attempts, and may attempt to Evade any area effect that doesn't usually allow it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Opportunist]{Opportunist}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Rogue</td>\n<td>The rogue gets a free attack against a foe who Withdraws from Melee, even if they have Extraction. If they don't have Extraction, they count as Vulnerable to her.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer]{Sorcerer}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6, Sp d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)]{Armor Interference (Cloth)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bloodline]{Bloodline}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Sorcerer)]{Favored Powers (Sorcerer)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sorcerer</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the sorcerer may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>bolt</em>, <em>elemental manipulation</em>, or <em>protection</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcery Mastery]{Sorcery Mastery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sorcerer</td>\n<td>The sorcerer may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Advanced Bloodline]{Advanced Bloodline}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Sorcerer</td>\n<td>The sorcerer gains his bloodline's advanced ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard]{Wizard}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6, Arcana d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard Armor Interference (Cloth)]{Armor Interference (Cloth)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Schools]{Schools}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spellbooks]{Spellbooks}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Bond]{Arcane Bond}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Wizard</td>\n<td>The wizards forms an intense magical bond with an object or creature.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Mastery]{Arcane Mastery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Wizard</td>\n<td>The wizard may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Inspiration]{Eldritch Inspiration}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Wizard</td>\n<td>The wizard can spend a Benny to cast any power of his Rank or lower at a –2 penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Dragonmarked Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Detection]{Mark of Detection}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Half-elf</td>\n<td>Mark of Detection with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{augury}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait}</em> (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, and any \"knowledge\" based skill only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em> (no Identify), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em> (can only locate traps), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{mind reading}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Finding]{Mark of Finding}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human, Half-orc, or Orc</td>\n<td>Mark of Finding with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{analyze foe}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana} </em>(Identify only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{darksight}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight} </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight} </em>have the range of touch only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Handling]{Mark of Handling}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Handling with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (animals only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em> (animals only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language} </em>(Beasts for the power only), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em><em> </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language} </em>have the range of touch only.<em><br /></em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Healing]{Mark of Healing}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Halfling</td>\n<td>Mark of Healing with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{accelerate healing}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} </em>(@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{survival}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> (not Mass Healing), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{resurrection}</em>. All powers are touch only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Hospitality]{Mark of Hospitality}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Halfling</td>\n<td>Mark of Hospitality with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em> (humanoids only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{plane shift}</em> (Extra-dimensional space for the power only), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{slumber}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Making]{Mark of Making}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Making with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure item}</em> (not including Create Food and Water), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em> (not including Alignment Sense), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{object reading}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</em> has a ranch of touch only.<em><br /></em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Passage]{Mark of Passage}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Passage with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{leaping}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em> (mount only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em> (not including Teleport Foe). All powers (except <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em>) have a range of touch only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Scribing]{Mark of Scribing}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Gnome</td>\n<td>Mark of Scribing with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em> (spoken or written words trapping only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{magic mark}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{message}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{secret writing}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Sentinel]{Mark of Sentinel}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Sentinel with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em>,  <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,  <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{gift of battle}</em>,  <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>. All powers have the  range of touch only.<em><br /></em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Shadow]{Mark of Shadow}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Elf</td>\n<td>Mark of Shadow with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em> (including Epic Powers), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em> (including Duration), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise} </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em> are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Storm]{Mark of Storm}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Half-elf</td>\n<td>Mark of Storm with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}</em> (air and water trapping only, not including Damage or Deadly), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em> (air and water trapping only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em> (air and water trappings only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis} </em>(air and water trappings only). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Warding]{Mark of Warding}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Dwarf</td>\n<td>Mark of Warding with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em> (including Epic Powers), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier} </em>(not including Damage), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{glyph}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{lock/unlock}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{sentry}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Prestige Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer]{Arcane Archer}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB or Mp, Shooting d8</td>\n<td><strong>Enhance:</strong> arrows for +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} and damage. <strong>Trapping:</strong> Give the arrow and enviromental @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trappings]{Trapping}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer II]{Arcane Archer II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, AA</td>\n<td><strong>Phase Arrow:</strong> Empower an arrow to pass through physical barriers. <strong>Hail of Arrows: </strong>split it into many arrows that covers an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer III]{Arcane Archer III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, AA II</td>\n<td><strong>Imbue:</strong> an arrow with an area of effect power once per turn. <strong>Death Arrow:</strong> fired once per day (victim who is Shaken or Wounded must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} roll or die).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster]{Arcane Trickster}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB or MP, Sneak Attack, Thievery d8</td>\n<td><strong>Ranged Legerdemain:</strong> Can use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} at Range of 5\" at –2 penalty. <strong>Impromptu Attack:</strong> Once per encounter, trickster may use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack} without @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster II]{Arcane Trickster II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AT</td>\n<td><strong>Invisible Thief:</strong> Once per day, automatically cast invisibility for 1 Power Point and an automatic raise (no roll).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster III]{Arcane Trickster III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, AT II</td>\n<td><strong>Surprise Spells:</strong> The hero's spells benefit from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin]{Assassin}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sneak Attack</td>\n<td><strong>Hide in Plain Sight:</strong> –4 to be seen if assassin doesn't move. <strong>Resistance to Poison:</strong> +4 to resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Poison]{Poison}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin II]{Assassin II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Assassin</td>\n<td><strong>Infiltration Expertise:</strong> The assassin can spend seven days creating an unfailing identity for herself. <strong>Swift Death:</strong> Once per day, the killer gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on a foe of her choice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin III]{Assassin III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Assassin II</td>\n<td><strong>Death Attack:</strong> If assassin attacks with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} and causes at least one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, the victim must make @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} roll or die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple]{Dragon Disciple}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB or MP, Arcana d6</td>\n<td><strong>Breath Attack:</strong> 3d6 damage plus @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trappings]{Trapping} effects, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template}, once per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple II]{Dragon Disciple II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, DD</td>\n<td><strong>Wings:</strong> The character grows wings for @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight} (Pace 8).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple III]{Dragon Disciple III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, DD II</td>\n<td><strong>Dragon Form:</strong> Twice per day the dragon disciple may take the form of a dragon of her bloodline.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist]{Duelist}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Ag d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td><strong>Surgical Strike:</strong> +2 damage with certain weapons. <strong>Parry:</strong> Duelist may Defend if she hasn't acted yet for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonus +6.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist II]{Duelist II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Deulist</td>\n<td><strong>Crippling Strike:</strong> Reduce foe's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} by 2 until healed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist III]{Duelist III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Duelist II</td>\n<td><strong>Deflect Arrows:</strong> –2 to be hit with physical ranged attacks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight]{Eldritch Knight}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB or MP, Fighting d8</td>\n<td><strong>Eldritch Recharge:</strong> Regain a Power Point with raise on an attack or arcane skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight II]{Eldritch Knight II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, EK</td>\n<td><strong>Eldritch Strike:</strong> to add +2 to the attack total. Spend 2 Power Points after making an attack to add +2 to the attack total.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight III]{Eldritch Knight III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, EK II</td>\n<td><strong>Imp. Eldritch Strike:</strong> Spend 2 Power Points after making a successful attack to increase the attack's damage by +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extreme Explorer]{Extreme Explorer}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Survival d6, See text</td>\n<td><strong>Pathfinding:</strong> Increase travel speed by 10%, possibly avoid Enemy encounters.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extreme Explorer II]{Extreme Explorer II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, EE</td>\n<td><strong>Epic Tales:</strong> Tell a tale to grant the party a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} while resting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extreme Explorer III]{Extreme Explorer III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, EE II</td>\n<td><strong>Call Down the Legends:</strong> Summon 5 Shades of heroes for one hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster]{Loremaster}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, See text</td>\n<td><strong>Lore:</strong> Free reroll on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster II]{Loremaster II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, LM</td>\n<td><strong>Secret:</strong> Gain an ability from any core Class Edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster III]{Loremaster III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, LM II</td>\n<td><strong>Greater Lore:</strong> Gain any 2 new powers available in the campaign.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"highlighted\">\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge]{Mystic Theurge}</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, ABs, See text</td>\n<td><strong>Combined Spells: </strong>Cast two spells at once, rolling an arcane skill for each along with the Wild Die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge II]{Mystic Theurge II}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, MT</td>\n<td><strong>Spell Synergy: </strong>Reduce cost of each spell when using Combined Spells ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge III]{Mystic Theurge III}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, MT II</td>\n<td><strong>Spell Synthesis: </strong>When the theurge uses her Combined Spells ability she reduces the cost of each spell by one Power Point (to a minimum of 1).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Racial Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adamantine Body]{Adamantine Body}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Warforged</td>\n<td>Start with +4 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{Armor}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bladedancer]{Bladedancer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Elf, A d8, Fighting d8, Two-Weapon Fighting</td>\n<td>Make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{run} roll, and get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack at everything in his path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extra Shifter Ability]{Extra Shifter Ability}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shifter</td>\n<td>Gains one additional shifting ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healing Factor]{Healing Factor}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shifter, V d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} on any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} when ending shifting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Overload Metabolism]{Overload Metaolism}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Warforged, A d8, Str d8</td>\n<td>Once per session make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. two on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. Reduce @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Agility} one die type for 10 minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Primal Fury]{Primal Fury}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Half-orc or Orc, Berserk</td>\n<td>No penalty to end rage, and the hero will not hit an ally on a Critical Failure with her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psicrystal]{Psicyrstal}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Kalashtar, SB (Psionics), Sm d8</td>\n<td>Allows the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar} to have a fragment of thier personality placed into a srystalline construct with some abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psiforged Body]{Psiforged Body}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Warforged, AB (Psionics)</td>\n<td>This adds 5 Powers Points for a Psionic Warforged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reactive Shifting]{Reactive Shifting}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shifter, Quick</td>\n<td>Shifters can shift as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} even when not on their turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Running Throw]{Running Throw}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Str d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>The hero moves at least half their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} and throws a weapon may increase their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{range} by 2/4/8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scamper]{Scamper}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Halfling, A d8</td>\n<td>Opponents larger than the hero subtract 1 from their attack rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Scamper]{Improved Scamper}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Scamper</td>\n<td>Opponents get no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ganging Up]{gang up} on the hero.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shieldwall]{Shieldwall}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Hobogoblin, Block</td>\n<td>The hero can add his shield modifier to an adjacent ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shifter Stamina]{Shifter Stamina}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shifter</td>\n<td>The adventurer is immune to nonlethal damage and the effects of fatigue while they are shifted.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sunder]{Sunder}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Dwarf</td>\n<td>The adventurer ignores 1 point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 2 points on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sunder]{Improved Sunder}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sunder</td>\n<td>The hero ignores 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 4 points on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.War Cry]{War Cry}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":20}}}
{"_id":"dXw2IWoxeU2mdhEa","name":"Currency","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Currency</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p><cite>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</cite> uses a gold standard for trade across Eberron. In general, commerce relies on four precious metals, coined throughout the continents. Some traders accept gemstones when bargaining.</p>\n<p>Naturally, trade also occurs via bartering, although most characters (and merchants!) prefer coins when buying or selling wares. Costs default to gold pieces (gp) on Gear tables unless otherwise noted.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"5\">Coins &amp; exchange value</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Coin</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">CP</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">SP</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">GP</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">PP</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Copper (cp)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1/10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1/100</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1/1,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Silver (sp)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1/10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1/100</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gold (gp)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">100</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1/10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Platinum (pp)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1,000</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">100</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V1XoYfTcK7Tm5STt"}}}
{"_id":"dunAw0B1Slwf1514","name":"Bugbear","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Bugbear</h1>\n<p>The goblinoid species—goblins, hobgoblins, and bugbears—were once the dominant civilization in Khorvaire, with the goblinoid Empire of Dhakaan ruling the continent for thousands ofyears. It was crippled by a long conflict with the daelkyr and their aberrant armies; even though the daelkyr were defeated, the seeds of madness took root in the empire and tore it apart. Today there are four primary goblinoid cultures in Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>Known as <em>guul'dar</em>, or \"strong people\", among the <em>dar</em> or goblin races. <em>Guul'dar</em> are born for battle and mayhem being fierce and aggressive. Surviving by raiding and hunting, they bully the weak and despite being bossed around. In Darguun they living in tribes in the Marguul mountains, or in the <em>ghaal'dur </em>tribes ruling Darguun often serving as shock troops being ruled by the hobgoblins with superior numbers and intellect.</p>\n<h3>The Marguul</h3>\n<p>The Marguul bugbears threw off the yoke of the <em>ghaal'dar</em> long ago, seizing territory in the Seawall Mountains in the south of Darguun. They are infamous raiders, and while they have brokered a truce with the Ghaal'dar, anyone venturing into the Seawall Mountains had best travel with a Marguul guide.</p>\n<p>As a Marguul bugbear, you are savage and proud of it. The Marguul worship the Mockery and believe in victory by any means necessary: there is no such thing as honor on the battlefield. It's certainly an unusual choice for a player character, but if you've taken a liking to a particular group of the small folk, you could be a powerful ally.</p>\n<h3>The Heirs of Dhakaan</h3>\n<p>Though the Dhakaani Empire defeated the alien daelkyr, the war left seeds ofcorruption strewn throughout the empire. As Dhakaan began to fall, a number of generals and governors gathered their forces and retreated into shelters deep within the earth, determined to preserve their civilization until the Empire could finally be restored. After thousands of years, their descendants have finally emerged, competing among themselves to determine which leader deserves the imperial crown. Once this is settled, they will turn to the conquest of Darguun and Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>The Dhakaani are far fewer in number than the <em>ghaal'dar</em>; they had to carefully limit their population in the underground vaults they've dwelled in for the past age. However, they have held onto the martial discipline and techniques that allowed their ancestors to dominate the continent. Their weaponsmiths are superior even to the artificers of House Cannith, and they are experts in the working of adamantine and other exotic metals. Anyone who presumes to look down upon goblinoids should be surprised by the skills of the Dhakaani.</p>\n<p>The Heirs of Dhakaan are an agnostic society and don't have clerics, paladins, or druids. Their focus is on martial excellence, and their spiritual leaders are bards, who tell tales of past glory. Among the Dhakaan, goblinoids work together. Hobgoblins are the strategists and commanders, typically having the skills of fighters, bards, or rangers. Bugbears cultivate a focused battle rage and are typically barbarians. Goblins are largely artisans and laborers, but exceptional goblins join the khesh'dar (\"silent folk\"), learning the skills of rogues, monks, or rangers. The khesh'dar spread agents across the Five Nations, and one can never know when a city goblin might turn out to be an assassin.</p>\n<p>As an adventurer from a Dhakaani clan, consider why are you working with the other player characters? Are you a scout gathering information? Are you searching for allies to defeat a rival clan, or to support your own unlikely bid for the Imperial throne? Are you an exile? If so, do you hope to regain your position, or have you abandoned your ties to the Dhakaani?</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bloodthirsty]{Bloodthirsty}:</strong> Bugbears are very brutal killers and like to inflict pain. </li>\n<li><strong>Brute Strength:</strong> Bugbears are naturally strong, and start with a d6 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} instead of a d4. This increases their maximum @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}:</strong> Bugbear eyes are accustomed to the dark of Khyber. Darkvision ignores up to –4 penalties for all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} up to 10\" away. Beyond 10\" they ignore up to –2 penalties. Such vision is in black and white (monchrome) only.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Bugbears start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Goblin} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong>Large Size: </strong>Bugbears average about seven to eight feet tall, increasing their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}) by 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Long-limbs]{Long-limbs}:</strong> Bugbears are long-limbed goblinoids. They have @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1. </li>\n<li><strong>Silent Ambushers:</strong> Bugbears are natural ambushers. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}. This increases their maximum @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} to a d12+1.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/bugbear.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/bugbear.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L4NqGfd9AVja33DY"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"dz97ZPT4ZiVS2a21","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","content":"","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bt6afhtf6wi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Domains","color":"#000000","name":"4.2. Domains","children":["YMpFKQTMh1Wl0ze1","98ANLmDp6UA6in6Q","EZ8F7XWrX8klsOez","EbEkxu3vgft3aCaF","0tIqaAVU3wnwp11Q","cbvyMUcqPSNAE5Hf","NjKrO6ZSMYE0wCqX","Bh5CpFZQUCJFbTUy","D4rAvjLZ7YB93xRX","iRWehIxGnOYu4u7k","kXlR5fcstCG1JeOY","vnocgzpqh1qyjkUf","tPlqhMAV1a5G2VQN","gg8nWrfCOyKklxit","jugxe7QG2r2hAMgH","BSAFHpqQHd9Mbyum"],"folderPath":["temp_5n9ndtjortv","temp_ogabsqlqv6a"]}}}
{"_id":"e14FyGL3uSJw5CmD","name":"Rogue","content":"<p>Rogues devote as much effort to mastering the use of a variety of skills as they do to perfecting their combat abilities, giving them a broad expertise that few other characters can match. Many rogues focus on stealth and deception, while others refine the skills that help them in a dungeon environment, such as climbing, finding and disarming traps, and opening locks.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Gambling, Notice, Stealth, Taunt, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Fleet-Footed, Luck Great Luck</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Close Fighting, Improved Close Fighting, Dirty Fighter, Really Dirty Fighter, Dodge, Improved Dodge, Feint, Free Runner, Level Headed, Improved Level Headed, Steal Away</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobats, Combat Acrobat. Escape Artist, Femme Fatale/Ladykiller, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections, Humiliate, Streetwise</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.FZK94Vor67GYJ8FI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"eFHRMnTSnMT1r5Gl","name":"Group Rolls","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Group Rolls</h2>\n  <p>When the GM wants to make a Trait roll for a group of Extras with like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Traits}, \n    roll one Trait die as usual along with a Wild Die and treat this as the group’s result. This gives a decent average without making rolls for every individual.</p>\n\n<blockquote class=\"flavor\">\n    <em><strong>Example:</strong></em> \n    A group of soldiers attempts to pass by an enemy encampment. The GM rolls their Stealth die (a d6) and a Wild Die and takes the best of the two as the soldiers’ total.\n</blockquote>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2UZOrhF6a0yPIfdg"}}}
{"_id":"eJfdGORlbXxo3sH6","name":"Knight","content":"<p>You belong to an order of knights who have sworn oaths to achieve a certain goal. The nature of this goal depends on the order you serve, but in your eyes it is without question a vital and honorable endeavor. Most of these orders aren't limited to fighting types, but are open to all sorts of folk who are willing to battle and die for the order's cause. Particularly with the prevalence of magic there are some knightly orders that look for battlemages, such as the Knights Arcane of Aundair.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Athletics, Battle, Fighting, Riding, Traditions</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Code of Honor</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Brave</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Fast Mount, Mounted Combatant, Steady Hands, Trademark Weapon, Improved Trademark Weapon</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Command Presence, Fervor, Fantaticism, Hold the Line!, Death before Dishonor, Natural Leader, Tactician, Master Tactician</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Knight, Monster Hunter</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Bolster, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.m7XwStWRKJSYManh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ehB8Uux0ewtFIRaX","name":"Grappling","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Grappling</h2>\n\n\t<p>As an action, an attacker can make an opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to grapple a defender. \n\t\tIf the attacker wins, the foe is Entangled. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, he’s Bound. (Success on a foe who was already Entangled makes him Bound.) \n\t\tSee<strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound %26 Entangled]{Bound &amp; Entangled}</strong>.</p>\n\n\t<p>If a foe is Bound, the <em>grappler</em> is also @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted %26 Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} while maintaining his hold.</p>\n\n\t<p>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus applies when grappling a defender, \n\t\tbut other maneuvers don’t unless the Game Master rules otherwise in a specific situation.</p>\n\n\t<p><strong>Size Matters:</strong> If there’s a difference in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size %26 Scale]{Scale} between the attacker and defender, \n\t\tthe grappler subtracts the difference from his total (the defender doesn't get a bonus or penalty for Scale difference).</p>\n\n\t<p>Creatures may not generally grapple a foe more than two Sizes larger than themselves \n\t\tunless they have exceptional reach or Strength for their Size (GM’s call).</p>\n\n\t<blockquote><em><strong>Example:</strong></em> A dragon (Huge +4) tries to pin a humanoid thief (Normal). \n\t\tThe difference between Huge and Normal Scales is 4, so the dragon must subtract 4 from its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll. \n\t\tThe rogue doesn't get a bonus or penalty.\n\t</blockquote>\n\n\t<p><strong>Crush:</strong> A grappler may harm someone he’s Entangled or Bound by making an opposed Strength roll as an action on his turn. \n\t\tWith success, his attack does his Strength in damage (gaining bonus damage for a raise as normal).</p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.eCHqFTud7cLdyUGl"}}}
{"_id":"enUo0WHI6uaukv4p","name":"The Drop","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>The Drop</h2>\n  <p>Sometimes an attacker is able to catch a foe off-guard and gets “The Drop” on him. \n\t\tThe GM decides when this is in effect— usually it’s when the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound %26 Entangled]{bound} \n\t\tor completely unaware of an attack. The Drop usually happens up close but the GM can also allow it in other situations \n\t\tas she sees fit (a sniper attacking an unaware and stationary target).\n\t</p>\n\n\t<p>The Drop adds +4 to a character’s attack and damage rolls against that target for one action.</p>\n\t\n\t<p><strong>Knockout Blow:</strong> If a character takes enough damage to be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shaken]{Shaken} \n\t\tor worse from an attacker with The Drop on him, he must make a Vigor roll (at −2 if the attack was to the head) or be knocked unconscious.</p>\n\n\t<p>KO’ed characters stay that way for about half an hour or until the GM decides it’s dramatically appropriate to wake up. \n\t\tNote that Knockout Blows come from any kind of damage, not just blows to the head!</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.NNSvjWDvI6bOugnS"}}}
{"_id":"exM7tmeOZrp07Qp5","name":"Uskilled Attempts","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Unskilled Attempts</h2>\n  <p>If a character doesn’t have a skill for an action he’s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as repairing a steam engine or piloting an airship.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.zZrlQiJiFMBdRLVR"}}}
{"_id":"exRQR7Zhpttzk1cD","name":"Cleric","content":"<p>It’s important to understand that in Eberron, not all priests can wield divine energies. A priest provides spiritual guidance to a community and congregation and they don’t need magic to do this. A cleric is a full-fledged divine champion, and someone who possesses such a powerful connection wouldn’t waste that power on sermons and everyday services. People of faith assume that such power has a purpose.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Faith, Fighting, Healing, Religion</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance: </strong>Chain of Command, Vow</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Arcane Background (Miracles), Attractive, Charismatic</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge for a warrior cleric</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Fantaticism, Inspire</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Holy/Unholy Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Holy Adept</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Strong Willed, Iron Will, Work the Room</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Champion</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.z8YQ22r7SzqkZWpt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ey93l8xiuHBUSEz7","name":"Navigation","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Navigation</h1>\n<p>Traveling the treacherous seas of Eberron is an adventure in itself. The following quick method helps you determine how quickly a vessel travels and whether or not it stays on course.</p>\n<p>Each hex on the map is equal to 10 miles (3 leagues). Vessels cross as many squares as their Travel Speed each day, modified by their crew.</p>\n<p>The captain must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} roll for each day of travel and add the modifiers listed below:</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\" style=\"width:50%\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Navigation Modifiers</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Mod</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Circumstance</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Vessel stays along coast</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>The captain has no compass</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>Most of the crew has no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–1</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d12</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>With a success, the vessel moves as expected. A raise adds +1 to the vessel’s movement. Failure means the ship travels its expected movement in a random direction—roll a [[/r d6]] to determine the direction of the hex it moves to.</p>\n<p>If the roll moves the vessel into a land mass on the map, it may run aground. The captain must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} roll (the crew adds a group support roll as well to account for lookouts in the crow’s nest and so forth).</p>\n<p>A raise means the ship avoids the shoals, sandbars, or reefs and suffers no ill effects. Success means the ship is beached. It takes [[/r 2d20]] hours to pull it free, or [[/r 1d20]] hours if another ship is available. Failure indicates the ship has run aground. The vessel is wrecked and everyone aboard must swim to land or drown.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Boarding]{Boarding}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranks of Archers]{Ranks of Archers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Sinking]{Sinking}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_6g48t5q06rw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"fVYkn8svfIZxT72G","name":"Wound Cap","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Wound Cap</h2>\n<p>Use this Setting Rule when you want combat to remain dangerous but reduce the chances of characters (and villains!) dying from a single lucky blow. It can still happen, but it is far more rare.</p>\n<p>Characters can never suffer more than four @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} in a single hit and therefore never have to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} more than four wounds either!</p>\n<p><strong>Large Creatures:</strong> The Wound Cap applies even to creatures with more than three Wounds (due to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} or the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Resilient or Very Resilient)]{Resilient/Very Resilient Special Ability}). A Huge creature that can take five Wounds, for example, can’t take more than four from a single attack, so it can’t normally be killed with a single attack. The GM can always overrule this in specific and obvious situations, of course, such as massive blasts, falling from towering cliffs or mountains, etc.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rv4q29jrhjs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.YzizCZqcpHTsdUOa"}}}
{"_id":"fbHDxYw5uRcdeUph","name":"Assassin","content":"<p>A member of House Phiarlan, House Thuranni’s Shadow Network, the Black Dogs of House Ghallanda, or an agent of one of the Five Nations of Galifar such as a Dark Lantern, assassins pose a threat but only to their targets. House Tarkanan is known to have assassins among its ranks as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Intimidation, Notice, Shooting, Stealth, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Fleet-Footed, Quick</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Calculating, Close Fighting, Improved Close Fighting, Dirty Fighter, Really Dirty FIghter, Dodge, Improved Dodge, Extraction, Improved Extraction, Feint, First Strike, Improved First Strike, Free Runner, Killer Instinct, Marksman</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobat, Combat Acrobat, Assassin, Escape Artist, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections, Streetwise</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges: </strong>Danger Sense</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pbfHHDOqLV1c2mv8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"fggYxuKdsRgZf1sw","name":"Armor Table","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Armor</h1>\n<div>\n<p>Armor is written in parentheses next to a character’s Toughness, like this: 11 (2). This means 2 points of the character’s 11 Toughness comes from Armor. An Armor Piercing attack can bypass those 2 points but not the other 9.</p>\n<p>Note that greaves (leg guards) and vambraces (arm guards) are listed as pairs. Halve the weight and cost if a character wears only half the set (Minimum Strength doesn’t change).</p>\n</div>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"5\">Armor</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Item</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Armor</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Min Str.</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Weight</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"bar-heading\" colspan=\"5\"><span class=\"no-class\">Cloth/Hide Leather</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Hide Jacket]{Hide Jacket} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">+1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">5 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Hide Leggings]{Hide Leggings} (legs)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">+1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Armor]{Leather Armor} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">+1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">5 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Pants]{Leather Pants} (legs)</td>\n<td style=\