{"_id":"ilrbx8yUEwFE4Nrt","name":"Support","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Support</h2>\n  <p>Sometimes characters may want to cooperate or help an ally with a task. If so, and the GM decides it’s possible, \n\t\tsupporting characters roll the relevant skill (as an action if the game is in rounds) and declare which of their ally’s skills they’re attempting to Support.</p>\n\t<p>Success grants the ally +1 to one skill total this round, and a raise adds +2.\n\t\tA @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} on the support roll subtracts 2 from the lead’s total— \n\t\tsometimes extra hands just get in the way!\n\t</p>\n\t<p>Remove all Support bonuses at the end of the recipient’s turn, whether he used them or not (perhaps by taking an action different than the one he was Supported for).</p>\n\t<p>The maximum bonus from all Support rolls is +4. Strength checks are an exception and have no maximum bonus since more muscle can always manage more mass.</p>\n\t<p>Players and GMs should be creative when making Support rolls. An adventurer with Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}, for example, \n\t\tmight make a roll to find useful herbs for an ally attempting a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} check, \n\t\tor a character with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Academics]{Academics} might recall historical information helpful to a wizard doing research \n\t\ton an ancient relic.\n\t</p>\n\t<p>General encouragement (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll) such as “You can do it!” or “Check your six!” are perfectly acceptable, \n\t\tbut at the GM’s discretion lose effectiveness if repeated.\n\t</p>\n\n\t<blockquote>\n\t\t<em><strong>Example:</strong></em> \n\t\tThe heroes mount up for a day’s ride. Spooked by a pack of wolves, the horses bolt. The cleric, having no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} skill, \n\t\tfinds herself in danger of losing control of the mount. The paladin shouts “Hold the reins loosely!” She rolls Riding and gets a raise. \n\t\tThe cleric adds +2 to the unskilled Riding roll to control her horse.\n\t</blockquote>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.gqwdnmREHJnyCYSS"}}}
{"_id":"imJFsXQq7qYmmZXH","name":"Disease","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Disease</h2>\n  <p>\n    Diseases cover a wide range of maladies, from long-term debilitating illnesses to those which might cause immediate spasms or @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Death]{death}.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Diseases can be contracted through various vectors, such as an airborne\n    source, ingestion, or the touch or bite of a creature that causes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wounds]{Wound} or\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shaken]{Shaken} result. In any of these situations, the victim must make an immediate\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Trait Summaries]{Vigor} roll to avoid infection.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    To handle such a diverse range of diseases, we’ve broken them down into\n    three major categories. If you’re trying to model a specific disease, adjust\n    the rules presented here to better reflect its symptoms.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Recovery:</strong> Diseases can be cured by the\n    <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power with the Neutralize Poison or Disease modifier, or\n    with specific medications — whether or not those are available depends on the\n    game (GM’s call).\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4txb7iklyvb","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.sYmRb0jl47kTw673"}}}
{"_id":"iuFAwlTJRQ2ANEFK","name":"Keen","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>The weapon is exceptionally sharp, giving it @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{Armor Piercing} +2.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"iwcrejauXi7Dj9CU","name":"4 Power Modifiers","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h1 class=\"wide\">Power Modifiers</h1>\n  <p>\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers} allow characters \n    to customize their abilities, adding a special effect that better reflects their power’s \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping}.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Power Modifiers are selected when a power is activated and may be freely\n    changed each time. An icy <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em> \n    might cause @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing]{Armor Piercing} damage in one attack and \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Lingering Damage]{Lingering Damage} in the next.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    The common modifiers listed on this page can be used with any power a\n    character is using (unless otherwise prevented from modifying the power).\n    Some powers also list additional specific Power Modifiers that can be used\n    with that power.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Casters must declare which modifiers they’re using before rolling their\n    arcane skill. The number in parentheses is the price in additional \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points}\n    it costs to add the effect. A Power Modifier may only be applied once\n    per casting.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Duration:</strong> Power Modifiers last for the\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Duration]{Duration} of the\n    spell, or until the end of the target’s next turn in the case of Instant\n    powers.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Epic Powers:</strong> Some Power Modifiers are marked with a gold\n    star. These are Epic Powers. \n    requiring the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Mastery]{Arcane} or \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Divine Mastery]{Divine Mastery} Edges.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Adaptable caster (+1)</h3>\n  <p>\n    The caster can spend one extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Point} when activating a power to alter\n    its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping}. This can have important consequences if a foe has a particular\n    resistance to the spell’s usual Trapping or weakness to the new one!\n  </p>\n  <h3>Armor Piercing (+1 to +3)</h3>\n  <p>\n    The attack is focused to defeat armor or seeks out a foe’s exposed areas.\n    Each Power Point spent grants the power \n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 2 to a\n    max­imum of AP 6.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Fatigue (+2)</h3>\n  <p>\n    Powers that drain or tax an opponent can cause @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}. \n    The modifier may be attached to any power that can cause damage or is resisted by the target. If\n    she’s affected by the power in any way, she also suffers Fatigue. This\n    cannot cause @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitation}, however.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Glow/Shroud (+1)</h3>\n  <p>\n    Glow creates soft light (caster’s choice of color) in a Small Blast Template\n    centered on the target. It subtracts 2 from her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}\n    totals and negates 1 point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalties for those attacking the glowing character.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Shroud dims and slightly obscures the target so that attacks against her\n    suffer a −1 penalty and she adds +1 to her Stealth rolls.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Heavy Weapon (+2)</h3>\n  <p>\n    The caster creates a focused blast. The attack counts as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon]{Heavy Weapon}.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Hinder/Hurry (+1)</h3>\n  <p>\n    The target is slowed in some way, perhaps due to intense cold, a slippery\n    surface, or even binding matter or energy. His base Pace is reduced by 2.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    A caster can @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hinder or Hurry]{Hurry} the recipient instead, granting increased energy, sure\n    footing, or more powerful muscles. His Pace is increased by 2.\n  </p>\n  <p>Effects of either modifier aren’t cumulative.</p>\n  <h3>Lingering Damage (+2)</h3>\n  <p>\n    The target is hit by fire, cold, acid, gnawing insects, or some other\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping} that continues to cause damage after the initial attack. On the\n    victim’s next turn, he suffers the power’s base damage minus one die type\n    (for one additional turn only). If hit with a 2d6 <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>, for\n    example, the victim takes 2d4 damage at the start of his next turn. If the\n    base damage is already a d4 die type, it is d4–2 instead.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Range (+1/+2)</h3>\n  <p>\n    Double the power’s listed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} \n    for 1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Point}, or triple it for +2. This\n    modifier may not be used on powers with a Range of Touch or the Cone or\n    Stream Template.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Selective (+1)</h3>\n  <p>\n    With intense focus, the caster can choose not to affect any or all\n    individual targets within a power’s area of effect (picking all enemies\n    instead of allies in a <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>, for example).\n  </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":