{"_id":"jSA0o4irVBr0TBvk","name":"Bennies","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Bennies</h2>\n  <p>Every now and then, dice rolls may not work in your favor. That’s why <cite>Savage Eberron</cite> gives players a little control over their hero’s fate.</p>\n\n  <h3>Player Character Bennies</h3>\n    <p>Players start each game session with three “Bennies” (American slang for “benefits”), represented by poker chips, gaming stones, the official Bennies we make for all of our games, \n        or other tokens that signify a little bit of good luck or fate. Bennies are discarded at the end of each session—use them or lose them!</p>\n    <p><strong>Combat:</strong> If a session ends in the middle of combat or other dramatic event, wait until it’s resolved in the next session before giving out new Bennies.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.MQVTJecTZtkf85Vl"}}}
{"_id":"jeLa1gsfmOtQnEBk","name":"Test","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Test</h2>\n  <p>The <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support}</strong> option allows a character to help out her allies. \n\t\tTest is the opposite— it lets him make things more difficult for his foes! \n\t\tTests include embarrassing an opponent, throwing sand in his eyes, staring him down with a steely gaze, or anything else a clever player can think of to rattle \n\t\this enemy and put him off-balance.\n\t</p>\n\t<p>To perform a Test, the player describes the action and works with the GM to determine the most appropriate skill to roll for it. \n\t\tTests are resisted instinctively, so the “attacker’s” skill roll is opposed by the attribute it’s linked to. \n\t\tTripping someone is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll versus Agility since that’s what Athletics is linked to. \n\t\t@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} is linked to Smarts, so verbally humiliating someone is resisted by that attribute. \n\t\t@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, when used as a Test instead of an actual attack, \n\t\tisn’t compared to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry}— it’s opposed by Agility. \n\t\tWhatever skill is used, performing a Test is an action.\n\t</p>\n\t<p>If the attacker wins the opposed roll, he can choose to make his foe \n\t\t<strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted %26 Vulnerable]{Distracted or ­Vulnerable}</strong>. \n\t\tIf he wins with a raise, the target is also @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shaken]{Shaken}, \n\t\tand there may be other subjective effects as the GM allows, such as a tripped foe being knocked @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n\t<p><strong>Modifiers:</strong> The GM must determine which modifiers apply to a Test. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, for example, \n\t\tshould include @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range}, \"@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover %26 Obstacles]{Cover}, \n\t\t@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}, etc. \n\t\tA hero with a bonus to his Parry does <em>not</em> add it to his Agility when challenged with a Fighting roll, however, because the defender resists with Agility— \n\t\tnot his Parry.\n\t</p>\n\t<p>Take the details into consideration as well— using a shameful secret to hit a rival’s ego where it hurts, for example, might be worth a +2 bonus to the attacker.</p>\n\t<p><strong>Repetition:</strong> Using the same or similar action repeatedly quickly grows less effective, so the GM shouldn't allow players to use \n\t\tthe same tactics, insults, or threats more than once an encounter.</p>\n\t<p><strong>Additional Dice:</strong> If characters have addi­tional dice for a Test, such as when using a weapon with a high Rate of Fire, \n\t\the may roll all the dice but takes only the highest as his Test total. He doesn’t get multiple results and he can’t spread them out to other targets.\n\t</p>\n\n\t<aside class=\"sidebar\">\n\t\t<h1>Dungeoneering</h1>\n\t\t<p>When heroes delve into dungeons— or ruins or even buildings— combat can get cramped.</p>\n\t\t<p>In <cite>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</cite>, creative use of these <strong>Situational Rules</strong> give the characters options during combat. \n\t\t\tInstead of just waiting for your turn to get through a door and attack, for example, your hero can attempt other actions to make an impact with teamwork.</p>\n\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\t<strong> Support:</strong> Coordinate your actions and use Support to ensure success. \n\t\t\t\tFor example, the paladin tries to Push past an ogre blocking the entrance to the villain’s chamber, hoping to create space for the fighter. \n\t\t\t\tThe rogue rolls Support using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}(“Is that all you got?”) \n\t\t\t\tto assist with the paladin’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Push]{Push} attempt.\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\t<strong>Test:</strong> Coordinate tactics to make it harder for enemies to fight back. In the Push example above, the sorcerer— \n\t\t\t\twho wants to save @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points} for attacks on the villain— can @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} \n\t\t\t\tthe ogre with Taunt. Knowing it speaks Giant, she shouts insults in that tongue. \n\t\t\t\tIf she succeeds on the opposed roll, she makes the ogre @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted %26 Vulnerable]{Distracted}, \n\t\t\t\twhich helps the paladin win the opposed Push.\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t</aside>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.j2NVBjzgpgqLcgH1"}}}
{"_id":"jfvLAutQQwzkl4zw","name":"Bane","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>When used against a specific type of creature (dwarf, goblin, elemental, etc), a bane weapon has +2 AP and its damage die increases one type.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"jugxe7QG2r2hAMgH","name":"Trickery Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Trickery Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Chance, luck, secrets, stealth</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> Kol Korran, Olladra, The Mockery, The Traveler, Cults of the Dragon Below</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]{Curse}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{Drain Power Points}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{Empathy}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fortune's Favored]{Fortune's Favored}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{Growth/Shrink}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{Illusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{Intangibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{Leaping}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{Mind Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{Time Stop}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{Wish}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bt6afhtf6wi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Domains","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"jytREDFqV8CZmhb0","name":"Limited Free Actions","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Limited Free Actions</h2>\n  <p>\n    A character may only perform one limited free action per turn. For example, the barbarian’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Intimidating Glare]{Intimidating Glare} \n    allows her to make an Intimidation Test as a limited free action. If the barbarian also had access to another limited free action, she could not do it in the same turn \n    as she used Intimidating Glare.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Combat]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aeejh0xnzv6","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Combat keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.NhYGWP7j72ovBppY"}}}
{"_id":"k8t7tf3YqFw1PPVN","name":"The Golden Hour","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>The Golden Hour</h2>\n  <p>\n    Patients who survive their initial trauma have about an hour to survive\n    most life-threatening injuries. If they receive medical attention during\n    that time, they can generally be saved. The longer the wait, however, the\n    more likely the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wounds]{Wounds} are to be fatal.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    In <cite>Savage Eberron</cite>, we extend this concept to healing in\n    general. Besides reflecting the real-world concept, it also provides good\n    game balance and drama as the party has to decide whether to press on\n    despite their injuries.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Healing]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yxu1ag41di","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Healing keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.KLjCyca8DT2v6eF1"}}}
{"_id":"kEuyhP3uXRABm8HM","name":"Crew Provisions","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Crew Provisions</h1>\n<p>The crews of ships must eat and drink, and ensuring each vessel is properly provisioned is a major concern of any captain.</p>\n<p>To keep things simple, provisions are purchased as generic “points” rather than tracking every bit of food and water required. Each point represents one day’s food, water, and other supplies for each man on board, and costs 5 silver sovereigns per head. This includes fruit capable of staving off scurvy.</p>\n<p>Every 500 points of provisions takes up one cargo space.</p>\n<p>Note that provisions are not the same as “Food” that can be bought and sold at ports. Provisions are biscuits, hardtack, and water. Food is fruit, bread, grain, wine, and other “luxuries.” A cargo space worth of Food can be converted into 50 provisions in an emergency.</p>\n<h2 class=\"blue-example\">Example:</h2>\n<p><em>The Frigate Jolly Edward sets sail with twelve crew. The captain expects to be at sea for at least a month, so he needs 12 provisions for each of 30 days, or 360 provisions. He decides to play it safe and buys 500 provisions. The provisions cost 500 pieces of eight and take up one cargo space.</em></p>\n<p><em>If the ship runs out of food, the captain could convert a cargo space worth of “Food” (a commodity) to 50 provisions. This would feed his 12-man crew for about 4 days.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Hunger:</strong> Wild Cards suffer from starvation normally (one provision a day counts as adequate food). For the rest of the crew, make a group Vigor roll each day they have half rations (one provision for every two men). Subtract 2 if the men have less than this.</p>\n<p>Should the crew collectively reach Incapacitated state, 10% of the men perish each day from starvation. Most crews mutiny long before this starts to happen.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Boarding]{Boarding}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranks of Archers]{Ranks of Archers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Sinking]{Sinking}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6g48t5q06rw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"kIpE7V9cwUa2USNX","name":"Returning","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Thrown Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>The weapon returns to its user’s hand at the end of her turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> —</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"kSWcoQ4cWv2MO60t","name":"Edges","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Edges</h1>\n<p>Below is a list of Edges common to most settings. You’ll find new Edges designed for your game world in official <em>Savage Worlds</em> books as well.</p>\n<p>The Edges are grouped by type to help during character creation. You’ll find a summary below.</p>\n<p>Unless an Edge specifically says otherwise, it may only be selected once.</p>\n<p>The core base Edges are those presented in <em>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</em> rather than the <em>Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</em>.</p>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<p>Below each Edge is the minimum Rank (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}) required to take it along with any other prerequisites such as attributes, skills, or other Edges.</p>\n<h2>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Setting Edges}</h2>\n<p>To keep this Edge summary list managable @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Setting Edges} for <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Classes}</span>, <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Dragonmarks}</span>, <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Prestige edges}</span>, and <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Racial edges}</span> have been moved to a seperate page.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Background Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Alertness]{Alertness}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore –2 penalty when making @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait rolls} with off-hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>AB for outcasts that manifest an Aberrant Dragonmark.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Divine Magic)]{Arcane Background (Divine Magic)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>AB for the faithful who follow one of the religions of Eberron.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>AB for wizards that study and manipulate the fabric of magic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Arcane Background (Psionics)}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>AB for those that use their own mental energy to manipulate matter and people. Most common in Sarlona.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a −2 penalty (even if cast by allies!); magical damage is reduced by 2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Arcane Resistance]{Improved Arcane Resistance}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Arcane Resistance</td>\n<td>As Arcane Resistance except penalty is increased to −4 and magical damage is reduced by 4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aristocrat]{Aristocrat}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} with upper class.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Attractive]{Attractive}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d6</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Very Attractive]{Very Attractive}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Attractive</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Berserk]{Berserk}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>After being @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken or Wounded}, melee attacks must be@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attacks}, +1 die type to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength}, +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}, ignore one level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll hits random target. Take @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} after every five consecutive rounds, may choose to end rage with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Smarts} roll –2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brave]{Brave}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and –2 to rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawny]{Brawny}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d6, V d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}) +1. Treat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Strength} as one die type higher for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and Minimum Strength to use weapons, armor, or equipment.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N. St d6, V d6</td>\n<td>Link @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Agility} (including resistance). Short @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} of any thrown item increased by +1. Double that for the adjusted Medium Range, and double again for Long Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Charismatic]{Charismatic}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Elan]{Elan}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 when spending a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait roll}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fame]{Fame}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>+1 Persuasion rolls when recognized (Common Knowledge), double usual fee for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Famous]{Famous}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fame</td>\n<td>+2  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when recognized, 5× or more usual fee for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast Healer]{Fast Healer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Vd8</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Vigor} when rolling for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Healing]{natural healing}; check every 3 days.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} +2, increase running die one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.House Scion]{House Scion}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, DGMK Race</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} with your Dragonmarked House.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Natural Swimmer]{Natural Swimmer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} to swimming, +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} when swimming, and can hold breath 50% longer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Linguist]{Linguist}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>Character has d6 in languages equal to half her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Smarts} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Luck]{Luck}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the start of each session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Luck]{Great Luck}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Luck</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} at the start of each session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Quick]{Quick}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>The hero may discard and redraw @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} of 5 or lower.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>Character starts with three times the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{starting funds} and an annual salary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Rich</td>\n<td>Five times @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{starting funds} and an annual salary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.University Trained]</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d8</td>\n<td>\n<p>4 points for Knowledge skills, +1 point for use in a language.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Combat Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Blind Fighting]{Blind Fighting}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d8, Notice d8</td>\n<td>Hhe hero halves @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Block]{Block}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry}, ignore 1 point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Block]{Improved Block}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Block</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry}, ignore 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bodyguard]{Bodyguard}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, A d8, Block, Notice d8</td>\n<td>Attacks against one adjacent ally are rolled against the heroes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry}, as long as they reamin adjacent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawler]{Brawler}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d8, V d8</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} +1, add d4 to damage from fists; or increase it a die type if combined with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}, or similar abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bruiser]{Bruiser}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Brawler</td>\n<td>Increase unarmed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} damage a die type and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} another +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brutal]{Brutal}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, WC</td>\n<td>+1 to damage for each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Calculating]{Calculating}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d8, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of penalties on one action with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card)} of Five or less.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Close Fighting]{Close Fighting}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>The hero gains a bonus to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} equal to the enemy's weapon @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Close Fighting]{Improved Close Fighting}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Close Fighting</td>\n<td>As Close Fighting, but also gaining a +1 bonus to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} equal to enemy weapons @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Reflexes]{Combat Reflexes}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Spirit} to recover from being @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Counterattack]{Counterattack}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against one foe per round who failed a  roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Counterattack]{Improved Counterattack}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Counterattack</td>\n<td>As Counterattack, but against three failed attacks per round.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dead Shot]{Dead Shot}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, Athletics or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>First successful@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Thorwing) or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, double damage from when dealt a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dodge]{Dodge}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d8</td>\n<td>−2 to be hit by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{ranged attacks}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Dodge]{Improved Dodge}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Dodge</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} totals.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extraction]{Extraction}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>One adjacent foe doesn’t get a free attack when you @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{withdraw from close combat}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Extraction]{Improved Extraction}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Extraction</td>\n<td>Three adjacent foes don’t get free attacks when you @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{withdraw from close combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast Mount]{Fast Mount}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Riding d6</td>\n<td>Mount and dismount as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Feint]{Feint}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>You may choose to make foe resist with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Smarts Instead of Agility} during a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Fighting Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack once per round when foe moves within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved First Strike]{Improved First Strike}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, First Strike</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against up to three foes when they move within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Formation Fighter]{Formation Fighter}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} by an additional +1 (Max. still +4).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Free Runner]{Free Runner}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} and add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} in foot @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{chases} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (climbing).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Roll a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with one melee attack per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Improved Frenzy}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Frenzy</td>\n<td>Roll a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with up to two melee attacks per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V</td>\n<td>+1d6 damage vs. creatures three @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Sizes} larger or more.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Giant Killer]{Improved Giant Killer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Giant Killer</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{armor} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{size} of a creature three @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size and Scale} larger or more.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ground Fighter]{Ground Fighter}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A or St d6</td>\n<td>No penalties when @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}. +1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} against a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone} opponent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hard To Kill]{Hard To Kill}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties} when making @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Harder To Kill]{Harder To Kill}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Hard to Kill</td>\n<td>Roll a die if the character perishes. Even if he’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, he survives somehow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improvisational Fighter]{Improvisational Fighter}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d6</td>\n<td>Ignore –2 penalty when attacking with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Improvised Weapons]{Improvised Weapons}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Jaw]{Iron Jaw}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} and  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Vigor} rolls to avoid @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{Knockout Blows}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Killer Instinct]{Killer Instinct}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td>The hero gets a free reroll in any opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} he initiates.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8</td>\n<td>Draw an additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} each round in combat and choose which one to use.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Level Headed]{Improved Level Headed}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Level Headed</td>\n<td>Draw two additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} each round in combat and choose which one to use.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lunge]{Lunge}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Gain +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{reach} with the adventurer's weapon.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Marksman]{Marksman}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Athletics or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of penalties from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range},@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Speed]{Speed}; or add +1 to first @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing) or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll. Character may not move or fire greater than @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF 1}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Fighting} +1, fists and feet count as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}, add d4 damage die to unarmed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks (or increase die a step if you already have it).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Warrior]{Martial Warrior}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Martial Artist</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Fighting} +2, increase damage die type a step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mighty Blow]{Mighty Blow}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>On first successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll, double damage when dealt a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mounted Combatant]{Mounted Combatant}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Riding d8</td>\n<td>Ignores two points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} penalties and may spend a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} for mount. May also make @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll to increase pace of mount by 2\".</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nerves of Steel]{Nerves of Steel}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore one level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Nerves of Steel]{Improved Nerves of Steel}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Nerves of Steel</td>\n<td>Ignore up to two levels of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.No Mercy]{No Mercy}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td>+2 damage when spending a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Oversized Weapon Master]{Oversized Weapon Master}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, St d10, Fighting d10, Size 0</td>\n<td>The character may use a two-handed weapon with one hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Reload]{Rapid Reload}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shooting d6</td>\n<td>Reduce the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} value of a weapon by 1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Shot]{Rapid Shot}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Shooting d6</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Rapid Shot]{Improved Rapid Shot}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Rapid Shot</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for up to two @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steady Hands]{Steady Hands}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unstable Platform]{Unstable Platform} penalty; reduce running penalty to –1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steal Away]{Steal Away}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d8, Stealth d6</td>\n<td>The hero can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} to hide when withdrawing.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sucker Punch]{Sucker Punch}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d6, Fighting d8,First Strike</td>\n<td>If the hero succeeds on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}, they recieve a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attack}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll at –2 to hit all targets in weapon’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach}, no more than once per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sweep]{Improved Sweep}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sweep</td>\n<td>As above, but ignore the –2 penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Trademark Weapon}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, d8 in related skill</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} total with a specific weapon; +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} while weapon is readied.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Trademark Weapon]{Improved Trademark Weapon}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Trademark Weapon</td>\n<td>The attack and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} bonus increases to +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.True Hero]{True Hero}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, WC, Iron Jaw</td>\n<td>When the hero would get @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{incapacitated}, they get a free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Two-Weapon Fighting]{Two-Weapon Fighting}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>Make one extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll with a second melee weapon in the off-hand at no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wrestler]{Wrestler}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A or St d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>Make make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting] roll rather than @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Crushing} damage is increased to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} + d4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Takedown Move]{Takedown Move}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Wrestler</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Push]{Push} moves are opposed at a –2 (–4 on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Leadership Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.A Few Good Men]{A Few Good Men}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Inspire, Sm d8 , Battle d10</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, add one more Token to force calculations.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Board 'Em]{Board 'Em}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Command, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>+4 to group @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls to grapple an enemy vessel.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in Battle]{Born in Battle}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command]{Command}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} recovery rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command Presence]{Command Presence}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command</td>\n<td>Increase Command Range to 10″ (20 yards)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Coordinated Firepower]{Coordinated Firepower}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sm d6, Command, Athletics or Shooting d8+</td>\n<td>The hero adds a flat +2 attack bonus for additional ranged attacks for those within command range. Additional bonus damage on raises.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Cry Havoc!]{Cry Havoc!}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sp d8, Fervor, Battle d10</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the character may declare a charge that will cause his enemy to lose one extra token.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Death before Dishonor]{Death before Dishonor}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sp d8, Hold the Line, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero gains +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Spirit} when rolling for Morale.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Drop!]{Drop!}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command, Notice d6</td>\n<td>Allows to hero to command allies to drop @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fanaticism]{Fanaticism}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fervor</td>\n<td>Those in Command Range gain +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fervor]{Fervor}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sp d8, Command</td>\n<td>Extras in range add +1 to their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} damage rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Help Me!]{Help Me!}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command</td>\n<td>When an enemy moves adjacent to the hero, the hero may call for help acting as if they were on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hold]{Hold}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hold the Line!]{Hold the Line!}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command</td>\n<td>+1 to  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} in Command Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inspire]{Inspire}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command</td>\n<td>Once per turn, the hero may roll his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} one type of Trait roll, and apply it to everyone in Command Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master and Commander]{Master and Commander}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Boating d10, Intimidation d8, must be sole captain</td>\n<td>Crews get +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Natural Leader]{Natural Leader}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d8, Command</td>\n<td>Leadership Edges now apply to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Siege Breaker]{Siege Breaker}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero can increase the Siege Bonus when conducting a siege with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Siege Mentality]{Siege Mentality}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero can increase the Siege Bonus when defending in a siege with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tactician]{Tactician}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d6</td>\n<td>Draw an extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} each turn that may be assigned to any allied @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} in Command Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Tactician]{Master Tactician}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Tactician</td>\n<td>Draw and distribute two extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} instead of one.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Power Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adaptable Caster]{Adaptable Caster}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Artificer, Magic, or Wizard), arcane skill d6</td>\n<td>The trappings can be changed on the powers for 1 Power Point.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Armor]{Arcane Armor}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Arcane Interference</td>\n<td>Your Armor Interference counts as one level higher.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channeling]{Channeling}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB</td>\n<td>Reduce Power Point cost by 1 with a raise on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Activation]{Activation} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Concentration]{Concentration}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any) or MP (Any)</td>\n<td>Double duration of all non-Instant powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Craft Arcane Device]{Craft Arcane Device}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any but Psionics), Repair d6</td>\n<td>Allows user to create arcane devices to share with others imbued with a single power.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Finely Tuned]{Finely Tuned}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8 Craft Arcane Device or Infuse Item, Repair d8</td>\n<td>Reduce the cost of creating @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any or MP (Any), Vow (to your Deity)</td>\n<td>Add +1 to +4 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} for each Power Point spent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mentalist]{Mentalist}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Psionics), Psionics d6</td>\n<td>+2 to opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.New Powers]{New Powers}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB</td>\n<td>Your character knows two new powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any) or MP (Any)</td>\n<td>Grants 5 additional Power Points.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Surge]{Power Surge}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, AB (Any), arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>The hero recovers 10 Power Points when his action card is a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soul Drain]{Soul Drain}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d8, AB (Any) or MP (Any)</td>\n<td>Take a level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} to recover 5 Power Points, or 2 to recover 10.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Professional Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ace]{Ace}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td>\n<td>Character may spend @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for his vehicle and ignores up to 2 points of penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Acrobat]{Acrobat}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll on acrobatic @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} attempts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Acrobat]{Combat Acrobat}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Acrobat</td>\n<td>−1 to hit with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{ranged and melee attacks}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in the Saddle]{Born in the Saddle}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Riding d6</td>\n<td>Gain one free reoll on all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} rolls and increase the mount's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} by 2 and its running die one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Entertainer]{Entertainer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Performance d8</td>\n<td>+1 to any two:  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}  skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hidden Strike]{Hidden Strike}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Fighting d6, Stealth d8</td>\n<td>+2 to damage foes when @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or assassin has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inquisitive]{Inquisitive}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d8, Research d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research} and certain types of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Jack-Of-All-Trades]{Jack-of-All-Trades}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d10</td>\n<td>Gain d4 in a skill (or d6 with a raise) until replaced.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Knight]{Knight}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, St d8, V d8, Fighting d8, Riding d8</td>\n<td>The knight is gifted with the tools of his trade. He also gains a +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when dealing with good causes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Storyteller]{Master Storyteller}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Persuasion d8</td>\n<td>The storyteller rolls d8's for Glory rolls instead of d6's.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Legendary Storyteller]{Legendary Storyteller}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Master Storyteller</td>\n<td>The storyteller gains a d8 Glory for each raise after the first.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monster Hunter]{Monster Hunter}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d6</td>\n<td>The hero is immune to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks of one type of creature. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mr Fix It]{Mr. Fix It}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Repair d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} rolls, half the time required with a raise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Necromancer]{Necromancer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8, AB (Cleric, Divine Magic, Magic or Wizard), arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>May cast @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie} as a Novice. Additional, reduce the cost of casting and extend the duration.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Necromancer]{Master Necromancer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Necromancer</td>\n<td>Zombies raised by Necromancer gain an extra die in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} and one skill of his choice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rope Monkey]{Rope Monkey}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d8, Athletics d10</td>\n<td>The sailor can swing among the rigging to move around a ship or canopy. They may also make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll if they fall to take half damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scholar]{Scholar}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Research d8</td>\n<td>+2 to any one “knowledge” skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ship's Carpenter]{Ship's Carpenter}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Boating d6, Repair d8</td>\n<td>The sailor can repair wounds to a ship without a dry dock.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soldier]{Soldier}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, S d6, V d6</td>\n<td>Strength is one die type higher for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Minimum Strength]{Min Str}. Reroll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} rolls when resisting environmental @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Thief]{Thief}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Stealth d6, Thievery d6</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in urban environments.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Troubadour]{Troubadour}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Common Knowledge d6, Performance d8</td>\n<td>Add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls; may use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} in place of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} for Leadership Edges or Edges that require @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Woodsman]{Woodsman}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, Survival d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in the wilds.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Social Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bolster]{Bolster}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>May remove @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable} state after a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Common Bond]{Common Bond}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>The hero may freely give her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to others.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Connections]{Connections}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>Contacts provide aid or other favors once per session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Menacing]{Menacing}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, See Text</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Provoke]{Provoke}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Intimidation or Persuasion d6</td>\n<td>May “provoke” foes with a raise on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Rabble-Rouser}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Spirit d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a Medium Blast Template with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reliable]{Reliable}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Retort]{Retort}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Intimidation d6</td>\n<td>A raise when resisting a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attack makes the foe @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skullduggery]{Skullduggery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Deception d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Streetwise]{Streetwise}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and criminal networking.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strong Willed]{Strong Willed}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Smarts or Spirit}-based @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Will]{Iron Will}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Brave, Strong Willed</td>\n<td>The bonus now applies to resisting and recovery from powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work The Room]{Work The Room}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, roll a second die when @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Supporting} via @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and apply result to additional ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work the Crowd]{Work the Crowd}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Work the Room</td>\n<td>As above, but up to twice per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Weird Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Bond]{Beast Bond}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>The hero may spend @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} for animals under her control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Master]{Beast Master}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Animals like your hero and he has a pet of some sort. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Champion]{Champion}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>+2 damage vs. supernaturally evil creatures.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at +2 to sense ambushes or similar events.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healer]{Healer}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} rolls, magical or otherwise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Liquid Courage]{Liquid Courage}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d8</td>\n<td>Alcohol increases @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} a die type and ignores one level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Agility, Smarts}, and related skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scavenger]{Scavenger}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Luck</td>\n<td>May find a needed item once per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]{Storm Chaser}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during storms. Recieve extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Symbiont Mastery]{Symbiont Mastery}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>Recieve +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Spirit} in battle of wills with sybionts. With symbiont attached, +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d8, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}. Recieve extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Legendary Edges</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Followers]{Followers}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L</td>\n<td>The hero has five followers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Professional]{Professional}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Max Trait</td>\n<td>The character’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Expert]{Expert}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Professional in Trait</td>\n<td>The character’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master]{Master}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L, Expert in Trait</td>\n<td>The character’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Wild Die} is a d10 with a chosen @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Trait}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L</td>\n<td>The character gains a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} sidekick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tough As Nails]{Tough As Nails}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">L, V d8</td>\n<td>The hero can take four @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tougher Than Nails]{Tougher Than Nails}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Tough as Nails, V d12</td>\n<td>The hero can take five @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Weapon Master]{Weapon Master}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Fighting d12</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} increases by +1 and Fighting bonus damage die is d8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Arms]{Master of Arms}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Weapon Master</td>\n<td>Parry increases another +1 and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dealing Damage]{bonus damage} die is d10.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":16}}}
{"_id":"kWSHyc6CavxnoJ7v","name":"Free Attacks","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Free Attacks</h2>\n  <p>Some Edges, such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Counterattack]{Counterattack} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}, \n\t\tor options such as <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdrawing From Melee}</strong>, allow a character to make a free attack.</p>\n\t<p>Free attacks are a single attack unaltered by other Edges or combat options. This is usually a Fighting or grappling attack, but could include Shooting \n\t\tif the attacker is armed with a hand crossbow, wand, or small device \n\t\t(GM's call, see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranged Weapons in Melee]{Ranged Weapons in Melee}</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{4 Situational Rules}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.n6CeWMrlOzgdcjoo"}}}
{"_id":"kXlR5fcstCG1JeOY","name":"Protection Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Protection Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Protection, care giving, shelter, vigilance</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> Boldrei, Dol Arrah, Olladra, The Silver Flame</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Champion of Faith]{Champion of Faith}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Consecrate/Desecrate Ground]{Consecrate Ground}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{Empathy}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{Environmental Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{Fly}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{Gift of Battle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{Growth/Shrink}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{Illusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{Mind Link}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{Resurrection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bt6afhtf6wi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Domains","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"kyZD4VX3J6GxNKzg","name":"Deflecting","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Shield Enchantment</h3>\n<p>Increase the shield’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonus increased by +1.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 4,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"lE6JOkMxuXuW0e7v","name":"5 Cantrips","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h1 class=\"wide\">Cantrips</h1>\n  <p>\n    A mage sets a broom to sweeping his floor. A priest lights a candle with the\n    grace of her god. A bard tells an animated story in the night air,\n    illuminated with the dancing cinders of a campfire. Such minor orisons\n    (prayers) or lesser magicks are collectively called \"cantrips.\"\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    In <cite>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</cite>, any character with an Arcane\n    Background (see both Arcane Background and Class Edges @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Edges]{here}) can cast cantrips.\n  </p>\n  <h3>Activation</h3>\n  <p>\n    A character may cast a cantrip by making an arcane skill roll. This is an\n    action, and the effect must be based on one of the character’s existing\n    powers. A sorcerer could use <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em> with a \n    fire @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping} to light a\n    campfire, for example. A druid could use <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle}</em> to make vines\n    dance to entertain a group of children. A wizard can use <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{sound}</em> to\n    ring a bell calling a servant to his study.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Success means the desired effect occurs. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}\n    has an additional narrative impact of some kind— the candle glows brightly, the vines dance in perfect\n    synchronicity, or the bell rings loud and pure.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Failure causes the spell to fail without effect. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure}\n    causes the spell to backfire, which requires the caster to lose 1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points}\n    (or suffer @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} if the caster has no Power Points). Critical Failure also\n    causes an embarrassment or minor mishap of some sort— an animated broom\n    carelessly knocks a jar of ink onto the floor, a conjured flame lights a\n    book on fire, or the power makes an embarrassing sound or smell.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    A successfully cast cantrip’s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Duration]{Duration} is the same as the power it’s based\n    on and may be maintained by spending Power Points as usual.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    The GM has the final say on what a cantrip can do, but the effect must not\n    replace a power or cause damage (at least directly). It can be used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}\n    or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support}, or grant a +1 bonus on a subsequent roll in the same encounter.\n    For example, if the bard uses a cantrip to impress the children of\n    Sandpoint, the GM might give him +1 to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll later on if he\n    talks to their parents or someone else who witnessed the kindness.\n  </p>\n  <div>\n    <img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/halfwizard.webp\" />\n  </div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_vv8zdhdw0l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.NssYQO2Whw9eVEZb"}}}
{"_id":"lH5snVbbin3fisoy","name":"Arcane Background (Artificer)","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Arcane Background (Artificer)</h2>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Edge:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}</li>\n<li><strong>Requirements:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]{Artificer}</li>\n<li><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Smarts})</li>\n<li><strong>Artifice:</strong> Artificers may take Edges that require @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Weird Science)]{Arcane Background (Weird Science)}.</li>\n<li><strong>Tools: </strong>Artificers must carry their \"tools\" on their person to activate their powers.</li>\n<li><strong>Malfunction: </strong>When an artificer rolls a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} roll, the Dungeon Master rolls on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules-tables.Manfunction Table]{Manfunction Table} to see what happens.</li>\n<li><strong>Starting Powers:</strong> 2</li>\n<li><strong>Power Points:</strong> 15</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]{Burrow}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{Drain Power Points}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{Environmental Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{Fly}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{Growth/Shrink}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{Illusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{Leaping}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{Locate}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{Magic Mark}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{Plane Shift}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h2>Playing an Artificer</h2>\n<p>In Eberron, magic is almost technology. Spellcasters specialize in certain forms of that technology, while artificers tinker with its fundamental workings. Artificers understand magic on a different level from spellcasters, and do not cast spells as wizards and clerics do. They have an amazing facility with magic items and constructs, and in many ways, they keep the magical world of Eberron running.</p>\n<p>Masters of unlocking magic in everyday objects, artificers are supreme inventors. They see magic as a complex system waiting to be decoded and controlled. Artificers use tools to channel arcane power, crafting magical objects. To cast a spell, an artificer could use alchemist's supplies to create a potent elixir, calligrapher's supplies to inscribe a sigil of power on an ally's armor, or tinker's tools to craft a temporary charm. The magic of artificers is tied to their tools and their talents.</p>\n<h3>ARCANE SCIENCE</h3>\n<p>In the world of Eberron, arcane magic has been harnessed as a form of science and deployed throughout society. Artificers reflect this development. Their knowledge of magical devices, and their ability to infuse mundane items with magic, allows Eberron's most miraculous projects to continue.</p>\n<p>During the Last War, artificers were marshaled on a massive scale. Many lives were saved because of the inventions of brave artificers, but countless lives were also lost because of the mass destruction unleashed by their creations.</p>\n<h3>SEEKERS OF NEW LORE</h3>\n<p>Nothing excites an artificer quite like uncovering a new metal or discovering a source of elemental energy. In artificer circles, new inventions and strange discoveries create the most excitement. Artificers who wish to make their mark must innovate, creating something fresh, rather than iterating on familiar designs.</p>\n<p>This drive for novelty pushes artificers to become adventurers. Eberron's main travel routes and populated regions have long since been explored. Thus, artificers seek the frontiers of civilization in hopes of making the next great discovery in arcane research.</p>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Artificers craft, invent, and tinker with their inventions. All your powers are produced by inventions that are crafted using various tools. When creating an artificer, pick at least one kind of tool set that the artificer works with; @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist Supplies]{alchemist supplies} for potions and ungents, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tinker's Tools]{tinker's tools} for general tinkering, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Warforged Repair Kit]{warforged repair kit} if they work strictly with warforged, or another artisan tool kit that makes sense.</p>\n<p>In general, it's assumed an artificer is constantly working and tinker on their inventions during downtime. Perhaps before bed, in the morning, or during meals. It should be assumed the inventor takes at least an hour a day preparing items that might be used. If the artificer can't perform this tinkering, or does not have their tools, she can't use her powers.</p>\n<h2>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trappings}</h2>\n<p>As an artificer, you use tools when you cast your spells. When describing your spellcasting, think about how you're using a tool to perform the spell effect. If you cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist Supplies]{alchemist supplies}, you could be quickly producing a salve. If you cast it using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tinker's Tools]{tinker's tools}, you might have a miniature mechanical spider that binds wounds. When you cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> with a poison effect, you could fling foul chemicals or use a wand that spits venom.</p>\n<p>Artificers take pride in their custom inventions, often giving them creative names to differentiate them from other artificers. Such as \"Elenna's Miraculous Healing Ungent\" or \"Mending Spider\". You should make sure to do the same for your powers.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yqngxv6403a","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.3. Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"lI5IPZPThORV5qsg","name":"Cold Iron","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2 class=\"wide\">Cold Iron</h2>\n<p>Mined from the deepest depths of Khyber, cold iron is the weakness of certain fiends and fey creatures. Weapons forged with cold iron increase @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} by 2 and cost twice as much as normal.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Materials]{See Special Materials here}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"lQhddkySLVld21Wj","name":"Traps and Haunts","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Traps and Haunts</h2>\n  <p>\n    Traps are mechanical or magical in nature, usually constructed to protect\n    treasures or stop intruders. They range from simple camouflaged pits to\n    poisoned @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Darts(blowgun)]{darts} and triggered magical <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> effects.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Haunts function like traps, but are specific supernatural phenomena\n    connected to restless shades or other spirits. These areas react violently\n    to the presence of the living, usually triggering some kind of effect when\n    the area is entered or some item of personal import is touched or\n    approached.\n  </p>\n  <p>Here's how to read each trap or haunt's description:</p>\n  <p><strong>Type:</strong> Mechanical, Magical, Haunt</p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Notice Check:</strong> Yes or No, with any modifier to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll\n    to detect the presence of a trap. Success allows the heroes to react before\n    the trap or haunt is triggered.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Thievery Check:</strong> Yes or No, with any modifiers to the\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} die roll needed to succeed in disabling a trap.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Effects:</strong> How the trap springs or the haunt manifests, their game effects, and whether or not it can reset.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Wounds:</strong> Haunts can be affected by the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing power}. When\n    the haunt is healed a number of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wounds]{Wounds} equal to the number listed here,\n    it's disabled.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Reset:</strong> After a certain duration, a haunt (even a disabled\n    one) resets to its original state. The duration is listed in the haunt. This\n    continues until the haunt is destroyed.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Destroying a Haunt:</strong> To completely destroy a haunt, its\n    source must be destroyed. This is usually listed before the haunt or in the\n    description. This will often involve destroying something, such as a cursed\n    corpse.\n  </p>\n  <h2 class=\"trap\">Collapsing Floor</h2>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Type:</strong> Mechanical; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Check:</strong> Yes, at\n    –2; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} Check:</strong> Yes, at –2\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Trigger:</strong> A hinged section of floor is rigged to give way.\n    Any Size 0 or larger creature entering the room triggers a collapse.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Effect:</strong> Victims fall 30 feet (3d6+3 damage) unless they\n    make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} roll to dive clear.\n  </p>\n  <h2 class=\"trap\">Vengeful spirit</h2>\n  <p><strong>Type:</strong> Haunt (6’ radius);</p>\n  <p><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Check:</strong> No (the spirit appears without warning);</p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Trigger:</strong> Proximity; <strong>Wounds:</strong> 1;\n    <strong>Reset:</strong> 1 day\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Effect:</strong> The spirit manifests in front of the victim,\n    causing him to make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} check when the ghostly image appears.\n  </p>\n  <div>\n    <img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/traps.webp\" />\n  </div>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4txb7iklyvb","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.uDgqEb6JpbCD4TSc"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":8},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"lZ1rVk9vwOOm0TuH","name":"Hindrances","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Hindrances</h1>\n<p>Hindrances are character flaws and physical handicaps that occasionally make life a little tougher for your hero.</p>\n<p>Some Hindrances have actual game effects. Other, more subjective “roleplaying” Hindrances help you understand and roleplay your character. They should occasionally cause her to act in ways that aren’t necessarily smart, efficient, or in the best interests of the party or the overall goal. That’s what roleplaying games are all about, and the GM should reward you with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies] when your Hindrances cause significant trouble.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Hindrance Summaries</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.All Thumbs]{All Thumbs} (Minor):</strong> –2 to use mechanical or electrical devices.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Anemic]{Anemic} (Minor):</strong> –2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Apprentice/Novice]{Apprentice/Novice} (Minor/Major): </strong>Cannot start with higher than a d6 in arcane skill, as Major start with one less power from the Arcane Background.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Arrogant]{Arrogant} (Minor):</strong> Likes to dominate his opponent, challenge the most powerful foe in combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bad Eyes]{Bad Eyes} (Minor/Major):</strong> –1 to all Trait rolls dependent on vision, or –2 as a Major Hindrance. Eyewear negates penalty but have a 50% chance of breaking when the hero suffers trauma.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bad Luck]{Bad Luck} (Major):</strong> The characters starts with one less @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} per session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Big Mouth]{Big Mouth} (Minor):</strong> Unable to keep secrets and constantly gives away private information.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Blind]{Blind} (Major):</strong> –6 to all tasks that require vision (but choice of a free Edge to offset).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bloodthirsty]{Bloodthirsty} (Major):</strong> Never takes prisoners.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Can't Swim]{Can't Swim} (Minor):</strong> –2 to swimming (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}) rolls; Each inch moved in water costs 3” of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Cautious]{Cautious} (Minor):</strong> The character plans extensively and/or is overly careful.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Chain of Command]{Chain of Command} (Minor/Major):</strong> You have to follow orders from a superior, as Major you are expendable.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Clueless]{Clueless} (Major):</strong> –1 to Common Knowledge and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Clumsy]{Clumsy} (Major):</strong> –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Code of Honor]{Code of Honor} (Major):</strong> The character keeps his word and acts like a gentleman.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Combat Shock]{Combat Shock} (Minor/Major):</strong> First round of combat make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} check, at –2 for Major Hindrance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Curious]{Curious} (Major):</strong> The character wants to know about everything.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Death Wish]{Death Wish} (Minor):</strong> The hero wants to die after or while completing some epic task.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Delusional]{Delusional} (Minor/Major):</strong> The individual believes something strange that causes him occasional or frequent trouble.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Dependent]{Dependent} (Minor):</strong> The hero has a dependant they must care for.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Deserter]{Deserter} (Minor/Major):</strong> The adventurer was a deserter from the Last War.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Driven]{Driven} (Minor/Major):</strong> The hero’s actions are driven by some important goal or belief.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Elderly]{Elderly} (Major):</strong> –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace}, running, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Agility, Strength, and Vigor}. Hero gets 5 extra skill points.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Enemy]{Enemy} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character has a recurring nemesis.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Fanatic]{Fanatic} (Major):</strong> The hero fanatically believes in his country, monarch, or religion.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Greedy]{Greedy} (Minor/Major):</strong> The individual is obsessed with wealth and material possessions.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Habit]{Habit} (Minor/Major):</strong> Addicted to something, suffers @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} if deprived.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Hard of Hearing]{Hard of Hearing} (Minor/Major):</strong> –4 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} sounds; automatic failure if completely deaf.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Heavy Sleeper]{Heavy Sleeper} (Major):</strong> –4 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} to wake up. –4 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Vigor} to stay awake.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Heroic]{Heroic} (Major):</strong> The character always helps those in need.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Hesitant]{Hesitant} (Minor):</strong> Draw two @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} and take the lowest (except Jokers, which may be kept).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Illiterate]{Illiterate} (Minor):</strong> The character cannot read or write.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Inept]{Inept} (Minor/Major):</strong> Start with 2 fewer skill points, 4 fewer as major.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Impulsive]{Impulsive} (Major):</strong> The hero leaps before he looks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Jealous]{Jealous} (Minor/Major):</strong> The individual covets what others have.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Lying Eyes]{Lying Eyes} (Minor):</strong> –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when lying. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Loyal]{Loyal} (Minor):</strong> The hero is loyal to his friends and allies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Mean]{Mean} (Minor):</strong> –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Mild Mannered]{Mild Mannered} (Minor):</strong> –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Mute]{Mute} (Major):</strong> The hero cannot speak.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Nightmares]{Nightmares} (Major):</strong> –1 penalty to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Spirit} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Obese]{Obese} (Minor):</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} +1, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} –1 and running die of d4. Treat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} as one die type lower for Min @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Obligation]{Obligation} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character has a weekly obligation of 20 (Minor) to 40 (Major) hours.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.One Arm]{One Arm} (Major):</strong> –4 to tasks (such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}) that require two hands.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.One Eye]{One Eye} (Major):</strong> –2 to actions at 5″ (10 yards) or more distance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Outsider]{Outsider} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character doesn’t fit in to the local environment and subtracts 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls. As a Major Hindrance she has no legal rights or other serious consequences.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Overconfident]{Overconfident} (Major):</strong> The hero believes she can do anything.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Pacifist]{Pacifist} (Minor/Major):</strong> Fights only in self-defense as a Minor Hindrance, won’t fight at all as Major.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Phobia]{Phobia} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character is afraid of something, and subtracts –1/–2 from all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait rolls} in its presence.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Poverty]{Poverty} (Minor):</strong> Half starting funds and the character is always broke.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Quirk]{Quirk} (Minor):</strong> The individual has some minor but persistent foible that often annoys others.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Ruthless]{Ruthless} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character does what it takes to get her way.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Secret]{Secret} (Minor/Major):</strong> The hero has a dark secret of some kind.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Shamed]{Shamed} (Minor/Major):</strong> The individual is haunted by some tragic event from her past.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Slow]{Slow} (Minor/Major):</strong> Pace –1, reduce running die one step. As Major, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} –2, –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} and rolls to resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}. Neither may take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed} Edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Small]{Small} (Minor):</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} are reduced by 1. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} cannot be reduced below –1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Stubborn]{Stubborn} (Minor):</strong> The character wants his way and rarely admits his mistakes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Suspicious]{Suspicious} (Minor/Major):</strong> The individual is paranoid. As a Major Hindrance, allies subtract 2 when rolling to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} him.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Thin Skinned]{Thin Skinned} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character is particularly susceptible to personal attacks. As a Minor Hindrance, he subtracts two when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} tests. As a Major, he subtracts four.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Tongue-Tied]{Tongue-Tied} (Major):</strong> The character often misspeaks or can’t get her words out. –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Trouble Magnet]{Trouble Magnet} (Minor/Major):</strong> The adventurer always seems to attract the worst kind of trouble.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Ugly]{Ugly} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character is physically unattractive and subtracts 1 or 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Vengeful]{Vengeful} (Minor/Major):</strong> The adventurer seeks payback for slights against her. As a Major Hindrance, she’ll cause physical harm to get it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Vow]{Vow} (Minor/Major):</strong> The individual has pledged himself to some cause.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Wanted]{Wanted} (Minor/Major):</strong> The character is wanted by the authorities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Yellow]{Yellow} (Major):</strong> –2 to Fear checks and resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Young]{Young} (Minor/Major):</strong> Minor has 4 attribute points and 10 skill points, extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} per session. Major has 3 attribute points, 10 skill points, and two extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} per session.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><img class=\"centered\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/atmosphere/adventures-in-camp.webp\" /></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"m5GjQ6rQDecG4uBo","name":"Alchemical Items Table","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"8\">Alchemical Items</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"8\">\n<p>The following items may be found in most towns with an alchemist's shop.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Type</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Range</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Damage</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">AP</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">RoF</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Blast</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Weight</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist's Acid]{Alchemist's Acid}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">2d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{SBT}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">40 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>Thrown like a grenade. Those within the template take 2d4 damage when hit and 2d4&amp;ndash;2 damage at the start of their next turn unless the acid is washed off somehow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist's Acid]{Alchemist's Acid}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">2d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{SBT}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A sticky, flammable liquid that ignites on impact. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}. Those within the template take 2d4 damage when hit and 2d4&amp;ndash;2 damage at the start of their next turn unless dowsed with water. Target might catch @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{Fire}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Antitoxin]{Antitoxin, vial}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">.5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">75 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>Grants a +4 bonus to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} for one hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Holy Water (flask)]{Holy Water}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">2d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{SBT}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">25 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>Holy water can be thrown in a flask or splashed on an adjacent creature. Undead and certain evil creatures (DM's call) within the template take 2d4 damage when hit and 2d4–2 damage at the start of their next turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Smokestick]{Smokestick}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">.25</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>An alchemically treated stick that creates thick smoke (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark illumination}) in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} for one minute. Dissipates in strong wind in one round.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Smokestick, Noxious]{Smokestick, Noxious}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">.5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">125 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>An alchemically treated stick that creates thick smoke (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark illumination}) in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} for one minute. Dissipates in strong wind in one round. Those in the cloud must roll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} check or become @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} from retching and coughing.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sunrod]{Sunrod}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A gold and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} tipped iron rod that provides normal light in a 30 foot radius for six hours. It increases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} one level for another 30' beyond that. It emits no heat, and counts as sunlight.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tanglefoot bag]{Tanglefoot bag}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1/2/4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A Size 3 or smaller victim hit by this small sack of sticky materials is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} for five rounds and must make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll or be stuck to the ground (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Entangled}) as well.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Thunderstone]{Thunderstone}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">30 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>An alchemical rock with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} that explodes with a deafening boom when struck against a hard surface. Anyone a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} as well as deafened for one hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tindertwig]{Tindertwig}</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">3/6/12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">—</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">1 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A thin stick that alights with flame when struck against a hard surface. It allows torches and other flammable substances to be lit in a single action.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dl21vgq63wq","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear tables","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.m5GjQ6rQDecG4uBo"}}}
{"_id":"m6ZepPJClhZFJ4wY","name":"Recharging","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n    <h2>Recharging</h2>\n    <p>A character recovers 5 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points} per hour spent resting.</p>\n  <p>\n    What constitutes rest is up to the GM, but generally, it means sitting,\n    eating, tending wounds, sleeping, and avoiding any strenuous activity.\n    Walking or riding a horse isn’t usually restful, but riding in a cushioned\n    carriage might be.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    A few interruptions don’t stop a character from resting— standing watch,\n    planning, sharpening weapons, and so on (GM’s call).\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    An arcane hero can also spend a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to regain five Power Points. This is a\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Actions]{free action}.\n  </p>\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{See full Powers rules here}</p>\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Powers]{See full Powers list here}</p>\n&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; Updated upstream\n    <p>@Compendium[@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{See full Power Modifiers list here}</p>\n=======\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{See full Power Modifiers list here}</p>\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Stashed changes\n    \n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Activation]{See full rules here}</p>\n    \n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_inkjjer1fuj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/Powers keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.rSG4djOEOKNfAvx3"}}}
{"_id":"m8ahWJhuIzJHdCig","name":"Fanatics","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Fanatics</h2>\n<p>Use this rule in pulp-style games where henchmen are numerous and villains are larger than life.</p>\n<p>When a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} enemy character is hit by a successful attack and the GM thinks it’s appropriate, one of his henchmen, goons, or other allies jumps in front of his master and takes the attack instead.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rv4q29jrhjs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.wWGnMNZeZ0RRJLre"}}}
