{"_id":"xgmHA9e9X6RAoW2d","name":"Finishing Move","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Finishing Move</h2>\n\t<p>A completely helpless victim may be dispatched with a lethal weapon of some sort as an action. \n\t\tThis is automatic unless the GM decides there’s a special situation, such as a particularly tough or naturally armored victim, \n\t\ta chance for escape, and so on.</p>\n\t<p>The killer must usually dispatch his foe up close and personal, but the GM may occasionally let @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Finishing Move]{Finishing Moves}\n\t\tbe performed at range if the situation warrants.</p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Situational Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bljq2qm1bis","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Situational Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.erLS1IOYC2IqwWnI"}}}
{"_id":"xiTSCAfKilYsU8qL","name":"Critical Failures","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Critical Failures</h2>\n  <p>A Critical Failure occurs when a Wild Card rolls a 1 on both the skill die and Wild Die of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait roll}. \n    The attempt automatically fails and something bad happens--a weapon is dropped or gets stuck, the attack hits a friend, the vehicle crashes, spells misfire \n    (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Backlash]{Backlash}</strong>), and so on.</p>\n<p>Critical Failures cannot be rerolled by any means, even with <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies}</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Extras and Critical Failures:</strong> If an Extra rolls a 1 on a Trait check <em>and it’s important to know if it’s a Critical Failure</em>, \n    such as when casting a spell, roll a d6. On a 1, it’s a Critical Failure. Otherwise it’s just a normal failure.</p>\n<p><strong>Multiple Dice:</strong> Some abilities allow characters to roll multiple Trait dice, such as the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} Edge or firing a weapon with a Rate of Fire higher than 1. A Critical Failure with multiple dice occurs when more than half the die results are a natural 1. If the character is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}, the Wild Die <em>must</em> be a 1 as well.</p>\n\n<blockquote class=\"flavor\"><em><strong>Example:</strong></em> \n    A fighter with the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} Edge rolls two Fighting dice and one Wild Die. If two or more of the dice come up 1s, including the Wild Die, it’s a Critical Failure.\n</blockquote>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.old5bWCeFVnGyd4k"}}}
{"_id":"xirPwt6MtSTuoGxd","name":"Half-giant","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Half-giant</h1>\n<p>Coming from either Sarlona or Xen’drik, they are now a true-breeding stock from the ancient Titans of Xen’drik. Half-giants, for the most part, retain human sensibilities. They are curious, interested in cooperation and communication, and have a general tendency toward kindness. (Half-Giants are from Sarlona and Xen’drik, talk to your DM if you want to play this race.)</p>\n<p>Perhaps the most baffling of all the races on the continent, the nomadic half-giants of Sarlona are descendants of ancient giant explorers from Xen'drik. Some say the half-giants are degenerate offspring of the Xen'drik titans, while others contend they have a mixed human ancestry.</p>\n<p>What can be said is that the true-breeding half-giants are racially inclined toward psionic ability, and this racial trait binds them into tight-knit but individually isolated bands. Half-giants refer to their groups as families, rather than tribes or clans, although few members of a family are actually blood-related. In fact, many families adopt individuals of other races, particularly psionic ones such as elans, dromites, duergar, and maenads.</p>\n<h3>Half-Giant Lands</h3>\n<p>Half-giant families wander endlessly all over Sarlona, although they rarely stray into Riedran territory. There, they are often \"assimilated\"—a process beginning as slavery. What is remarkable is the degree to which they tend to coexist peaceably with denizens of all other regions. In Tashana, where families are known collectively as the Icebinders, half-giants have a long tradition of trade and cooperation with the shifter and human tribes. The Sandstrider families of Syrkarn keep more to themselves, with occasional but minimal conflict with the humans and eneko of the region. In Adar, a handful of half-giant families called the pathadrik wander among the settlements and monasteries.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Cumbersome]{Cumbersome}: </strong>Half-giants aren't the most dextrous of creatures. They suffer a −1 penalty to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Agility} rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Fire Acclimated]{Fire Acclimated}:</strong> Half-giants are accustomed to enduring high temperatures. They gain a +4 bonus to resist the effects of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heat]{heat} and fire. Damage from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heat]{heat} and fire is also reduced by 4.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Natural Brute]{Natural Brute}:</strong> Half-giants have natural core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Agility} for purposes of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}. The character may also resist Athletics @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} with Strength if she chooses. Finally, half-giants increase the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Medium Range}, and double again for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Long Range}. If a thrown item’s Range is 3/6/12, for example, a half-giant's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} is 4/8/16.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Outsider (Eneko)]{Outsider (Minor)}:</strong> Most other races are put off by half-giants due to their abnormally large size. In fact, many are at first taken for young (if strangely well-groomed) hill giants. They have −2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} as other races tend to distrust them.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} +1:</strong> Half-giants are much larger than humans, standing about 6 ½ − 8 feet tall, increasing thier @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}) by 1. This increases their maximum @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Strength} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Stomp]{Stomp}:</strong> With a forceful stomp of their foot, half-giants can create a wave of trembling earth. With a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll, targets caught within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} originating from the half-giant’s step are knocked @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{Prone}; with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, they are also @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/half-giant.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/half-giant.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.vXetYPQjtecEgRPV"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"xnM0pGSbPLv4BpAC","name":"Fortification","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Armor Enchantment</h3>\n<p>Fortified armor is more likely to turn away a lethal blow. The wearer gains a free reroll on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 2</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 5,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost trait}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"xuMPcSWIpHiuFyV6","name":"Lingering Damage","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n    <h2>Lingering Damage (+2), Modifier</h2>\n    <p>The target is hit by fire, cold, acid, gnawing insects, or some other\n        @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trapping} that continues to cause damage after the initial attack. On the\n        victim’s next turn, he suffers the power’s base damage minus one die type\n        (for one additional turn only). If hit with a 2d6 <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>, for\n        example, the victim takes 2d4 damage at the start of his next turn. If the\n        base damage is already a d4 die type, it is d4–2 instead.</p>\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{See full Powers rules here}</p>\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Powers]{See full Powers list here}</p>\n&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; Updated upstream\n    <p>@Compendium[@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{See full Power Modifiers list here}</p>\n=======\n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{See full Power Modifiers list here}</p>\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Stashed changes\n    \n    \n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_inkjjer1fuj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/Powers keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.xBbCQfgYSuxA8bbi"}}}
{"_id":"y0dO9T77wFZcQftr","name":"5 Vehicles","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Vehicles</h1>\n<p>Below are a number of sample vehicles (conveyances) for land, air, and water on Eberron.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Size:</span> The Size and Scale of the vehicle relative to a human (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}</strong> and the <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Size Table]{Size Table}</strong>.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Handling:</span> The vehicle’s responsiveness and maneuverability is added or subtracted from all its operator’s maneuvering rolls (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Driving]{Driving}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding}). This typically ranges from −4 for particularly slow or sluggish vehicles to +4 for those that can turn on a dime.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Top Speed:</span> Top Speed is expressed in miles per hour (MPH) for easy comparison to the real world. To convert miles per hour to Pace, multiply MPH by 1.5.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Toughness:</span> The vehicle’s base durability, including Armor in parentheses. Use these as guides when creating your own.<br />Vehicles can normally take three Wounds before they’re <strong>Wrecked</strong> (see below), but Large Vehicles can take one additional Wound, Huge vehicles two, and Gargantuan three.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Passengers:</span> The number of crew plus any additional passengers it can transport. A notation of “2+8,” for example, means it requires a crew of two and can carry up to eight additional passengers. <br />A vehicle without enough crew may not be able to operate all its weapons or other devices.<br />Ships and the like that require multiple crew to work their sails lose 10% Top Speed and subtract 1 from Handling if under crewed. The GM can multiply these effects if the vehicle is drastically undermanned, or it might simply be effectively immobile.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Cost:</span> The typical price of the vehicle in Eberron. This will vary widely depending on the type of vehicle, the environment, its condition, and other market factors.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Vehicle Notes</h2>\n<p><strong>Heavy Armor:</strong> Only weapons marked as Heavy Weapons can hurt this vehicle, regard­less of the damage roll. This keeps a lucky bow shot from destroying a longship, for example. Vehicles with Heavy Armor halve damage they take from colliding with other obstacles (including vehicles) that don’t have Heavy Armor. This is not to be confused with the heavy category of personal armor.</p>\n<p><strong>Weapons:</strong> Vehicles with weapons note their location for narrative play or when using miniatures on the tabletop. Here are the most common:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Fixed:</span> The vehicle’s weapon fires only in the listed direction (typically front or rear in a 45° arc).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Swivel Mount:</span> The weapon is mounted on a post or platform that can turn and fire in a 180° arc in the listed direction.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Turret:</span> The weapon is in a turret and can freely fire in a 360° arc.</li>\n</ul>\n<div><img src=\"modules/swpf-core-rules/assets/art/jewelry.webp\" /></div>\n<aside class=\"sidebar\">\n<h1>Vehicle damage</h1>\n<p>A vehicle can take three Wounds before it’s wrecked. Each Wound subtracts 10% of its Top Speed and reduces Handling by −1.</p>\n<p>If a fast-moving (GM’s call) vehicle such as a coach or wagon wrecks, all the passengers inside take 3d6 damage. Anyone riding on the outside of a coach or wagon when it wrecks takes 4d6 damage.</p>\n<p>Double the damage if the device was flying at significant altitude (at least a few hundred feet).</p>\n</aside>\n<div>\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Vehicles</h1>\n</div>\n<table><colgroup> <col></col> <col></col> <col></col> <col></col> <col></col> <col></col> <col></col> </colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"7\">Ground Vehicles</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Vehicle</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Size</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Handling</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Top Speed <br />(MPH)</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Toughness</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Crew</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Carriage]{Carriage}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1+3</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">100</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Pulled by one <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Horse, Light]{Horse}</strong>. Pace on the tabletop is 12 and it may run.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Cart]{Cart}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6/4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">15</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Pulled by one <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Horse, Light]{Horse} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Mule]{Mule}</strong>. Pace on the tabletop is 9/6 for the horse/mule and it may run.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Sled]{Sled}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4 <br />(Large)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">0</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">2+4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Wagon on runners for snow and ice travel. Pulled by two or more beasts. Pace on the tabletop is 6, and it may run.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Wagon, light]{Wagon, light}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4 <br />(Large)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">2+4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">35</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Pulled by two @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Horse, Light]{horses}. Pace on the tabletop is 12 and it may run.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Wagon, heavy]{Wagon, heavy}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6 <br />(Large)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4+8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">100</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Pulled by four @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Horse, Light]{horses}. Pace on the tabletop is 12 and it may run.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"7\">Airships</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Vehicle</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Size</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Handling</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Top Speed <br />(MPH)</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Toughness</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Crew</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Airship (dirigible)]{Airship (dirigible)}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8 <br />(Huge)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1+9</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">50,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Quite rare on Eberron. This exotic vessel is a sailing ship connected by heavy chains to a massive balloon which holds it aloft.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Alchemical Dragon]{Alchemical Dragon}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">11 <br />(Huge)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">0</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">12</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">14 (2)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10+50</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">100,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Extremely rare on Eberron. Warship shaped as dragon with magical/alchemical engines.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Glider]{Glider}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4 <br />(Large)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−4</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">500</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> A light wooden frame with wing-like sails.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"7\">Watercraft</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Vehicle</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Size</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Handling</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Top Speed <br />(MPH)</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Toughness</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Crew</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Galley]{Galley}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">13 <br />(Gar)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20 (4)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20+80</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">30,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Heavy Armor. Has both oars and sails. <em><strong>Weapons:</strong></em> Catapult (Fixed Front).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Keelboat]{Keelboat}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10 <br />(Huge)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">0</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">16 (4)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">12+80</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Heavy Armor. Has oars and a single mast with square sail.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Longship]{Longship}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10 <br />(Huge)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">16 (4)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20+80</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Heavy Armor. Has numerous oars, no sails.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Sailing Ship]{Sailing Ship}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10 <br />(Huge)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−1</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">15</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">14 (2)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5+9</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Heavy Armor. Has two masts and square sails.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Sailing Sloop]{Sailing Sloop}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8 <br />(Huge)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">25</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">12 (2)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20+80</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">25,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Heavy Armor. Has one mast and fore-and-aft rigged sails.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Warship (Galleon)]{Warship (Galleon)}</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">14 <br />(Gar)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">−2</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">9</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20 (4)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">20+80</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">50,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\"><em><strong>Notes:</strong></em> Heavy Armor. <em><strong>Weapons:</strong></em> 16× to 46× Cannon (Fixed Left and Right).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7e7xz1a6a2k","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.hd1vYHjuEkfsOTx7"}}}
{"_id":"y0tFVn3lsueQwcFv","name":"Natural Healing","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Natural Healing</h2>\n  <p>\n    Wounded characters make a Vigor roll every five days. Success recovers one\n    @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wounds]{Wound}, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} recovers two.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    A  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} <em>increases</em> the victim’s Wound level by  one--\n    either from infection, blood loss, or aggravating the injuries. If this causes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Incapacitation]{Incapacitation}, \n    don’t use the usual rules for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Applying Damage]{taking damage}. Instead, the victim lapses in and out of consciousness and makes a Vigor roll every 12 hours. \n    If the roll is failed, he expires. Success means he must roll again 12 hours later. With a raise he stabilizes and wakes. Allies may also attempt to stabilize the hero \n    as explained under <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bleeding Out]{Bleeding Out}</strong>.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Support:</strong> Don’t forget to use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} when your party has\n    been beaten up a bit. Characters with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}, or other \n    skills can make Support rolls to help allies make their Vigor rolls to heal!\n  </p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.3 Healing]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yxu1ag41di","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Healing keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.0mXbWRGRrdwUlEeY"}}}
{"_id":"y6BQv2y9uHLes7t7","name":"Aces","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Aces</h2>\n  <p>All @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Traits]{Trait} and damage rolls in <cite>Savage Eberron</cite> are open-ended. \n    That means that when you roll the highest number possible on a die (a 6 on a d6, an 8 on a d8, and so on), you get to roll that die again and add it to the total. \n    This is called an “Ace.” Any modifiers to the die roll should be tacked on after adding up an Aced roll.</p>\n\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Rules]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.n696wk9srNDXvArJ"}}}
{"_id":"y9SAck4ETc6t8C1w","name":"Duration","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n    <h2></h2>\n    <p>How long the power lasts in rounds (unless\n        otherwise noted).</p>\n    <p>\n    Powers expire at the end of the character’s turn X rounds later, where X is\n    the Duration listed. Count the round the power activated. If the cleric\n    activates <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait}</em> (Duration 5) on the second round of\n    combat, for example, it remains in place until the end of her turn on the\n    sixth round.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Powers may be maintained for their base Duration for 1 Power Point per\n    individual.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Unless it says otherwise, the caster can terminate a power she’s\n    activated as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Actions]{free actions}. She must terminate the entire power— she can’t\n    leave it on for some and off for others.\n  </p>    \n    <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Powers]{See full Powers section here}</p>\n    \n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_inkjjer1fuj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/Powers keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.P2AxROWk0MpK4Pom"}}}
{"_id":"yGwYvwZWtIZ14rDe","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","content":"","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0urjihl2ptj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Rules keywords","color":"#000000","name":"Rules keywords","children":["y6BQv2y9uHLes7t7","jSA0o4irVBr0TBvk","KSMBz6b82i7E4UsI","xiTSCAfKilYsU8qL","oPEbUM3YO1HnjWZU","eFHRMnTSnMT1r5Gl","Nf5GxdfgFzE1izmV","XxUbzwBbwfBWJfxA","9IkIEjNwnbMYYipu","qSksgGlXgKQhAvSO","Xb9qG3Vf9kH7qjRU","2rYVK0CG7eZ9Tbdn","3ecUSTKJMhi7L9xu","exM7tmeOZrp07Qp5","s6TBU0MflXkaeMd0"],"folderPath":["temp_5n9ndtjortv","temp_tl96ca99gn"]}}}
{"_id":"yIU3whNNgCXwDnJb","name":"Schools of Magic","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Schools of Magic</h1>\n<p><img class=\"right table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/people/wizard-at-study.webp\" width=\"265\" height=\"500\" /></p>\n<p>On Eberron, spells are categorized based on the effects generated by the power. These specialized groups are called schools. Any power not tied to a school of magic is considered to be a universal spell, such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{wish}</em>. There are eight schools of magic: Abjuration, Conjuration, Divination, Enchantment, Evocation, Illusion, Necromancy, and Transmutation.</p>\n<p>A spell is always considered to be from its school, no matter where it comes from. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em>, for example, is a Transmutation power, whether its cast from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}. The GM may decide, however, that a caster's specific trappings move the power into a different school for that caster (so a GM might rule that, while a typical barrier belongs to the conjuration school, a purely magical barrier might be an evocation spell instead).</p>\n<p>Knowing the schools of magic and their effects can be instrumental in identifying magical traps, weapons, items, or auras surrounding an opponent.</p>\n<p>Here are the various schools and the powers that belong to each. Note: these lists do not affect which powers an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Background} has access to. These lists simply identify which powers are associated to each particular school and the general focus of the school of magic.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Abjuration:</strong> The abjurer uses magic against itself, specializing in defensive magic.</li>\n<li><strong>Conjuration:</strong> Conjurers focus on spells to summon magical servants or bend reality to their will.</li>\n<li><strong>Divination:</strong> Diviners are masters of remote viewing and prophesies; they use their spells to explore the world.</li>\n<li><strong>Enchantment: </strong>The enchanter uses magic to manipulate the minds and perceptions of opponents.</li>\n<li><strong>Evocation: </strong>Evokers revel in the raw power of magic; they use spells to create and destroy with equal ease.</li>\n<li><strong>Illusion: </strong>Illusionists use magic to produce confounding sights, sounds and even smells to baffle and vex their opponents.</li>\n<li><strong>Necromancy: </strong>The dread necromancer commands undead and uses the foul power of unlife against enemies.</li>\n<li><strong>Transmutation: </strong>Transmuters use magic to change themselves and the world around them.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-columns-title\">Magic and Powers</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Activation]{Activation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Backgrounds}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers Summary List]{Powers Summary list}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cantrips]{Cantrips}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Schools of Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trappings}</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3> </h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":4},"cf":{"id":"temp_fsjso9rnq9","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Powers#/CF_SEP/4.1. Using Magic","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"yQK76yS3XPOXOxhK","name":"Actions","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Actions</h2>\n  <p>\n    Characters perform “actions” when their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} comes up each round.\n    This is their “turn.” A character can move (see <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Movement}</strong>,\n    below) and perform one regular action at any point in her movement,\n    attacking, casting a spell, and so on, without penalty.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Characters can choose from a multitude of actions on their turn. Common\n    actions include @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Supporting} allies, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Testing} foes, \n    using a power, or attacking with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}. \n    See <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions}</strong> to perform\n    more than one action per turn (though only one of these can be a limited\n    action).\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    More complex actions like lighting a torch or digging through a backpack\n    might require more than a round to complete (GM’s call).\n  </p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Combat]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aeejh0xnzv6","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Combat keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.XqbJwrUZsWzSXh8t"}}}
{"_id":"ySWIn9H7ny7rEYn7","name":"Dumb Luck","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Dumb Luck</h2>\n<p>Dumb Luck allows a player to spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} even after a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}. The failure still happens in some way, but the character can spend one Benny (and only one) for one more roll. The hero still drops her weapon, flubs her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, or otherwise “fails” the attempt—but if the reroll from the Benny is actually successful, it somehow still results in whatever success the new roll provides.</p>\n<p>A character trying to pick a lock might break the lock on a Critical Failure, for example, but only after cracking the lock. Or a warrior who fumbles a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll might hit a foe as if he’d thrown the weapon!</p>\n<p>The player and Game Master should work together to describe the scene in some fun or bizarre way that explains how the mishap ultimately results in success.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Red fires three shots from her submachine gun (Rate of Fire 3). She rolls a 1 on her Wild Die and two of her Shooting dice—a Critical Failure! The GM decides the sudden recoil makes her drop her gun.<br />Red’s player, Emily, calls on Dumb Luck and spends a Benny. The reroll results in two hits (one with a raise!). The GM says the weapon bounces on the ground and sprays randomly, hitting two of Red’s foes!</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rv4q29jrhjs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.hg2GtD4bvJMFT23j"}}}
{"_id":"yoUFXQcdUme8zOYF","name":"Dragonscale","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Dragonscale</h1>\n<p>Armorers can fashion their products with the scales of dragons when such wonders become available. The age of the dragon determines the bonus for dragonscalee items (+1 to +4, GM’s call). The armor isn't considered metal, and provides @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Enviromental Resistance]{enviromental resistance} for attacks the dragon was immune to. For example blue dragonscale gives resistance to electricity. Dragonscale costs 100 times its armor bonus.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Materials]{See Special Materials here}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Gear]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kfkrm0kt7s","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/Gear keywords","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"z2wBYh3zIVCSnxAX","name":"3 Races","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Races</h1>\n<p><cite>Savage Eberron </cite>includes fourteen recommended races and five particularly exotic racesfor use in character creation, along with abilities that reflect the most common or iconic virtues and drawbacks of each.</p>\n<p>Note that the following descriptions allude to a lot of rules we haven’t explained yet. Just skim them for now and come back once you have a grasp on the rest of the game.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Races</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bugbear]{Bugbear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Changeling]{Changeling}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarf}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elf}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gnome]{Gnome}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Goblin]{Goblin}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-elf]{Half-elf}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-orc]{Half-orc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Halfling]{Halfling}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hobgoblin]{Hobgoblin}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{Shifter}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Warforged]{Warforged}</p>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Exotic Races</h2>\n<p>The following races are far more exotic and rare in Eberron. These require DM approval for particular campaigns.</p>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf, Drow]{Elf, Drow}: Xen'drik</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Eneko]{Eneko}: Sarlona</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-giant]{Half-giant}: Sarlona and Xen'drik</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar}: Sarlona, Sharn and small other pockets</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Tiefling]{Tiefling}: Generally rare</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"zDplrIRoqRkzZOx1","name":"Speed","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h3>Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>If a melee weapon, the user gains the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} Edge. A ranged weapon increases its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{Rate of Fire} by 1, or reduces its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} time by one action. User’s choice for weapons that can be used either way.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 3</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 16,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Speed}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cgm3zn2v579","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/6. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/Enchantments keywords","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"zFxlQs1gS9a2yM3F","name":"Melee Attacks","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n  <h2>Melee Attacks</h2>\n  <p>\n    The Target Number to hit an opponent is equal to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} (2 plus half his\n    Fighting die type; 2 if he has no Fighting skill).\n  </p>\n  <p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Combat]{See full rules here}</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aeejh0xnzv6","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Rules#/CF_SEP/Combat keywords","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.C2JWS1veVTRYYGqH"}}}
